# BOOK	019	PSA	Psalms	Psalms
019	PSA	001	001	“BOOK I” Happy the man who walketh not in the counsel of the unrighteous, Nor standeth in the way of sinners, Nor sitteth in the seat of scoffers;
019	PSA	001	002	But whose delight is in the law of the LORD, And who meditateth on his precepts day and night.
019	PSA	001	003	He is like a tree planted by streams of water, That bringeth forth its fruit in its season, Whose leaves also do not wither: All that he doeth shall prosper.
019	PSA	001	004	Not so the unrighteous; They are like chaff, which the wind driveth away.
019	PSA	001	005	Therefore the wicked shall not stand in judgment, Nor sinners in the assembly of the just.
019	PSA	001	006	For the LORD knoweth the way of the righteous, But the way of the wicked leadeth to ruin.
019	PSA	002	001	Why do the heathen rage, And the nations meditate a vain thing?
019	PSA	002	002	Why do the kings of the earth rise up, And the princes combine together, Against Jehovah, and against his anointed king?
019	PSA	002	003	“Let us break their bonds asunder; Let us cast away from us their fetters!”
019	PSA	002	004	He that sitteth in heaven will laugh; The Lord will have them in derision.
019	PSA	002	005	Then shall he speak to them in his wrath, And confound them in his hot displeasure.
019	PSA	002	006	“I myself have anointed my king, Upon Zion, my holy hill!”
019	PSA	002	007	I will declare the decree of Jehovah: He hath said to me, “Thou art my son; This day I have begotten thee.
019	PSA	002	008	Ask of me, and I will give thee the nations for thine inheritance, And the ends of the earth for thy possession.
019	PSA	002	009	Thou shalt break them with a rod of iron; Thou shalt dash them in pieces like a potter's vessel.”
019	PSA	002	010	Be wise, therefore, O ye kings! Be admonished, ye rulers of the earth!
019	PSA	002	011	Be subject to Jehovah with awe, And fear with trembling!
019	PSA	002	012	Kiss the son, lest He be angry, and ye perish in your way; For soon shall his wrath be kindled. Happy are all they who seek refuge in him.
019	PSA	003	001	“A Psalm of David, when he fled from his son Absalom.” How many, O LORD, are mine enemies! How many are they who rise up against me!
019	PSA	003	002	How many are they who say of me, “There is no help for him with God”! (Pause)
019	PSA	003	003	But thou, O LORD! art my shield, My glory, and the lifter-up of my head.
019	PSA	003	004	I call upon the LORD with my voice, And he heareth me from his holy hill. (Pause)
019	PSA	003	005	I lay me down and sleep; I awake, for the LORD sustaineth me.
019	PSA	003	006	I will not fear the ten thousands of people Who on every side set themselves against me.
019	PSA	003	007	Arise, O LORD! Save me, O my God! For thou smitest the cheek of all my enemies; Thou breakest the teeth of the wicked.
019	PSA	003	008	Deliverance cometh from the LORD: May thy blessing be with thy people! (Pause)
019	PSA	004	001	“For the leader of the music; to be accompanied with stringed instruments. A psalm of David.” Hear me, when I call, O God of my righteousness! Thou hast helped me, when I was in trouble, —Have pity upon me, and hear my prayer!
019	PSA	004	002	How long, O men! will ye dishonor my dignity? How long will ye love vanity, and seek disappointment? (Pause)
019	PSA	004	003	Know ye that the LORD hath exalted one that is devoted to him; The LORD will hear, when I call upon him.
019	PSA	004	004	Stand in awe, and sin no more; Commune with your hearts upon your beds, and desist! (Pause)
019	PSA	004	005	Offer sacrifices of righteousness, And put your trust in the LORD!
019	PSA	004	006	There are many who say, Who will show us any good? LORD, lift thou up the light of thy countenance upon us!
019	PSA	004	007	Thou puttest gladness into my heart, Greater than theirs, when their corn and wine are abundant.
019	PSA	004	008	I will lay me down in peace, and sleep: For thou alone, O LORD! makest me dwell in safety.
019	PSA	005	001	“For the leader of the music; to be accompanied with wind instruments. A psalm of David.” Give ear to my words, O LORD; Have regard to my cry!
019	PSA	005	002	Listen to the voice of my supplication, my King and my God! For to thee do I address my prayer.
019	PSA	005	003	In the morning shalt thou hear my voice, O LORD! In the morning will I address my prayer to thee, and look for help.
019	PSA	005	004	For thou art not a God that hath pleasure in wickedness; The unrighteous man dwelleth not with thee.
019	PSA	005	005	The haughty shall not stand in thy sight; Thou hatest all that do iniquity.
019	PSA	005	006	Thou destroyest them that speak falsehood; The man of blood and deceit the LORD abhorreth.
019	PSA	005	007	But I, through thy great goodness, will come to thy house; In thy fear will I worship at thy holy temple.
019	PSA	005	008	Lead me, O LORD! in thy righteousness, because of mine enemies; Make thy path straight before my face!
019	PSA	005	009	For in their mouth there is no truth; Their heart is malignity; Their throat is an open sepulchre; They flatter with their tongue.
019	PSA	005	010	Requite them, O God! Let them be confounded in their devices; Cast them out for the multitude of their transgressions; For against thee have they rebelled!
019	PSA	005	011	But let all, that put their trust in thee, rejoice; Let them ever shout for joy, because thou defendest them; Let them, that love thy name, be joyful in thee!
019	PSA	005	012	For thou, O LORD! dost bless the righteous; With favor dost thou encompass him, as with a shield.
019	PSA	006	001	“For the leader of the music; to be accompanied with stringed instruments; to the octave. A psalm of David.” O LORD! rebuke me not in thine anger; Chasten me not in thy hot displeasure!
019	PSA	006	002	Have pity upon me, O LORD! for I am weak; Heal me, O LORD! for my bones tremble!
019	PSA	006	003	My soul, also, is sore troubled; And thou, O LORD! how long—?
019	PSA	006	004	Return, O LORD! and deliver me; Oh, save me according to thy mercy!
019	PSA	006	005	For in death no praise is given to thee; In the underworld who can give thee thanks?
019	PSA	006	006	I am weary with my groaning; All the night I make my bed to swim, And drench my couch with my tears.
019	PSA	006	007	Mine eye is wasted with grief; It hath become old because of all my enemies.
019	PSA	006	008	Depart from me, all ye that do iniquity; For the LORD heareth the voice of my weeping.
019	PSA	006	009	The LORD heareth my supplication; The LORD accepteth my prayer.
019	PSA	006	010	All my enemies shall be ashamed and utterly confounded; They shall be turned back, and put to shame suddenly.
019	PSA	007	001	“A psalm of David, which he sang to Jehovah, on account of the reproaches of Cush the Benjamite.” O Jehovah, my God! to thee do I look for help; Save me from them that persecute me, and deliver me!
019	PSA	007	002	Lest mine enemy tear me like a lion; Lest he rend me in pieces, while there is none to help.
019	PSA	007	003	O Jehovah, my God! if I have done this, —If there be iniquity upon my hands,
019	PSA	007	004	If I have rendered evil to my friend, Or have despoiled him that without cause is mine enemy, —
019	PSA	007	005	Let my adversary pursue and take me; Let him trample me to the ground, And lay me prostrate in the dust! (Pause)
019	PSA	007	006	Arise, O LORD! in thine anger; Lift thyself up against the rage of mine enemies; Awake for me, ordain judgment!
019	PSA	007	007	Let the assembly of the nations compass thee about, And on their account return to the height!
019	PSA	007	008	The LORD judgeth the nations; Judge me, O LORD! according to my righteousness, And requite me according to my integrity!
019	PSA	007	009	Oh, let the wickedness of the wicked be at an end; But establish the righteous! For the righteous God trieth the heart and the reins.
019	PSA	007	010	My shield is with God, Who saveth the upright in heart.
019	PSA	007	011	God is a righteous judge, And a God who is angry every day.
019	PSA	007	012	If he do not desist, He sharpeneth his sword; He bendeth his bow, and maketh it ready;
019	PSA	007	013	He prepareth for him the instruments of death; He shooteth his burning arrows.
019	PSA	007	014	Behold, he travailed with iniquity, And conceived mischief, But hath brought forth disappointment!
019	PSA	007	015	He made a pit and digged it. And is fallen into the ditch which he made.
019	PSA	007	016	His mischief returneth upon his own head, And his violence cometh down upon his own skull.
019	PSA	007	017	I will praise the LORD according to his righteousness; I will sing praise to the name of the LORD most high.
019	PSA	008	001	“For the leader of the music; to be accompanied with the gittith. A psalm of David.” O Jehovah, our Lord! How excellent is thy name in all the earth! Thou hast set thy glory above the heavens.
019	PSA	008	002	Out of the mouths of babes and sucklings hast thou ordained praise, To put thine adversaries to shame, And to silence the enemy and avenger.
019	PSA	008	003	When I consider thy heavens, the work of thy fingers, The moon and the stars which thou hast ordained:
019	PSA	008	004	What is man, that thou art mindful of him, And the son of man, that thou carest for him?
019	PSA	008	005	Yet thou hast made him little lower than God; Thou hast crowned him with glory and honor.
019	PSA	008	006	Thou hast given him dominion over the works of thy hands; Thou hast put all things under his feet, —
019	PSA	008	007	All sheep and oxen, Yea, and the beasts of the forest;
019	PSA	008	008	The birds of the air, and the fishes of the sea, And whatever passeth through the paths of the deep.
019	PSA	008	009	O Jehovah, our Lord, How excellent is thy name in all the earth!
019	PSA	009	001	“For the leader of the music; to be sung in the manner or with the voice of maidens. To the Benites, or to Ben. A psalm of David.” I will praise thee, O LORD! with my whole heart; I will show forth all thy marvellous works.
019	PSA	009	002	I will be glad and rejoice in thee: I will sing praise to thy name, O thou Most High!
019	PSA	009	003	All my enemies are turned back; They fall and perish at thy presence.
019	PSA	009	004	For thou dost defend my right and my cause; Thou sittest upon the throne, a righteous judge.
019	PSA	009	005	Thou rebukest the nations; Thou destroyest the wicked; Thou blottest out their name for evermore!
019	PSA	009	006	The enemy is fallen, —a desolation for ever! Thou, O LORD! hast destroyed their cities; Their memory itself hath perished!
019	PSA	009	007	The LORD reigneth for ever; He hath prepared his throne for judgment.
019	PSA	009	008	He judgeth the world in righteousness; He administereth judgment to the nations with uprightness.
019	PSA	009	009	Yea, the LORD is a refuge for the oppressed; A refuge in times of trouble.
019	PSA	009	010	They who know thy name put their trust in thee; For thou, O LORD! forsakest not them that seek thee!
019	PSA	009	011	Sing praises to the LORD, who reigneth in Zion; Declare his doings among the people!
019	PSA	009	012	As the avenger of blood, he remembereth the distressed; He forgetteth not their complaint.
019	PSA	009	013	“Have pity upon me, [said I,] O LORD! Look upon my affliction through them that hate me; Lift me up from the gates of death:
019	PSA	009	014	That I may show forth all thy praise in the gates of the daughter of Zion; That I may rejoice in salvation by thee.”
019	PSA	009	015	The nations have sunk into the pit which they made; In the net, which they hid, is their own foot taken.
019	PSA	009	016	Thus it is known that the LORD executeth judgment; The wicked are ensnared in the work of their own hands. [Stringed instruments. (Pause)
019	PSA	009	017	The wicked shall be driven into the underworld; Yea, all the nations that forger God.
019	PSA	009	018	For the poor shall not always be forgotten; The hopes of the afflicted shall not perish for ever.
019	PSA	009	019	Arise, O LORD! Let not man prevail; Let the nations be judged by thee!
019	PSA	009	020	Strike terror into them, O LORD! Let the nations know that they are but men! (Pause)
019	PSA	010	001	Why standest thou afar off, O LORD? Why hidest thou thyself in times of trouble?
019	PSA	010	002	Through the haughtiness of the wicked the poor are in distress; They are caught in the wiles which are contrived for them.
019	PSA	010	003	The wicked boasteth of his heart's desire; The rapacious renounceth and contemneth Jehovah.
019	PSA	010	004	The wicked [saith] in his haughtiness, “He careth not!” All his thoughts are, “There is no God.”
019	PSA	010	005	His course is always prosperous; Far in the heights are thy judgments from him; As for all his enemies, he puffeth at them.
019	PSA	010	006	He saith in his heart, “I shall never fall; I shall never be in adversity.”
019	PSA	010	007	His mouth is full of perjury, deceit, and oppression; Mischief and injustice are upon his tongue.
019	PSA	010	008	He sitteth in the lurking-places of the villages; In secret places doth he murder the innocent; His eyes are secretly fixed upon the poor.
019	PSA	010	009	He secretly lieth in wait, like a lion in a thicket; He lieth in wait to seize upon the helpless; He catcheth the poor, drawing him into his net.
019	PSA	010	010	He croucheth, and lowereth himself, And the wretched fall into his paws.
019	PSA	010	011	He saith in his heart, “God doth forget; He hideth his face; he doth never see it.”
019	PSA	010	012	Arise, O LORD! O God, lift up thine hand: Forget not the distressed!
019	PSA	010	013	Wherefore doth the wicked contemn God, And say in his heart, “He careth not for it”?
019	PSA	010	014	Thou dost see it; yea, thou beholdest malice and oppression, And markest it upon thy hand! The poor committeth himself to thee; Thou art the helper of the fatherless.
019	PSA	010	015	Break thou the arm of the unjust and wicked man; Seek out his wickedness, till thou canst find none!
019	PSA	010	016	Jehovah is king for ever and ever; The gentiles shall perish out of his land.
019	PSA	010	017	Thou, O LORD! wilt hear the desires of the distressed; Thou wilt strengthen their hearts; Thou wilt lend a listening ear!
019	PSA	010	018	Thou wilt maintain the cause of the fatherless and the oppressed, That henceforth none may be driven from the land.
019	PSA	011	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” In the LORD do I put my trust. Why say ye to me, “Flee, like a bird, to your mountain?
019	PSA	011	002	For, lo! the wicked bend their bow; They make ready their arrows on the string, To shoot in secret at the upright in heart.
019	PSA	011	003	If the pillars be broken down, What can the righteous do?”
019	PSA	011	004	The LORD is in his holy palace; The LORD'S throne is in heaven; His eyes behold, his eyelids prove the children of men.
019	PSA	011	005	The LORD trieth the righteous; But the wicked, and the lover of violence, his soul hateth.
019	PSA	011	006	Upon the wicked he will rain lightning; Fire and brimstone and a burning wind shall be the portion of their cup.
019	PSA	011	007	For the LORD is righteous; he loveth righteousness; The upright shall see his face.
019	PSA	012	001	“For the leader of the music; to the octave. A psalm of David.” Help, LORD; for the godly man ceaseth; The faithful are failing among men.
019	PSA	012	002	They speak falsehood one to another; With flattering lips, with a double heart, do they speak.
019	PSA	012	003	May the LORD destroy all flattering lips, And the tongue which speaketh proud things!
019	PSA	012	004	Who say, “With our tongues will we prevail; Our lips are our reliance; Who is lord over us?”
019	PSA	012	005	For the oppression of the poor and the sighing of the wretched, Now will I stand up, saith the LORD; I will set in safety him whom they puff at.
019	PSA	012	006	The words of the LORD are pure; Like silver purified in a furnace on the earth, Seven times refined.
019	PSA	012	007	Thou, O LORD! will watch over them; Thou wilt preserve them from this generation for ever.
019	PSA	012	008	The wicked walk on every side, When the vilest of men are exalted.
019	PSA	013	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” How long, O LORD! wilt thou forget me for ever? How long wilt thou hide thy face from me?
019	PSA	013	002	How long shall I have anxiety in my soul for ever, And sorrow in my heart all the day? How long shall my enemy be exalted over me?
019	PSA	013	003	Look down and hear me, O LORD, my God! Enlighten my eyes, lest I sleep the sleep of death;
019	PSA	013	004	Lest my enemy say, “I have prevailed against him!” Lest my adversaries rejoice, when I am fallen.
019	PSA	013	005	Yet will I trust in thy goodness; My heart shall rejoice in thy salvation;
019	PSA	013	006	I will sing to the LORD, that he hath dealt kindly with me.
019	PSA	014	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” The fool saith in his heart, “There is no God.” They are corrupt; abominable are their doings; There is none that doeth good.
019	PSA	014	002	Jehovah looketh down from heaven upon the children of men, To see if there are any that have understanding, That have regard to God.
019	PSA	014	003	They are all gone out of the way; together are they corrupt; There is none that doeth good—no, not one.
019	PSA	014	004	Shall not the evil-doers be requited, Who devour my people like bread, And call not upon Jehovah?
019	PSA	014	005	Yea, then shall they be in great fear; For Jehovah is with the race of the righteous.
019	PSA	014	006	Ye would put to shame the counsel of the poor; But Jehovah is their refuge.
019	PSA	014	007	Oh that salvation for Israel would come out of Zion! When Jehovah bringeth back the captives of his people, Then shall Jacob rejoice, and Israel be glad.
019	PSA	015	001	“A psalm of David.” LORD, who shall abide at thy tabernacle? Who shall dwell upon thy holy hill?
019	PSA	015	002	He that walketh uprightly, and doeth righteousness, And speaketh the truth from his heart;
019	PSA	015	003	He that slandereth not with his tongue, That doeth no injury to his neighbor, And uttereth no reproach against his neighbor;
019	PSA	015	004	In whose eyes a vile person is contemned; But who honoreth them that fear the LORD; Who sweareth to his own hurt, and changeth not;
019	PSA	015	005	He that lendeth not his money for interest, And taketh not a bribe against the innocent: He that doeth these things shall never be moved.
019	PSA	016	001	“A psalm off David.” Preserve me, O God! for to thee do I look for help.
019	PSA	016	002	I have said to Jehovah, Thou art my Lord; I have no happiness beyond thee!
019	PSA	016	003	The holy that are in the land, and the excellent, —in them is all my delight.
019	PSA	016	004	They who hasten after other gods shall have multiplied sorrows; Their drink-offerings of blood I will not offer, Nor will I take their names upon my lips.
019	PSA	016	005	Jehovah is my portion and my cup; Thou wilt maintain my lot!
019	PSA	016	006	My portion hath fallen to me in pleasant places; Yea, I have a goodly inheritance.
019	PSA	016	007	I will bless the LORD, who careth for me; Yea, in the night my heart admonisheth me.
019	PSA	016	008	I set the LORD before me at all times; Since he is at my right hand, I shall not fall.
019	PSA	016	009	Therefore my heart is glad, and my spirit rejoiceth; Yea, my flesh dwelleth in security.
019	PSA	016	010	For thou wilt not give me up to the underworld; Nor wilt thou suffer thy holy one to see the pit.
019	PSA	016	011	Thou wilt show me the path of life; In thy presence is fulness of joy; At thy right hand are pleasures for evermore.
019	PSA	017	001	“A psalm of David.” Hear the righteous cause, O LORD! Attend to my cry; Give ear to my prayer from lips without deceit!
019	PSA	017	002	May my sentence come forth from thy presence; May thine eyes behold uprightness!
019	PSA	017	003	Provest thou my heart, visitest thou me in the night, Triest thou me like gold, thou shalt find nothing!
019	PSA	017	004	My thoughts do not vary from my lips. As to the deeds of men, Through the word of thy lips I have kept me from the paths of the destroyer.
019	PSA	017	005	Support my steps in thy paths, That my feet may not slip!
019	PSA	017	006	I call upon thee, O God! for thou wilt hear me; Incline thine ear to me, and listen to my prayer!
019	PSA	017	007	Show forth thy loving-kindness, O thou that savest by thy right hand Them that seek refuge in thee from their adversaries!
019	PSA	017	008	Guard me as the apple of the eye; Hide me under the shadow of thy wings
019	PSA	017	009	From the wicked who assault me, From my deadly enemies who compass me about!
019	PSA	017	010	They shut up their hard heart; With their mouth they speak haughtily.
019	PSA	017	011	They encompass us in all our steps; They fix their eyes upon us, that they may cast us on the ground.
019	PSA	017	012	They are like a lion, eager for his prey; Like a young lion, lurking in secret places.
019	PSA	017	013	Arise, O LORD! disappoint them, cast them down! Deliver me from the wicked by thy sword,
019	PSA	017	014	From men, by thy hand, O LORD! from men of the world, Whose portion is in life; whom thou loadest with thy treasure; Whose children have enough, and leave their superfluity to their children.
019	PSA	017	015	But I through righteousness shall see thy face; I shall be satisfied with the revival of thy countenance.
019	PSA	018	001	I love thee, O LORD, my strength!
019	PSA	018	002	Jehovah is my rock, my fortress, and my deliverer; My God, my strength, in whom I trust; My shield, my strong defence, and my high tower.
019	PSA	018	003	I called upon the LORD, who is worthy to be praised, And was delivered from my enemies.
019	PSA	018	004	The snares of death encompassed me; The floods of destruction filled me with dismay;
019	PSA	018	005	The snares of the underworld surrounded me, And the nets of death seized upon me.
019	PSA	018	006	In my distress I called upon the LORD, And cried unto my God; He heard my voice from his palace, And my cry came before him into his ears.
019	PSA	018	007	Then the earth quaked and trembled; The foundations of the mountains rocked and were shaken, Because his wrath was kindled.
019	PSA	018	008	A smoke went up from his nostrils, And fire from his mouth devoured; Burning coals shot forth from him.
019	PSA	018	009	He bowed the heavens, and came down; And darkness was under his feet;
019	PSA	018	010	And he rode upon a cherub, and did fly; Yea, he did fly upon the wings of the wind.
019	PSA	018	011	And he made darkness his covering; His pavilion round about him was dark waters and thick clouds of the skies.
019	PSA	018	012	At the brightness before him, his thick clouds passed away; Then came hailstones and coals of fire.
019	PSA	018	013	The LORD also thundered from heaven, And the Most High uttered his voice, Amid hailstones and coals of fire.
019	PSA	018	014	He sent forth his arrows, and scattered them; Continual lightnings, and discomfited them.
019	PSA	018	015	Then the channels of the deep were seen, And the foundations of the earth were laid bare At thy rebuke, O LORD! At the blast of the breath of thy nostrils.
019	PSA	018	016	He stretched forth his hand from above; he took me, And drew me out of deep waters.
019	PSA	018	017	He delivered me from my strong enemy; From my adversaries, who were too powerful for me.
019	PSA	018	018	They fell upon me in the day of my calamity; But the LORD was my stay.
019	PSA	018	019	He brought me forth into a large place; He delivered me, because he delighted in me.
019	PSA	018	020	The LORD hath rewarded me according to my righteous; According to the cleanness of my hands hath he recompensed me.
019	PSA	018	021	For I have kept the ways of the LORD, And have not wickedly departed from my God.
019	PSA	018	022	For all his laws were in my sight; I did not put away his statutes from me.
019	PSA	018	023	I was upright before him, And kept myself from iniquity.
019	PSA	018	024	Therefore hath the LORD rewarded me according to my righteousness, According to the cleanness of my hands before his eyes.
019	PSA	018	025	To the merciful thou showest thyself merciful; To the upright thou showest thyself upright;
019	PSA	018	026	To the pure thou showest thyself pure, And to the perverse thou showest thyself perverse.
019	PSA	018	027	For thou savest the afflicted people, But the haughty countenance thou bringest down.
019	PSA	018	028	Thou causest my lamp to shine; Jehovah, my God, enlighteneth my darkness.
019	PSA	018	029	For through thee I have broken through troops; Through my God I have leaped over walls.
019	PSA	018	030	The ways of God are just and true; His word is pure, tried in the fire; He is a shield to all who put their trust in him.
019	PSA	018	031	Who, then, is God, save Jehovah? And who is a rock, save our God?
019	PSA	018	032	It is God that girded me with strength, And made my way plain.
019	PSA	018	033	He made my feet like the hind's, And set me in my high places;
019	PSA	018	034	He taught my hands to war, So that my arm bent the bow of brass.
019	PSA	018	035	Thou gavest me the shield of thy protection; Thy right hand held me up, And thy goodness made me great.
019	PSA	018	036	Thou didst make a wide path for my steps, So that my feet did not stumble.
019	PSA	018	037	I pursued my enemies and overtook them, And turned not back till I had destroyed them.
019	PSA	018	038	I smote them, so that they could not rise; They fell under my feet.
019	PSA	018	039	Thou didst gird me with strength for the battle; Thou didst cast down my adversaries under me.
019	PSA	018	040	Thou didst cause my enemies to turn their backs, So that I destroyed them that hated me.
019	PSA	018	041	They cried, but there was none to help; To Jehovah, but he answered them not.
019	PSA	018	042	I beat them small, like dust before the wind; I cast them out as the dirt of the streets.
019	PSA	018	043	Thou hast delivered me from the assaults of the nations; Thou hast made me the head of the kingdoms. Nations whom I knew not serve me;
019	PSA	018	044	They who have only heard of me obey me; Yea, men of a strange land submit themselves to me;
019	PSA	018	045	Men of a strange land fade away, like a leaf, And come trembling from their strongholds.
019	PSA	018	046	Jehovah is the living God; blessed be my rock; Exalted be the God of my salvation!
019	PSA	018	047	It is God who hath given me vengeance, And subdued the nations under me;
019	PSA	018	048	He delivered me from my enemies; Yea, thou hast lifted me up above my adversaries; Thou hast saved me from the violent man!
019	PSA	018	049	Therefore I will give thanks to thee, O LORD! among the nations, And sing praises to thy name.
019	PSA	018	050	Great deliverance giveth he to his king, And showeth mercy to his anointed, —To David and to his posterity for ever.
019	PSA	019	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” The heavens declare the glory of God; The firmament showeth forth the work of his hands.
019	PSA	019	002	Day uttereth instruction unto day, And night showeth knowledge unto night.
019	PSA	019	003	They have no speech nor language, And their voice is not heard;
019	PSA	019	004	Yet their sound goeth forth to all the earth, And their words to the ends of the world. In them hath he set a tabernacle for the sun,
019	PSA	019	005	Which cometh forth like a bridegroom from his chamber, And rejoiceth, like a strong man, to run his course.
019	PSA	019	006	He goeth forth from the extremity of heaven, And maketh his circuit to the end of it; And nothing is hid from his heat.
019	PSA	019	007	The law of the LORD is perfect, reviving the soul; The precepts of the LORD are sure, making wise the simple;
019	PSA	019	008	The statutes of the LORD are right, rejoicing the heart; The commandments of the LORD are pure, enlightening the eyes;
019	PSA	019	009	The fear of the LORD is clean, enduring for ever; The judgments of the LORD are true and righteous altogether.
019	PSA	019	010	More precious are they than gold; yea, than much fine gold; Sweeter than honey and the honeycomb.
019	PSA	019	011	By them also is thy servant warned, And in keeping of them there is great reward.
019	PSA	019	012	Who knoweth his own offences? Oh, cleanse thou me from secret faults!
019	PSA	019	013	Keep back also thy servant from presumptuous sins; Let them not have dominion over me! Then shall I be upright; I shall not be polluted with gross transgression.
019	PSA	019	014	May the words of my mouth and the meditation of my heart Be acceptable in thy sight, O LORD, my strength and my redeemer!
019	PSA	020	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” May Jehovah hear thee in the day of trouble; May the name of the God of Jacob defend thee!
019	PSA	020	002	May he send thee help from his sanctuary, And strengthen thee out of Zion!
019	PSA	020	003	May he have regard to all thine offerings, And accept thy burnt sacrifice! (Pause)
019	PSA	020	004	May he grant thee thy heart's desire, And fulfill all thy purposes!
019	PSA	020	005	We will rejoice in thy protection, And in the name of our God will we set up our banners, When Jehovah hath fulfilled all thy petitions.
019	PSA	020	006	Now I know that Jehovah helpeth his anointed; That he heareth him from his holy heaven, And aideth him with the saving strength of his right hand.
019	PSA	020	007	Some glory in chariots, and some in horses, But we in the name of Jehovah our God.
019	PSA	020	008	They stumble and fall, But we stand and are erect.
019	PSA	020	009	The LORD save the king! May he hear us when we call!
019	PSA	021	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” The king rejoiceth in thy strength, O LORD! Yea, he doth greatly exult in thy protection.
019	PSA	021	002	Thou hast given him his heart's desire, And hast not denied him the request of his lips. (Pause)
019	PSA	021	003	Yea, thou hast met him with rich blessings, Thou hast placed a crown of pure gold upon his head.
019	PSA	021	004	He asked life of thee; thou gavest it him; Even long life, enduring for ever.
019	PSA	021	005	Great is his glory through thine aid; Honor and majesty hast thou laid upon him.
019	PSA	021	006	Thou hast made him blessed for evermore; Thou hast made him glad with the joy of thy countenance.
019	PSA	021	007	For the king trusteth in the LORD; And through the goodness of the Most High he shall never fall.
019	PSA	021	008	Thy hand shall overtake all thine enemies; Thy right hand shall overtake them that hate thee.
019	PSA	021	009	Thou wilt make them like a burning oven in the time of thine anger; Jehovah shall swallow them up in his wrath, And the fire shall devour them.
019	PSA	021	010	Their offspring shalt thou destroy from the earth, And their posterity from the sons of men.
019	PSA	021	011	For they spread a net of mischief against thee; They devised plots against thee, but they did not prevail.
019	PSA	021	012	Therefore thou wilt cause them to turn their backs; Thou wilt make ready thine arrows upon the strings against them.
019	PSA	021	013	Exalt thyself, O LORD! by thy strength! So will we sing, and praise thy mighty deeds.
019	PSA	022	001	“For the leader of the music. To the tune of “The hind of the morning.” A psalm of David.” My God, my God! why hast thou forsaken me? Why so far from mine aid, and from the words of my cry?
019	PSA	022	002	O my God! I cry during the day, but thou hearest not; In the night also, but I have no rest.
019	PSA	022	003	And yet thou art holy, Dwelling amid the praises of Israel!
019	PSA	022	004	Our fathers trusted in thee; They trusted, and thou didst save them.
019	PSA	022	005	They called upon thee, and were delivered; They trusted in thee, and were not put to shame.
019	PSA	022	006	But I am a worm, and not a man; The reproach of men, and the scorn of the people.
019	PSA	022	007	All who see me scoff at me; They open wide the lips; they shake the head.
019	PSA	022	008	“He trusted in the LORD, let him help him; Let him deliver him, since he delighted in him!”
019	PSA	022	009	Surely thou art he that didst bring me into the world; Thou didst make me lie secure upon my mother's breast!
019	PSA	022	010	Upon thee have I cast myself from my birth; Thou hast been my God from my earliest breath!
019	PSA	022	011	Oh, be not far from me, for trouble is near; For there is none to help!
019	PSA	022	012	Many bulls surround me; Strong bulls of Bashan close me in on every side.
019	PSA	022	013	They open their mouths wide against me, Like a ravening and roaring lion.
019	PSA	022	014	I am poured out like water, And all my bones are out of joint; My heart is become like wax; It melteth in my bosom.
019	PSA	022	015	My strength is dried up like an earthen vessel, And my tongue cleaveth to my jaws; Thou hast brought me to the dust of death!
019	PSA	022	016	For dogs have surrounded me; Bands of evil-doers have encompassed me, —Like lions my hands and my feet.
019	PSA	022	017	I can count all my bones; They gaze, and feast their eyes upon me.
019	PSA	022	018	They divide my garments among them, And for my vesture they cast lots.
019	PSA	022	019	But be not thou far from me, O LORD! O my strength! make haste to mine aid!
019	PSA	022	020	Deliver my life from the sword; My blood from the power of the dog;
019	PSA	022	021	Save me from the lion's mouth; Shield me from the horns of the buffaloes!
019	PSA	022	022	I will proclaim thy name to my brethren; In the midst of the congregation will I praise thee.
019	PSA	022	023	Praise him, ye worshippers of Jehovah! Extol him, all ye race of Jacob. And fear him, all ye race of Israel!
019	PSA	022	024	For he hath not despised nor abhorred the misery of the afflicted. Nor hath he hid his face from him; But when he cried unto him, he heard.
019	PSA	022	025	My praise shall be of thee in the great congregation; I will pay my vows before them that fear him!
019	PSA	022	026	The afflicted shall eat, and be satisfied; They that seek the LORD shall praise him; Your hearts shall be glad for ever and ever!
019	PSA	022	027	All the ends of the earth shall remember, and turn to Jehovah; All the families of the nations shall worship before thee!
019	PSA	022	028	For the kingdom is Jehovah's; He is the governor of the nations.
019	PSA	022	029	All the rich of the earth shall eat and worship; Before him shall they also bow, who are going down to the dust, Who cannot keep themselves alive.
019	PSA	022	030	The future generation shall serve him; The race which is to come shall hear of Jehovah.
019	PSA	022	031	They shall come, and declare his righteousness; His mighty deeds to the people that shall be born.
019	PSA	023	001	“A psalm of David.” The LORD is my shepherd: I shall not want.
019	PSA	023	002	He maketh me to lie down in green pastures; He leadeth me beside the still waters.
019	PSA	023	003	He reviveth my soul; He leadeth me in paths of safety, For his name's sake.
019	PSA	023	004	When I walk through a valley of deathlike shade, I fear no evil; for thou art with me; Thy crook and thy staff, they comfort me.
019	PSA	023	005	Thou preparest a table before me In the presence of mine enemies. Thou anointest my head with oil; My cup runneth over.
019	PSA	023	006	Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life, And I shall dwell in the house of the LORD for ever.
019	PSA	024	001	“A psalm of David.” The earth is the LORD'S, and all that is therein; The world, and they who inhabit it.
019	PSA	024	002	For he hath founded it upon the seas, And established it upon the floods.
019	PSA	024	003	Who shall ascend the hill of the LORD? And who shall stand in his holy place?
019	PSA	024	004	He that hath clean hands and a pure heart; Who hath not inclined his soul to falsehood, Nor sworn deceitfully.
019	PSA	024	005	He shall receive a blessing from the LORD, And favor from the God of his salvation.
019	PSA	024	006	This is the race of them that seek him; They that seek thy face are Jacob. (Pause)
019	PSA	024	007	Lift up your heads, O ye gates! Lift yourselves up, ye everlasting doors, That the king of glory may come in!
019	PSA	024	008	“Who is this king of glory?” Jehovah, strong and mighty; Jehovah, mighty in battle.
019	PSA	024	009	Lift up your heads, O ye gates! Lift yourselves up, ye everlasting doors, That the king of glory may enter in!
019	PSA	024	010	“Who is this king of glory?” Jehovah, God of hosts, he is the king of glory. (Pause)
019	PSA	025	001	“A psalm of David.” To thee, O LORD! do I lift up my soul.
019	PSA	025	002	O my God! I trust in thee; let me not be put to shame! Let not my enemies triumph over me!
019	PSA	025	003	Yea, none that hope in thee shall be put to shame: They shall be put to shame who wickedly forsake thee.
019	PSA	025	004	Cause me to know thy ways, O LORD! Teach me thy paths!
019	PSA	025	005	Lead me in thy truth, and teach me! For thou art the God from whom cometh my help; In thee do I trust at all times!
019	PSA	025	006	Remember thy loving-kindness, O LORD! and thy tender mercy, Which thou hast exercised of old!
019	PSA	025	007	Remember not the faults and transgressions of my youth! According to thy mercy remember thou me, For thy goodness' sake, O LORD!
019	PSA	025	008	Good and righteous is the LORD; Therefore showeth he to sinners the way.
019	PSA	025	009	The humble he guideth in his statutes, And the humble he teacheth his way.
019	PSA	025	010	All the doings of the LORD are mercy and truth To those who keep his covenant and his precepts.
019	PSA	025	011	For thy name's sake, O LORD, Pardon my iniquity; for it is great!
019	PSA	025	012	Who is the man that feareth the LORD? Him doth he show the way which he should choose.
019	PSA	025	013	He shall himself dwell in prosperity, And his offspring shall inherit the land.
019	PSA	025	014	The friendship of the LORD is with them that fear him, And he will teach them his covenant.
019	PSA	025	015	Mine eyes are ever directed to the LORD, For he will pluck my feet from the net.
019	PSA	025	016	Look upon me, and pity me; For I am desolate and afflicted!
019	PSA	025	017	Lighten the sorrows of my heart, And deliver me from my troubles!
019	PSA	025	018	Look upon my affliction and distress, And forgive all my sins!
019	PSA	025	019	Consider how many are my enemies, And with what violence they hate me!
019	PSA	025	020	Guard thou my life, and deliver me! Let me not be put to shame, for I have trusted in thee!
019	PSA	025	021	Let integrity and uprightness preserve me, For on thee do I rest my hope!
019	PSA	025	022	Redeem Israel, O God! from all his troubles!
019	PSA	026	001	“A psalm of David.” Be thou my judge, O LORD! for I have walked in uprightness. I have put my trust in the LORD, therefore shall I not fall.
019	PSA	026	002	Examine me, O LORD! and prove me; Try my reins and my heart!
019	PSA	026	003	For thy kindness is ever before my eyes, And I walk in thy truth.
019	PSA	026	004	I sit not with men of falsehood. And go not in company with dissemblers.
019	PSA	026	005	I hate the assembly of evil-doers, And do not sit with the wicked.
019	PSA	026	006	I wash my hands in innocence. And go around thine altar. O LORD!
019	PSA	026	007	To utter the voice of thanksgiving, And tell of all thy wondrous works.
019	PSA	026	008	O LORD! I love the habitation of thy house, The place where thine honor dwelleth!
019	PSA	026	009	Gather not my breath with sinners, Nor my life with men of blood,
019	PSA	026	010	In whose hands is mischief, And whose right hands are full of bribes!
019	PSA	026	011	But as for me, I walk in my integrity; Oh, redeem me, and be merciful to me!
019	PSA	026	012	My feet tread in a straight path; In the congregation will I bless the LORD.
019	PSA	027	001	“A psalm of David.” The LORD is my light and my salvation; Whom shall I fear? The LORD is the shield of my life; Of whom shall I be afraid?
019	PSA	027	002	When the wicked came upon me to devour me, Even my persecutors and enemies, they stumbled and fell.
019	PSA	027	003	Though a host should encamp against me, my heart shall not fear; Though war should rise against me, yet will I be confident.
019	PSA	027	004	One thing have I desired of the LORD; that do I yet seek; That I may dwell in the house of the LORD all the days of my life, To behold the grace of the LORD, And to gaze upon his temple.
019	PSA	027	005	For in the day of trouble he will hide me in his pavilion; Yea, in the secret place of his tabernacle will he shelter me; He will set me upon a rock.
019	PSA	027	006	Yea, already doth he lift my head above my enemies, who are around me; Therefore in his tabernacle will I offer sacrifices with the sound of trumpets; I will sing, yea, with instruments of music I will give praise to the LORD.
019	PSA	027	007	Hear my voice, O LORD! when I cry unto thee; Have pity upon me, and answer me!
019	PSA	027	008	When I think of thy precept, “Seek ye my face!” Thy face, LORD, do I seek.
019	PSA	027	009	O hide not thou thy face from me; Cast not thy servant away in displeasure! Thou hast been my help, do not leave me; Do not forsake me, O God, my helper!
019	PSA	027	010	For my father and my mother have forsaken me; But the LORD will take me up.
019	PSA	027	011	Teach me thy way, O LORD! And lead me in the right path, because of my enemies!
019	PSA	027	012	Give me not up to the will of my adversaries! For false witnesses have risen up against me, And such as breathe out injustice.
019	PSA	027	013	I trust that I shall see the goodness of the LORD In the land of the living. Hope thou in the LORD!
019	PSA	027	014	Be of good courage; let thy heart be strong; Hope thou in the LORD!
019	PSA	028	001	“A psalm of David.” To thee do I cry, O LORD! O my rock! be not silent to me, Lest, if thou answer me not, I become like those who go down to the pit!
019	PSA	028	002	Hear the voice of my supplication, when I cry unto thee, When I lift up my hands to thy most holy sanctuary!
019	PSA	028	003	Draw me not away with the impious, and with evil-doers, Who speak peace to their neighbors, while mischief is in their hearts!
019	PSA	028	004	Give them according to their deeds, and the wickedness of their doings; Give them according to the work of their hands; Render to them their desert!
019	PSA	028	005	For they regard not the doings of the LORD, nor the work of his hands; Therefore will he destroy them, and not again build them up.
019	PSA	028	006	Praised be the LORD, for he hath heard the voice of my supplications!
019	PSA	028	007	The LORD is my strength and my shield; My heart trusteth in him, and he helpeth me; Therefore doth my heart exult, And in my song I will praise him.
019	PSA	028	008	Jehovah is the strength of his people; He is the protecting shield of his anointed.
019	PSA	028	009	Save thy people, and bless thine inheritance; Feed them also, and build them up for ever!
019	PSA	029	001	“A psalm of David.” Give to Jehovah, O ye sons of God! Give to Jehovah glory and praise!
019	PSA	029	002	Give to Jehovah the glory due to his name; Worship Jehovah in holy attire!
019	PSA	029	003	The voice of Jehovah is heard above the waters; The God of glory thundereth, -Jehovah above the great waters.
019	PSA	029	004	The voice of Jehovah is powerful; The voice of Jehovah is full of majesty;
019	PSA	029	005	The voice of Jehovah breaketh the cedars; Yea, Jehovah breaketh the cedars of Lebanon;
019	PSA	029	006	Yea, he maketh them to leap like a calf, —Lebanon and Sirion like a young buffalo.
019	PSA	029	007	The voice of Jehovah divideth the flames of fire.
019	PSA	029	008	The voice of Jehovah maketh the wilderness tremble; Yea, Jehovah maketh the wilderness of Kadesh tremble.
019	PSA	029	009	The voice of Jehovah maketh the hinds bring forth, And layeth bare the forests; While, in his palace, every one declareth his glory.
019	PSA	029	010	Jehovah sitteth above the flood; Yea, Jehovah sitteth king for ever.
