019	PSA	041	008	“A deadly disease cleaveth fast unto him; He lieth down, and he shall never arise!”
019	PSA	041	009	Yea, my familiar friend in whom I trusted, who did eat of my bread, —He hath lifted up his heel against me.
019	PSA	041	010	But do thou, O LORD! have pity upon me; Raise me up, that I may requite them!
019	PSA	041	011	By this I know that thou favorest me, Because my enemy doth not triumph over me.
019	PSA	041	012	As for me, thou wilt uphold me in my integrity; Thou wilt set me before thy face for ever!
019	PSA	041	013	[Praised be Jehovah, the God of Israel, From everlasting to everlasting. Amen! Amen!]
019	PSA	042	001	“BOOK II. For the leader of the music. A song of the sons of Korah.” As the hart panteth for the water-brooks, So panteth my soul for thee, O God!
019	PSA	042	002	My soul thirsteth for God, the living God: When shall I come, and appear before God?
019	PSA	042	003	My tears have been my food day and night, While they say to me continually, “Where is thy God?”
019	PSA	042	004	When I think of it, I pour out my soul in grief; How I once walked with the multitude, Walked slowly with them to the house of God, Amid sounds of joy and praise with the festive multitude!
019	PSA	042	005	Why art thou cast down, O my soul? And why art thou disquieted within me? Hope thou in God; for I shall yet praise him, Him, my deliverer and my God!
019	PSA	042	006	My soul is cast down within me, While I remember thee from the land of Jordan and Hermon, From the mountain Mizar.
019	PSA	042	007	Deep calleth for deep at the noise of thy waterfalls; All thy waves and billows have gone over me!
019	PSA	042	008	Once the LORD commanded his kindness by day, And by night his praise was with me, -Thanksgiving to the God of my life.
019	PSA	042	009	Now I say to God, my rock, Why hast thou forgotten me? Why go I mourning on account of the oppression of the enemy?
019	PSA	042	010	Like the crushing of my bones are the reproaches of the enemy, While they say to me continually, “Where is thy God?”
019	PSA	042	011	Why art thou cast down, O my soul? And why art thou disquieted within me? Hope thou in God; for I shall yet praise him, Him, my deliverer and my God!
019	PSA	043	001	Judge me, O God! and defend my cause against a merciless nation! Deliver me from unjust and deceitful men!
019	PSA	043	002	Thou art the God of my refuge: why dost thou cast me off? Why go I mourning on account of the oppression of the enemy?
019	PSA	043	003	O send forth thy light and thy truth; let them guide me; Let them lead me to thy holy mountain, and to thy dwelling-place!
019	PSA	043	004	Then will I go to the altar of God, To the God of my joy and exultation; Yea, upon the harp will I praise thee, O God, my God!
019	PSA	043	005	Why art thou cast down, O my soul? And why art thou disquieted within me? Hope thou in God; for I shall yet praise him, Him, my deliverer and my God!
019	PSA	044	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of the sons of Korah.” O God! we have heard with our ears, Our fathers have told us, What deeds thou didst in their days, In the days of old.
019	PSA	044	002	With thine own hand didst thou drive out the nations, And plant our fathers; Thou didst destroy the nations, And cause our fathers to flourish.
019	PSA	044	003	For not by their own swords did they gain possession of the land, Nor did their own arms give them victory; But thy right hand, and thine arm, and the light of thy countenance; For thou didst favor them!
019	PSA	044	004	Thou art my king, O God! O send deliverance to Jacob!
019	PSA	044	005	Through thee we may cast down our enemies; Through thy name we may trample upon our adversaries!
019	PSA	044	006	I trust not in my bow, Nor can my sword save me.
019	PSA	044	007	But it is thou only who savest us from our enemies, And puttest to shame those who hate us!
019	PSA	044	008	In God will we glory continually; Yea, we will praise thy name for ever! (Pause)
019	PSA	044	009	Yet now thou hast cast us off, and put us to shame; Thou goest not forth with our armies.
019	PSA	044	010	Thou makest us turn back from the enemy, And they who hate us make our goods their prey.
019	PSA	044	011	Thou makest us like sheep destined for food, And scatterest us among the nations.
019	PSA	044	012	Thou sellest thy people for nought, And increasest not thy wealth by their price.
019	PSA	044	013	Thou makest us a reproach to our neighbors, A scorn and a derision to those who are around us.
019	PSA	044	014	Thou makest us a byword among the nations, And causest the people to shake their heads at us.
019	PSA	044	015	My ignominy is continually before me, And shame covereth my face,
019	PSA	044	016	On account of the voice of the scoffer and the reviler, And on account of the enemy and the avenger.
019	PSA	044	017	All this hath come upon us; Yet have we not forgotten thee, Nor have we been false to thy covenant.
019	PSA	044	018	Our hearts, have not wandered from thee, Nor have our feet gone out of thy path;
019	PSA	044	019	Though thou hast crushed us in a land of jackals, And covered us with thick darkness.
019	PSA	044	020	If we had forgotten the name of our God, Or stretched forth our hands to a strange God,
019	PSA	044	021	Surely God would search it out; For he knoweth the secrets of the heart.
019	PSA	044	022	But for thy sake we are killed all the day; We are counted as sheep for the slaughter.
019	PSA	044	023	Awake! why sleepest thou, O Lord? Arise! cast us not off for ever!
019	PSA	044	024	Wherefore dost thou hide thy face, And forget our affliction and oppression?
019	PSA	044	025	Our soul is bowed down to the dust; Our body cleaveth to the earth.
019	PSA	044	026	Arise, O thou, our strength! And deliver us, for thy mercy's sake!
019	PSA	045	001	“For the leader of the music. To be accompanied with the Shoshannim. A song of loveliness by the sons of Korah.” My heart is overflowing with a good matter; I will address my work to the king: May my tongue be like the pen of a ready writer!
019	PSA	045	002	Thou art the fairest of the sons of men; Grace is poured upon thy lips; For God hath blessed thee for ever!
019	PSA	045	003	Gird thy sword to thy thigh, thou hero!-Thy glory and ornament!
019	PSA	045	004	In thy glorious array ride forth victoriously, On account of truth and mildness and justice; And thy right hand shall teach thee terrible things!
019	PSA	045	005	Thine arrows are sharp; Nations shall fall before thee; They shall pierce the hearts of the king's enemies.
019	PSA	045	006	Thy throne is God's for ever and ever; The sceptre of thy kingdom is a sceptre of equity!
019	PSA	045	007	Thou lovest righteousness, and hatest iniquity; Therefore hath God, thy God, anointed thee With the oil of gladness above thy fellows!
019	PSA	045	008	All thy garments are myrrh, aloes, and cassia; From ivory palaces stringed instruments delight thee.
019	PSA	045	009	Daughters of kings are among thy chosen women; On the right hand stands the queen In gold of Ophir.
019	PSA	045	010	Listen, O daughter! consider, and incline thine ear; Forget thy people and thy father's house!
019	PSA	045	011	For the king is captivated with thy beauty; He is now thy lord; honor thou him!
019	PSA	045	012	So shall the daughter of Tyre seek thy favor with gifts, The rich among the people.
019	PSA	045	013	All glorious is the king's daughter in her apartment; Her robe is embroidered with gold.
019	PSA	045	014	In variegated garments shall she be led to the king; The virgin companions that follow her shall be brought unto thee.
019	PSA	045	015	With gladness and rejoicing shall they be brought; They shall enter the king's palace.
019	PSA	045	016	Instead of thy fathers shall be thy children, Whom thou shalt make princes through all the land.
019	PSA	045	017	I will make thy name memorable throughout all generations; So shall the nations praise thee for ever and ever!
019	PSA	046	001	“For the leader of the music. Of, or for, the sons of Korah. To be sung in the manner, or with the voice, of virgins.” God is our refuge and strength; An ever present help in trouble.
019	PSA	046	002	Therefore will we not fear, though the earth be changed; Though the mountains tremble in the heart of the sea;
019	PSA	046	003	Though its waters roar and be troubled, And the mountains shake with the swelling thereof. (Pause)
019	PSA	046	004	A river with its streams shall make glad the city of God, The holy dwelling-place of the Most High.
019	PSA	046	005	God is the midst of her; she shall not be moved; God will help her, and that full early.
019	PSA	046	006	The nations raged; kingdoms were moved; He uttered his voice, the earth melted.
019	PSA	046	007	The LORD of hosts is with us; The God of Jacob is our refuge. (Pause)
019	PSA	046	008	Come, behold the doings of the LORD; What desolations he hath made in the earth!
019	PSA	046	009	He causeth wars to cease to the end of the earth; He hath broken the bow, and snapped the spear asunder, And burned the chariots in fire.
019	PSA	046	010	“Desist, and know that I am God; I will be exalted among the nations, I will be exalted throughout the earth!”
019	PSA	046	011	The LORD of hosts is with us; The God of Jacob is our refuge.
019	PSA	047	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of the sons of Korah.” O clap your hands, all ye nations! Shout unto God with the voice of triumph!
019	PSA	047	002	For terrible is Jehovah, the Most High, The great king over all the earth.
019	PSA	047	003	He hath subdued nations under us, And kingdoms under our feet;
019	PSA	047	004	He hath chosen for us an inheritance, The glory of Jacob, whom he loved. (Pause)
019	PSA	047	005	God goeth up with a shout; Jehovah with the sound of the trumpet.
019	PSA	047	006	Sing praises to God, sing praises! Sing praises to our king, sing praises!
019	PSA	047	007	For God is king of all the earth; Sing to him hymns of praise!
019	PSA	047	008	God reigneth over the nations; God sitteth upon his holy throne.
019	PSA	047	009	The princes of the nations gather themselves together To the people of the God of Abraham; For the mighty of the earth belong to God; He is supremely exalted.
019	PSA	048	001	“A psalm of the sons of Korah.” Great is Jehovah, and greatly to be praised In the city of our God, upon his holy mountain.
019	PSA	048	002	Beautiful in its elevation is Mount Zion, The joy of the whole earth; The joy of the farthest North is the city of the great king;
019	PSA	048	003	In her palaces God is known as a refuge.
019	PSA	048	004	For, lo! kings were assembled against it; They passed away together.
019	PSA	048	005	As soon as they saw, they were astonished; They were confounded, and hasted away.
019	PSA	048	006	There terror seized upon them, —Pain, as of a woman in travail;
019	PSA	048	007	As when the east wind breaketh in pieces The ships of Tarshish.
019	PSA	048	008	As we have heard, so have we seen In the city of the LORD of hosts, in the city of our God; God will establish it for ever. (Pause)
019	PSA	048	009	We think of thy loving-kindness, O God! In the midst of thy temple!
019	PSA	048	010	As thy name, O God! so thy praise, extendeth to the ends of the earth; Thy right hand is full of righteousness.
019	PSA	048	011	Mount Zion rejoiceth, The daughters of Judah exult, On account of thy righteous judgments.
019	PSA	048	012	Go round about Zion; number her towers;
019	PSA	048	013	Mark well her bulwarks; count her palaces; That ye may tell it to the next generation!
019	PSA	048	014	For this God is our God for ever and ever; He will be our guide unto death.
019	PSA	049	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of the sons of Korah.” Hear this, all ye nations; Give ear, all ye inhabitants of the world;
019	PSA	049	002	Both high and low, rich and poor alike!
019	PSA	049	003	My mouth shall speak wisdom, And the meditation of my mind shall be understanding.
019	PSA	049	004	I will incline mine ear to a poem; I will utter my song upon the harp.
019	PSA	049	005	Why should I fear in the days of adversity, When the iniquity of my adversaries encompasseth me;
019	PSA	049	006	They who trust in their riches, And glory in the greatness of their wealth?
019	PSA	049	007	No one can redeem his brother from death, Nor give a ransom for him to God,
019	PSA	049	008	That he should live to eternity, And not see the pit.
019	PSA	049	009	Too costly is the redemption of his life, And he giveth it up for ever.
019	PSA	049	010	For he seeth that wise men die, As well as the foolish and the ignorant; They perish alike, And leave their wealth to others.
019	PSA	049	011	They imagine that their houses will endure for ever, And their dwelling-places from generation to generation: Men celebrate their names on the earth.
019	PSA	049	012	Yet man, who is in honor, abideth not; He is like the beasts that perish.
019	PSA	049	013	Such is the way which is their confidence! And they who come after them approve their maxims. (Pause)
019	PSA	049	014	Like sheep they are cast into the underworld; Death shall feed upon them; And the upright shall soon trample upon them. Their form shall be consumed in the underworld, And they shall no more have a dwelling-place.
019	PSA	049	015	But God will redeem my life from the underworld; Yea, he will take me under his care. (Pause)
019	PSA	049	016	Be not thou afraid, when one becometh rich; When the glory of his house is increased!
019	PSA	049	017	For, when he dieth, he will carry nothing away; His glory will not descend after him.
019	PSA	049	018	Though in his life he thought himself happy, —Though men praised thee, while thou wast in prosperity, —
019	PSA	049	019	Yet shalt thou go to the dwelling-place of thy fathers, Who never more shall see the light!
019	PSA	049	020	The man who is in honor, but without understanding, Is like the beasts that perish.
019	PSA	050	001	“A psalm of Asaph.” The mighty God, Jehovah, speaketh, and calleth the earth, From the rising of the sun to its going down.
019	PSA	050	002	Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, God shineth forth.
019	PSA	050	003	Our God cometh, and will not be silent; Before him is a devouring fire, And around him a raging tempest.
019	PSA	050	004	He calleth to the heavens on high, And to the earth, while he judgeth his people:
019	PSA	050	005	“Gather together before me my godly ones, Who have made a covenant with me by sacrifice!”
019	PSA	050	006	(And the heavens shall declare his righteousness, For it is God himself that is judge., Pause)
019	PSA	050	007	“Hear, O my people, and I will speak! O Israel, and I will testify against thee! For I am God, thine own God.
019	PSA	050	008	I reprove thee not on account of thy sacrifices; For thy burnt-offerings are ever before me.
019	PSA	050	009	I will take no bullock from thy house, Nor he-goat from thy folds;
019	PSA	050	010	For all the beasts of the forest are mine, And the cattle on a thousand hills.
019	PSA	050	011	I know all the birds of the mountains, And the wild beasts of the field are before me.
019	PSA	050	012	If I were hungry, I would not tell thee; For the world is mine, and all that is therein.
019	PSA	050	013	Do I eat the flesh of bulls, Or drink the blood of goats?
019	PSA	050	014	Offer to God thanksgiving, And pay thy vows to the Most High!
019	PSA	050	015	Then call upon me in the day of trouble: I will deliver thee, and thou shalt glorify me!”
019	PSA	050	016	And to the wicked God saith, “To what purpose dost thou talk of my statutes? And why hast thou my laws upon thy lips?—
019	PSA	050	017	Thou, who hatest instruction And castest my words behind thee!
019	PSA	050	018	When thou seest a thief, thou art in friendship with him, And hast fellowship with adulterers.
019	PSA	050	019	Thou lettest loose thy mouth to evil, And thy tongue frameth deceit;
019	PSA	050	020	Thou sittest and speakest against thy brother; Thou slanderest thine own mother's son.
019	PSA	050	021	These things hast thou done, and I kept silence; Hence thou thoughtest that I was altogether like thyself: But I will reprove thee, and set it in order before thine eyes.
019	PSA	050	022	Mark this, ye that forget God, Lest I tear you in pieces, and none deliver you!
019	PSA	050	023	Whoso offereth praise honoreth me; And to him who hath regard to his ways Will I show salvation from God.”
019	PSA	051	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David, when Nathan the prophet came unto him, after his intercourse with Bathsheba.” Be gracious unto me, O God! according to thy loving kindness; According to the greatness of thy mercy, blot out my transgressions!
019	PSA	051	002	Wash me thoroughly from my iniquity, And cleanse me from my sin!
019	PSA	051	003	For I acknowledge my transgressions, And my sin is ever before me.
019	PSA	051	004	Against thee, thee only, have I sinned, And in thy sight have I done evil; So that thou art just in thy sentence, And righteous in thy judgment.
019	PSA	051	005	Behold! I was born in iniquity, And in sin did my mother conceive me.
019	PSA	051	006	Behold! thou desirest truth in the heart; So teach me wisdom in my inmost soul!
019	PSA	051	007	Purge me with hyssop, until I be clean; Wash me, until I be whiter than snow!
019	PSA	051	008	Make me to hear joy and gladness, So that the bones which thou hast broken may rejoice!
019	PSA	051	009	Hide thy face from my sins, And blot out all my iniquities!
019	PSA	051	010	Create within me a clean heart, O God! Renew within me a steadfast spirit!
019	PSA	051	011	Cast me not away from thy presence, And take not thy holy spirit from me!
019	PSA	051	012	Restore to me the joy of thy protection, And strengthen me with a willing spirit!
019	PSA	051	013	Then will I teach thy ways to transgressors, And sinners shall be converted to thee.
019	PSA	051	014	Deliver me from the guilt of blood, O God, the God of my salvation! That my tongue may sing aloud of thy goodness!
019	PSA	051	015	O Lord! open thou my lips, That my mouth may show forth thy praise!
019	PSA	051	016	For thou desirest not sacrifice, else would I give it; Thou delightest not in burnt-offerings.
019	PSA	051	017	The sacrifice which God loveth is a broken spirit; A broken and contrite heart, O God! thou wilt not despise!
019	PSA	051	018	Do good to Zion according to thy mercy; Build up the walls of Jerusalem!
019	PSA	051	019	Then shalt thou be pleased with sacrifices of righteousness, With burnt-offerings and complete offerings; Then shall bullocks be offered upon thine altar.
019	PSA	052	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David, when Doeg, the Edomite, came and told Saul, and said to him, David is come to the house of Abimelech.” Why gloriest thou in mischief, thou man of violence? The goodness of God yet continueth daily.
019	PSA	052	002	Thy tongue deviseth mischief, Like a sharp razor, thou contriver of deceit!
019	PSA	052	003	Thou lovest evil more than good, And to lie more than to speak truth. (Pause)
019	PSA	052	004	Thou lovest all devouring words, O thou deceitful tongue!
019	PSA	052	005	Thee also shall God utterly destroy! o He shall seize thee, and tear thee from thy dwelling-place, And uproot thee from the land of the living. (Pause)
019	PSA	052	006	The righteous shall see and fear, And shall laugh at him.
019	PSA	052	007	“Behold the man that made not God his strength, But trusted in the abundance of his riches, And placed his strength in his wickedness!”
019	PSA	052	008	But I shall be like a green olive-tree in the house of God; I will trust in the goodness of God for ever and ever.
019	PSA	052	009	I will praise thee for ever for what thou hast done; I will trust in thy name, because it is good, Before the eyes of thy godly ones!
019	PSA	053	001	“For the leader of the music. To be sung on wind instruments. A psalm of David.” The fool saith in his heart, “There is no God!” They are corrupt; their doings are abominable; There is none that doeth good.
019	PSA	053	002	God looketh down from heaven upon the children of men, To see if there are any that have understanding, That have regard to God.
019	PSA	053	003	They are all gone astray; together are they corrupt; There is none that doeth good, no, not one.
019	PSA	053	004	Shall not the evil-doers be requited, Who eat up my people like bread, And call not upon God?
019	PSA	053	005	Yea! fear shall come upon them, Where no fear is; For God will scatter the bones of him that encampeth against thee; Thou shalt put them to shame, for God despiseth them!
019	PSA	053	006	O that salvation for Israel would come out of Zion! When God bringeth back the captives of his people, Jacob shall rejoice, and Israel be glad.
019	PSA	054	001	“For the leader of the music. To be sung on stringed instruments A psalm of David, when the Ziphites came and said to Saul, Doth not David hide himself with us?” Save me, O God! by thy name, And by thy strength defend my cause!
019	PSA	054	002	O God! hear my prayer, Give ear to the words of my mouth!
019	PSA	054	003	For enemies have risen up against me, And oppressors seek my life; They have not set God before their eyes. (Pause)
019	PSA	054	004	Behold! God is my helper; The Lord is the support of my life.
019	PSA	054	005	He will repay evil to my enemies; For thy truth's sake, O God! cut them off!
019	PSA	054	006	With a willing heart will I sacrifice to thee; I will praise thy name, O LORD! for it is good;
019	PSA	054	007	For thou hast delivered me from all trouble, So that my eye hath looked with joy upon my enemies!
019	PSA	055	001	“For the leader of the music. To be sung on stringed instruments. A psalm of David.” Give ear to my prayer, O God! Hide not thyself from my supplication!
019	PSA	055	002	Attend unto me, and hear me! I wander about mourning and wailing,
019	PSA	055	003	On account of the clamors of the enemy, On account of the violence of the wicked. For they bring evil upon me, And in wrath set themselves against me.
019	PSA	055	004	My heart trembleth in my bosom, And the terrors of death have fallen upon me.
019	PSA	055	005	Fear and trembling have seized me, And horror hath overwhelmed me.
019	PSA	055	006	Then I say, O that I had wings like a dove! For then would I fly away, and be at rest.
019	PSA	055	007	Behold, I would wander far away, And take up my abode in a wilderness. (Pause)
019	PSA	055	008	I would hasten away to a shelter From the rushing wind and tempest.
019	PSA	055	009	Confound, O Lord! divide their counsels! For I behold violence and strife in the city.
019	PSA	055	010	Day and night do these go about its walls; In the midst of it are iniquity and mischief.
019	PSA	055	011	Wickedness is in the midst of it; Oppression and fraud depart not from its streets.
019	PSA	055	012	It was not an enemy that reviled me, Then I could have borne it; Nor one that hated me, who rose up against me; From him I could have hid myself.
019	PSA	055	013	But it was thou, a man my equal, My friend, and my acquaintance.
019	PSA	055	014	We held sweet converse together, And walked to the house of God in company.
019	PSA	055	015	May sudden death seize upon them! May they go down to the underworld alive! For wickedness is in their dwellings, in the midst of them.
019	PSA	055	016	As for me, I will call upon God, And Jehovah will save me.
019	PSA	055	017	At evening, at morn, and at noon I mourn and sigh, And he will hear my voice.
019	PSA	055	018	He will deliver me in peace from my conflict; For many have risen up against me.
019	PSA	055	019	God will hear me, and bring them down, —He that hath been judge of old. (Pause) Because they have no changes, Therefore they fear not God.
019	PSA	055	020	They lift up their hands against their friend, And break their covenant with him.
019	PSA	055	021	Their speech was softer than butter, But war was in their heart; Their words were smoother than oil, Yet were they drawn swords.
019	PSA	055	022	“Cast thy burden upon the LORD, and he will sustain thee; He will never suffer the righteous to fall!”
019	PSA	055	023	Yea, thou, O God! wilt bring them down into the lowest pit! Bloody and deceitful men shall not live out half their days. But I will trust in thee!
019	PSA	056	001	“For the leader of the music. To be sung to the tune of “The dumb dove among strangers.” A psalm of David, when the Philistines took him in Gath.” Have pity upon me, O God! for man panteth for my life; My adversary daily oppresseth me!
019	PSA	056	002	Mine enemies daily pant for my life, And many are they who war proudly against me.
019	PSA	056	003	When I am in fear, I will put my trust in thee!
019	PSA	056	004	Through God shall I praise his word; In God do I put my trust; I will not fear; What can flesh do to me?
019	PSA	056	005	Every day they wrest my words; All their thoughts are against me for evil.
019	PSA	056	006	They gather themselves together, they hide themselves, they watch my steps, Lying in wait for my life.
019	PSA	056	007	Shall they escape by their iniquity? In thine anger cast down the people, O God!
019	PSA	056	008	Count thou my wanderings; Put my tears into thy bottle! Are they not recorded in thy book?
019	PSA	056	009	When I cry to thee, my enemies shall turn back; This I know, that God is for me.
019	PSA	056	010	Through God shall I praise his word; I shall glory in the promise of Jehovah.
019	PSA	056	011	In God do I put my trust; I will not fear: What can man do to me?
019	PSA	056	012	Thy vows are upon me, O God! I will render praises to thee!
019	PSA	056	013	For thou hast delivered me from death, Yea, my feet from falling, That I may walk before God in the light of the living.
019	PSA	057	001	“For the leader of the music. To be sung to the tune of “Do not destroy.” A psalm of David, when he fled from Saul in the cave.” Have pity upon me, O God! have pity upon me, For in thee doth my soul seek refuge! Yea, in the shadow of thy wings do I take shelter, Until these calamities be overpast!
019	PSA	057	002	I call upon God the Most High, Upon God, who performeth all things for me;
019	PSA	057	003	He will send from heaven, and save me; He will put to shame him that panteth for my life; (Pause) God will send forth his mercy and his truth.
019	PSA	057	004	My life is in the midst of lions; I dwell among them that breathe out fire; Among men whose teeth are spears and arrows, And whose tongue is a sharp sword.
019	PSA	057	005	Exalt thyself, O God! above the heavens, And thy glory above all the earth!
019	PSA	057	006	They have prepared a net for my steps; My soul is bowed down; They have digged a pit before me, But into it they have themselves fallen.
019	PSA	057	007	My heart is strengthened, O God! my heart is strengthened! I will sing, and give thanks.
019	PSA	057	008	Awake, my soul! awake, psaltery and harp! I will wake with the early dawn.
019	PSA	057	009	I will praise thee, O Lord! among the nations; I will sing to thee among the kingdoms!
019	PSA	057	010	For thy mercy reacheth to the heavens, And thy truth to the clouds!
019	PSA	057	011	Exalt thyself, O God! above the heavens, And thy glory above all the earth!
019	PSA	058	001	“For the leader of the music. To the tune of “Do not destroy.” A psalm of David.” Do ye, indeed, administer justice faithfully, ye mighty ones? Do ye judge with uprightness, ye sons of men?
019	PSA	058	002	Nay, in your hearts ye contrive iniquity; Your hands weigh out violence in the land!
019	PSA	058	003	The wicked are estranged, from their very birth; The liars go astray as soon as they are born.
019	PSA	058	004	They have poison, like the poison of a serpent; Like the deaf adder's, which stoppeth her ear;
019	PSA	058	005	Which listeneth not to the voice of the charmer, And of the sorcerer, skilful in incantations.
019	PSA	058	006	Break their teeth, O God! in their mouths! Break out the great teeth of the lions, O LORD!
019	PSA	058	007	May they melt like waters, which flow away; May their arrows, when they aim them, be as if cut in pieces!
019	PSA	058	008	May they be like the snail, which melteth away as it goeth; Like the abortion of a woman, that seeth not the sun!
019	PSA	058	009	Before your pots feel the heat of the thorns, Whether fresh, or burning, may they be blown away!
019	PSA	058	010	The righteous shall rejoice, when he seeth such vengeance; He shall bathe his feet in the blood of the wicked.
019	PSA	058	011	Then shall men say, “Truly there is a reward for the righteous! Truly there is a God who is judge upon the earth!”
019	PSA	059	001	“For the leader of the music. To the tune of “Do not destroy.” A psalm of David, when Saul sent, and they watched the house to kill him.” Deliver me from my enemies, O my God! Defend me from them that rise up against me!
019	PSA	059	002	Deliver me from the doers of iniquity, And save me from men of blood!
019	PSA	059	003	For, lo! they lie in wait for my life; The mighty are gathered against me, Without any offence or fault of mine, O LORD!
019	PSA	059	004	Without any offence of mine, they run and prepare themselves; Awake to help me, and behold!
019	PSA	059	005	Do thou, O Jehovah, God of hosts, God of Israel, Awake to punish all the nations! Show no mercy to any wicked transgressors! (Pause)
019	PSA	059	006	Let them return at evening, Let them howl like dogs, And go round about the city!
019	PSA	059	007	Behold! with their mouths they belch out malice; Swords are upon their lips; “For who,” say they, “will hear?”
019	PSA	059	008	Yet thou, O LORD! wilt laugh at them; Thou wilt hold all the nations in derision!
019	PSA	059	009	O my Strength! to thee will I look! For God is my defence;
019	PSA	059	010	My God will come to meet me with his mercy; God will cause me to look with joy upon my enemies.
019	PSA	059	011	Slay them not, lest my people forget; Scatter them by thy power, and cast them down, O Lord, our shield!
019	PSA	059	012	The word of their lips is the sin of their mouth; Let them be overtaken in their pride, For the curses and the falsehood which they utter!
019	PSA	059	013	Consume them in thy wrath; consume them that they be no more, That they may know that God ruleth in Jacob, Even to the ends of the earth! (Pause)
019	PSA	059	014	Let them return at evening, Let them howl like dogs, And go round about the city!
019	PSA	059	015	Let them wander about for food, When they have passed the night unsatisfied!
019	PSA	059	016	But I will sing of thy power; Yea, in the morning will I sing aloud of thy mercy; For thou hast been my defence, My refuge in the day of my distress.
019	PSA	059	017	To thee, O my Strength! will I sing! For God is my defence; a God of mercy to me.
019	PSA	060	001	“For the leader of the music; upon the Shushan-Eduth; a psalm of David for instruction; when he was at strife with the Syrians of Mesopotamia, and the Syrians of Zoba; when Joab returned, and smote twelve thousand Edomites in the valley of Salt.” O God! thou hast forsaken us; thou hast broken us in pieces; Thou hast been angry! O revive us again!
019	PSA	060	002	Thou hast made the land tremble; thou hast rent it; O heal its breaches, for it tottereth!
019	PSA	060	003	Thou hast caused thy people to see hard things; Thou hast made us drink the wine of reeling.
019	PSA	060	004	Lift up a banner for them that fear thee, For the sake of thy faithfulness, that they may escape!
019	PSA	060	005	That thy beloved may be delivered, Save with thy right hand, and answer me!
019	PSA	060	006	God promiseth in his holiness; I will rejoice; I shall yet divide Shechem, And measure out the valley of Succoth.
019	PSA	060	007	Gilead shall be mine, and mine Manasseh; Ephraim shall be my helmet, And Judah my sceptre;
019	PSA	060	008	Moab shall be my wash-bowl; Upon Edom shall I cast my shoe; I shall triumph over Philistia!
019	PSA	060	009	Who will bring me to the strong city? Who will lead me into Edom?
019	PSA	060	010	Wilt not thou, O God! who didst forsake us, And didst not go forth with our armies?
019	PSA	060	011	Give us thine aid in our distress, For vain is the help of man!
019	PSA	060	012	Through God we shall do valiantly; For he will tread down our enemies.
019	PSA	061	001	“For the leader of the music. To be sung upon stringed instruments. A psalm of David.” Hear my cry, O God! Attend to my prayer!
019	PSA	061	002	From the extremity of the land I cry unto thee in deep sorrow of heart; Lead me to the rock that is high above me!
019	PSA	061	003	For thou art my refuge, My strong tower against the enemy.
019	PSA	061	004	I shall dwell in thy tabernacle for ever; I will seek refuge under the covert of thy wings.
019	PSA	061	005	For thou, O God! wilt hear my vows, And give me the inheritance of those who fear thy name.
019	PSA	061	006	O prolong the life of the king! May his years extend through many generations!
019	PSA	061	007	May he reign for ever before God! Grant that mercy and truth may preserve him!
019	PSA	061	008	So will I sing praise to thy name for ever; I will daily perform my vows.
019	PSA	062	001	“For the leader of the music of the Jeduthunites, A psalm of David.” Truly my soul resteth on God alone; From him cometh my deliverance!
019	PSA	062	002	He alone is my rock and my salvation; He is my safeguard, I shall not wholly fall!
019	PSA	062	003	How long will ye continue to assault a single man? How long will ye all seek to destroy me, Like a bending wall, or a tottering fence?
019	PSA	062	004	They study how to cast me down from my eminence; They delight in falsehood; They bless with their mouths, but in their hearts they curse.
019	PSA	062	005	My soul, rest thou on God alone, For from him cometh my hope!
019	PSA	062	006	He alone is my rock and my salvation; He is my safeguard, —I shall not fall.
019	PSA	062	007	From God cometh my help and my glory: My strong rock, my refuge, is God.
019	PSA	062	008	Trust in him at all times, ye people! Pour out your hearts before him! God is our refuge!
019	PSA	062	009	Truly men of low degree are vanity, And men of high degree are a lie; Placed in the balance, They are all lighter than vanity.
019	PSA	062	010	Trust not in extortion; Place no vain hopes in rapine! If riches increase, set not your heart upon them!
019	PSA	062	011	Once hath God promised, twice have I heard it, That power belongeth unto God.
019	PSA	062	012	To thee also, O Lord! belongeth mercy; For thou dost render to every man according to his work!
019	PSA	063	001	“A psalm of David, when he was in the wilderness of Judah.” O God! thou art my God! earnestly do I seek thee! My soul thirsteth, my flesh longeth for thee, In a dry, thirsty land. where is no water!
019	PSA	063	002	Thus I look toward thee in thy sanctuary, To behold thy power and thy glory!
019	PSA	063	003	For thy loving-kindness is better than life; Therefore my lips shall praise thee!
019	PSA	063	004	Thus will I bless thee, while I live; In thy name will I lift up my hands!
019	PSA	063	005	My soul shall be satisfied as with marrow and fatness, And with joyful lips my mouth shall praise thee,
019	PSA	063	006	When I think of thee upon my bed, And meditate on thee in the night-watches.
019	PSA	063	007	For thou art my help, And in the shadow of thy wings I rejoice.
019	PSA	063	008	My soul cleaveth to thee; Thy right hand holdeth me up.
019	PSA	063	009	While they who seek to destroy my life Shall themselves go down into the depths of the earth.
019	PSA	063	010	They shall be given up to the sword, And be a portion for jackals.
019	PSA	063	011	But the king shall rejoice in God; All that swear by him shall be honored; But the mouth of liars shall be stopped.
019	PSA	064	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” Hear my voice, O God! when I pray! Preserve my life from the terrors of the enemy!
019	PSA	064	002	Hide me from the assembly of the wicked, From the brawling crowd of evil-doers!
019	PSA	064	003	For like a sword they sharpen their tongues, Like arrows they aim their poisoned words,
019	PSA	064	004	To shoot in secret at the upright; Suddenly do they shoot at him without fear.
019	PSA	064	005	They prepare themselves for an evil deed; They commune of laying secret snares: “Who,” say they, “will see them?”
019	PSA	064	006	They meditate crimes: “We have finished,” say they, “our plans!” The heart and bosom of every one of them are deep.
019	PSA	064	007	But God will shoot an arrow at them; Suddenly shall they be wounded.
019	PSA	064	008	Thus their own tongues shall bring them down; All who see them will flee away.
019	PSA	064	009	Then will all men stand in awe, And declare what God hath done, And attentively consider his work.
019	PSA	064	010	The righteous shall rejoice, and trust in the LORD; All the upright in heart shall glory.
019	PSA	065	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” To thee belongeth trust, to thee praise, O God in Zion! And to thee shall the vow be performed!
019	PSA	065	002	O Thou that hearest prayer! To thee shall all flesh come!
019	PSA	065	003	My iniquities are heavy upon me; But thou wilt forgive our transgressions!
019	PSA	065	004	Happy is he whom thou choosest, And bringest near thee to dwell in thy courts! May we be satisfied with the blessings of thy house, Thy holy temple!
019	PSA	065	005	By wonderful deeds dost thou answer us in thy goodness, O God, our salvation! Who art the confidence of all the ends of the earth, And of the most distant seas!
019	PSA	065	006	Thou makest fast the mountains by thy power, Being girded with strength!
019	PSA	065	007	Thou stillest the roar of the sea, The roar of its waves, And the tumult of the nations.
019	PSA	065	008	They who dwell in the ends of the earth are awed by thy signs; Thou makest the outgoings of the morning and of the evening to rejoice!
019	PSA	065	009	Thou visitest the earth and waterest it; Thou enrichest it exceedingly; The river of God is full of water. Thou suppliest the earth with corn, When thou hast thus prepared it.
019	PSA	065	010	Thou waterest its furrows, And breakest down its ridges; Thou makest it soft with showers, And blessest its increase.
019	PSA	065	011	Thou crownest the year with thy goodness; Thy footsteps drop fruitfulness;
019	PSA	065	012	They drop it upon the pastures of the wilderness, And the hills are girded with gladness.
019	PSA	065	013	The pastures are clothed with flocks, And the valleys are covered with corn; They shout, yea, they sing for joy.
019	PSA	066	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm.” Shout joyfully unto God. all ye lands!
019	PSA	066	002	Sing ye the honor of his name; Make his praise glorious!
019	PSA	066	003	Say unto God, How terrible are thy doings! Through the greatness of thy power thine enemies are suppliants to thee!
019	PSA	066	004	Let all the earth worship thee; Let it sing praise to thee, let it sing praise to thy name! (Pause)
019	PSA	066	005	Come, behold the works of God! How terrible his doings among the sons of men!
019	PSA	066	006	He turned the sea into dry land; They went through the deep on foot; Then we rejoiced in him.
019	PSA	066	007	By his power he ruleth for ever; His eyes are fixed upon the nations; Let not the rebellious exalt themselves! (Pause)
019	PSA	066	008	O bless our God, ye nations. And make the voice of his praise to be heard!
019	PSA	066	009	It is he who preserveth our lives, And suffereth not our feet to stumble.
019	PSA	066	010	Thou hast, indeed, proved us, O God! Thou hast tried us as silver is tried.
019	PSA	066	011	Thou broughtest us into a snare, And didst lay a heavy burden upon our backs;
019	PSA	066	012	Thou didst cause men to ride upon our heads, And we have gone through fire and water: But thou hast brought us to a place of abundance.
019	PSA	066	013	I will go into thy house with burnt-offerings! I will pay thee my vows, —
019	PSA	066	014	The vows which my lips uttered. Which my mouth promised in my trouble.
019	PSA	066	015	Burnt sacrifices of fatlings will I offer to thee with the fat of rams; Bullocks, with he-goats, will I sacrifice to thee. (Pause)
019	PSA	066	016	Come and hear, all ye who fear God, And I will relate what he hath done for me!
019	PSA	066	017	I called upon him with my mouth, And praise is now upon my tongue.
019	PSA	066	018	If I had meditated wickedness in my heart, The Lord would not have heard me:
019	PSA	066	019	But surely God hath heard me; He hath had regard to the voice of my supplication.
019	PSA	066	020	Blessed be God, who did not reject my prayer, Nor withhold his mercy from me!
019	PSA	067	001	“For the leader of the music. To be sung on stringed instruments. A psalm.” O God! be merciful to us, and bless us, And cause thy face to shine upon us! (Pause)
019	PSA	067	002	That thy doings may be known on earth, And thy saving power to all the nations.
019	PSA	067	003	Let the nations praise thee, O God! Yea, let all the nations praise thee!
019	PSA	067	004	Let all the nations be glad, and shout for joy! For justly dost thou judge the people, And govern the nations on the earth.
019	PSA	067	005	Let the nations praise thee, O God! Yea, let all the nations praise thee!
019	PSA	067	006	For the earth hath yielded her increase, And God, our God, hath blessed us.
019	PSA	067	007	May God continue to bless us, And may all the ends of the earth fear him!
019	PSA	068	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” Let God arise, and his enemies are scattered, And they who hate him flee before him!
019	PSA	068	002	As smoke is dispersed, so thou dispersest them; As wax melteth before the fire, So perish the wicked before the face of God.
019	PSA	068	003	But the righteous are glad and rejoice in his presence, Yea, they exult exceedingly.
019	PSA	068	004	Sing unto God; sing praises to his name! Prepare a way for him who rideth through the desert! Jehovah is his name; be joyful in his presence!
019	PSA	068	005	The father of the fatherless, and the protector of the widow, Is God in his holy habitation.
019	PSA	068	006	God causeth the forsaken to dwell in houses; He leadeth forth to prosperity them that are bound; But the rebellious shall dwell in a barren land.
019	PSA	068	007	O God! when thou didst go before thy people, When thou didst march through the wilderness. (Pause)
019	PSA	068	008	The earth quaked, and the heavens dropped at the presence of God; This Sinai trembled at the presence of God, the God of Israel.
019	PSA	068	009	Thou, O God! didst send a plentiful rain; Thou didst strengthen thy wearied inheritance.
019	PSA	068	010	Thy people established themselves in the land; Thou, O God! in thy goodness, didst prepare it for the needy!
019	PSA	068	011	The Lord gave the song of victory Of the maidens publishing glad tidings to the mighty host.
019	PSA	068	012	“The kings with their armies have fled, —have fled! And the matron at home divideth the spoil.
019	PSA	068	013	Truly ye may repose yourselves in the stalls, Like the wings of a dove covered with silver, And her feathers with shining gold.”
019	PSA	068	014	When the Most High destroyed the kings in the land, It was white [with their bones] like Salmon.
019	PSA	068	015	Ye lofty hills, ye hills of Bashan, Ye many-topped hills, ye hills of Bashan,
019	PSA	068	016	Why frown ye, ye many-topped hills, At the hill in which God is pleased to dwell, In which Jehovah will dwell for ever?
019	PSA	068	017	The chariots of God are myriads, yea, thousands of thousands; The Lord is in the midst of them, as upon Sinai, in the sanctuary.
019	PSA	068	018	Thou hast ascended on high, Thou hast led captive the vanquished, Thou hast received gifts among men, Even the rebellious, that here thou mightst dwell, O LORD God!
019	PSA	068	019	Praised be the Lord daily! When we are heavy-laden, the Mighty One is our help.
019	PSA	068	020	Our God is a God of salvation; From the Lord Jehovah cometh deliverance from death.
019	PSA	068	021	But God smiteth the head of his enemies, Even the hairy crowns of those who go on in their iniquity.
019	PSA	068	022	“I will bring them back,” saith the Lord, “from Bashan; I will bring them back from the deep sea;
019	PSA	068	023	That thy foot may be dipped in their blood, That thy dogs may drink the blood of thine enemies.”
019	PSA	068	024	We have seen thy procession, O God! The procession of my God, my king, to his sanctuary!
019	PSA	068	025	The singers go before, the minstrels follow, Amidst damsels playing on timbrels.
019	PSA	068	026	Praise ye God in your assemblies; Praise the Lord, all ye from the fountain of Israel!
019	PSA	068	027	Here is Benjamin, the youngest, and his leaders; The chiefs of Judah, and their band; The chiefs of Zebulon, and the chiefs of Naphtali.
019	PSA	068	028	Thy God has ordained thy strength, [O Israel!] Show forth thy might, O God! thou who hast wrought for us!
019	PSA	068	029	Because of thy temple in Jerusalem Shall kings bring presents to thee.
019	PSA	068	030	Rebuke the wild beast of the reeds, The multitude of bulls with the calves of the nations, So that they shall cast themselves down with masses of silver; Scatter thou the nations that delight in war!
019	PSA	068	031	Princes shall come out of Egypt; Ethiopia shall haste with outstretched hands to God.
019	PSA	068	032	Ye kingdoms of the earth, sing unto God; Sing praises to Jehovah;
019	PSA	068	033	To him who rideth upon the ancient heaven of heavens! Behold, he uttereth his voice, his mighty voice!
019	PSA	068	034	Give glory to God, Whose majesty is in Israel, and whose might is in the clouds!
019	PSA	068	035	Terrible art thou, O God! from thy sanctuary! The God of Israel giveth strength and power to his people. Praised be God!
019	PSA	069	001	“For the leader of the music. Upon the Shoshannim. A psalm of David.” Save me, O God! For the waters press in to my very life!
019	PSA	069	002	I sink in deep mire, where is no standing; I have come into deep waters, and the waves flow over me.
019	PSA	069	003	I am weary with crying; my throat is parched; Mine eyes are wasted, while I wait for my God.
019	PSA	069	004	More numerous than the hairs of my head are they who hate me without reason; Mighty are they who seek to destroy me, being my enemies without cause: I must restore what I took not away.
019	PSA	069	005	O God! thou knowest my offences, And my sins are not hidden from thee!
019	PSA	069	006	Let not them that trust in thee through me be put to shame, O Lord Jehovah, God of hosts! Let not them that seek thee through me be confounded, O God of Israel!
019	PSA	069	007	For on account of thee do I suffer reproach, And shame covereth my face!
019	PSA	069	008	I am become a stranger to my brothers; Yea, an alien to my mother's sons.
019	PSA	069	009	For zeal for thy house consumeth me, And the reproaches of them that reproach thee fall upon me.
019	PSA	069	010	When I weep and fast, That is made my reproach;
019	PSA	069	011	When I clothe myself in sackcloth, Then I become their by-word.
019	PSA	069	012	They who sit in the gate speak against me, And I am become the song of drunkards.
019	PSA	069	013	Yet will I address my prayer to thee, O LORD! May it be in an acceptable time according to thy great goodness! Hear, O God! and afford me thy sure help!
019	PSA	069	014	Save me from the mire, and let me not sink; May I be delivered from my enemies, —from the deep waters!
019	PSA	069	015	Let not the water-flood overflow me; Let not the deep swallow me up, And let not the pit close her mouth upon me!
019	PSA	069	016	Hear me, O LORD! since great is thy loving-kindness; According to the abundance of thy tender mercies look upon me!
019	PSA	069	017	Hide not thy face from thy servant; I am greatly distressed, O make haste to mine aid!
019	PSA	069	018	Draw near to me, and redeem my life; Deliver me because of my enemies!
019	PSA	069	019	Thou knowest my reproach, and dishonor, and shame; All my adversaries are in thy view!
019	PSA	069	020	Reproach hath broken my heart, and I am full of heaviness; I look for pity, but there is none; For comforters, but find none.
019	PSA	069	021	For my food they give me gall, And in my thirst they give me vinegar to drink.
019	PSA	069	022	May their table be to them a snare; May it be a trap to them, while they are at ease!
019	PSA	069	023	May their eyes be darkened, that they may not see; And cause their loins continually to shake!
019	PSA	069	024	Pour out upon them thine indignation, And may the heat of thine anger overtake them!
019	PSA	069	025	Let their habitation be desolate, And let none dwell in their tents!
019	PSA	069	026	For they persecute those whom thou hast smitten, And talk of the pain of those whom thou hast wounded.
019	PSA	069	027	Add iniquity to their iniquity, And let them never come into thy favor!
019	PSA	069	028	Let them be blotted out of the book of the living; Let not their names be written with the righteous!
019	PSA	069	029	But I am poor, and sorrowful: May thine aid, O God! set me on high!
019	PSA	069	030	Then I will praise the name of God in a song; I will give glory to him with thanksgiving.
019	PSA	069	031	More pleasing shall this be to the LORD Than a full-horned and full-hoofed bullock.
019	PSA	069	032	The afflicted shall see, and rejoice; The hearts of them that fear God shall be revived.
019	PSA	069	033	For the LORD heareth the poor, And despiseth not his people in their bonds.
019	PSA	069	034	Let the heaven and the earth praise him; The sea, and all that move therein!
019	PSA	069	035	For God will save Zion, and will build the cities of Judah, That they may dwell therein, and possess it.
019	PSA	069	036	Yea, the posterity of his servants shall possess it, And they that love him shall dwell therein.
019	PSA	070	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David, for remembrance.” Make haste, O God! to deliver me, O LORD! come speedily to mine aid!
019	PSA	070	002	May they all be confounded, and covered with shame, Who seek to take my life! May they be driven back with disgrace Who desire to do me injury!
019	PSA	070	003	May they be turned back with shame Who cry out to me, “Aha! aha!”
019	PSA	070	004	But let all who seek thee be glad and rejoice in thee! Let them that love thy protection ever say, “May God be praised!”
019	PSA	070	005	But I am poor and needy; O God! hasten to mine aid! Thou art my help and my deliverer, O LORD! make no delay!
019	PSA	071	001	In thee, O LORD! do I put my trust! Let me never be put to shame!
019	PSA	071	002	In thy goodness deliver and rescue me; Incline thine ear to me, and save me!
019	PSA	071	003	Be thou the rock of my abode, where I may continually resort! Thou hast granted me deliverance; For thou art my rock and my fortress!
019	PSA	071	004	Save me, O my God! from the hand of the wicked, -From the hand of the unjust and cruel!
019	PSA	071	005	For thou art my hope, O Lord Jehovah! Thou hast been my trust from my youth!
019	PSA	071	006	Upon thee have I leaned from my birth; From my earliest breath thou hast been my support; My song hath been continually of thee!
019	PSA	071	007	I am a wonder to many, But thou art my strong refuge.
019	PSA	071	008	Let my mouth be filled with thy praise; Yea, all the day long, with thy glory.
019	PSA	071	009	Cast me not off in mine old age; Forsake me not, When my strength faileth!
019	PSA	071	010	For my enemies speak against me, And they who lay wait for my life consult together:
019	PSA	071	011	“God,” say they, “hath forsaken him; Pursue and seize him; for he hath none to deliver him!”
019	PSA	071	012	O God! be not far from me! Come speedily to mine aid, O my God!
019	PSA	071	013	Let them perish with shame who are my enemies; Let them be covered with contempt and dishonor who seek my hurt!
019	PSA	071	014	But I will hope continually; I shall yet praise thee more and more.
019	PSA	071	015	My mouth shall speak of thy goodness, —Of thy sure protection all the day long; For thy mercies are more than I can number.
019	PSA	071	016	I will celebrate thy mighty deeds, O Lord Jehovah! I will make mention of thy goodness, of thine only!
019	PSA	071	017	O God! thou hast taught me from my youth, And thus far have I declared thy wondrous deeds;
019	PSA	071	018	And now, when I am old and gray-headed, O God! forsake me not, Until I make known thine arm to the next generation, -Thy mighty power to all that are to come!
019	PSA	071	019	For thy goodness, O God! reacheth to the heavens; Wonderful things doest thou! O God! who is like unto thee?
019	PSA	071	020	Thou hast suffered us to see great and grievous troubles; Thou wilt again give us life, And wilt bring us back from the depths of the earth!
019	PSA	071	021	Thou wilt increase my greatness; Thou wilt again comfort me!
019	PSA	071	022	Then will I praise thee with the psaltery; Even thy faithfulness, O my God! To thee will I sing with the harp, O Holy One of Israel!
019	PSA	071	023	My lips shall rejoice, when I sing to thee; And my soul, which thou hast redeemed from death;
019	PSA	071	024	My tongue also shall continually speak of thy righteousness: For all who seek my hurt are brought to shame and confounded.
019	PSA	072	001	“For Solomon.” To the king, O God! give thy justice, And to the son of a king thy righteousness!
019	PSA	072	002	Yea! he shall judge thy people with equity, And thine oppressed ones with justice.
019	PSA	072	003	For the mountains shall bring forth peace to the people, And the hills, through righteousness.
019	PSA	072	004	He shall defend the oppressed of the people; He shall save the needy, And break in pieces the oppressor.
019	PSA	072	005	They shall fear thee as long as the sun and moon shall endure, From generation to generation.
019	PSA	072	006	He shall be like rain descending on the mown field, —Like showers which water the earth.
019	PSA	072	007	In his days shall the righteous flourish, And great shall be their prosperity, as long as the moon shall endure.
019	PSA	072	008	He shall have dominion from sea to sea, And from the river to the ends of the earth.
019	PSA	072	009	They that dwell in the desert shall bow before him, And his enemies shall lick the dust.
019	PSA	072	010	The kings of Tarshish and of the isles shall bring presents; The kings of Sheba and Seba shall offer gifts;
019	PSA	072	011	Yea, all kings shall fall down before him; All nations shall serve him.
019	PSA	072	012	For he shall deliver the poor who crieth for aid, And the oppressed who hath no helper.
019	PSA	072	013	He shall spare the weak and needy, And save the lives of the poor.
019	PSA	072	014	He shall redeem them from deceit and violence, And their blood shall be precious in his sight.
019	PSA	072	015	He shall prosper, and to him shall be given of the gold of Sheba; Prayer also shall be made for him continually, And daily shall he be praised.
019	PSA	072	016	There shall be an abundance of corn in the land; Its fruit shall shake like Lebanon, even on the tops of the mountains; And they of the cities shall flourish as the grass of the earth.
019	PSA	072	017	His name shall endure for ever; His name shall be continued as long as the sun. By him shall men bless themselves; All nations shall call him blessed.
019	PSA	072	018	[Praised be God, Jehovah, the God of Israel, Who alone doeth wonderful things!
019	PSA	072	019	Praised be his glorious name for ever! May his glory fill the whole earth! Amen, Amen!
019	PSA	072	020	Here end the Psalms of David, the son of Jesse.]
019	PSA	073	001	“BOOK III. A psalm of Asaph.” Truly God is good to Israel, —To those who are pure in heart.
019	PSA	073	002	Yet my feet almost gave way; My steps had well nigh slipped:
019	PSA	073	003	For I was envious of the proud, When I saw the prosperity of the wicked.
019	PSA	073	004	For they have no pains even to their death; Their bodies are in full health.
019	PSA	073	005	They have not the woes of other men, Neither are they smitten like other men.
019	PSA	073	006	Therefore pride encircleth their neck as a collar; Violence covereth them as a garment.
019	PSA	073	007	From their bosom issueth their iniquity; The designs of their hearts burst forth.
019	PSA	073	008	They mock, and speak of malicious oppression; Their words are haughty;
019	PSA	073	009	They stretch forth their mouth to the heavens, And their tongue goeth through the earth;
019	PSA	073	010	Therefore his people walk in their ways, And there drink from full fountains.
019	PSA	073	011	And they say, “How doth God know? How can there be knowledge with the Most High?”
019	PSA	073	012	Behold these are the ungodly! Yet they are ever prosperous; they heap up riches.
019	PSA	073	013	Verily I have cleansed my heart in vain; In vain have I washed my hands in innocence.
019	PSA	073	014	For every day have I been smitten; Every morn have I been chastened.
019	PSA	073	015	If I should resolve to speak like them, Surely I should be treacherous to the family of thy children.
019	PSA	073	016	So, when I studied to know this, It was painful to my eyes;
019	PSA	073	017	Until I went into the sanctuaries of God, And considered what was their end.
019	PSA	073	018	Behold! thou hast set them on slippery places; Thou castest them down into unseen pits.
019	PSA	073	019	How are they brought to desolation in a moment, And utterly consumed with sudden destruction!
019	PSA	073	020	As a dream when one awaketh, Thou, O Lord! when thou awakest, wilt make their vain show a derision.
019	PSA	073	021	When my heart was vexed And I was pierced in my reins,
019	PSA	073	022	Then was I stupid and without understanding; I was like one of the brutes before thee.
019	PSA	073	023	Yet am I ever under thy care; By my right hand thou dost hold me up.
019	PSA	073	024	Thou wilt guide me with thy counsel, And at last receive me in glory.
019	PSA	073	025	Whom have I in heaven but thee, And whom on earth do I love in comparison with thee?
019	PSA	073	026	Though my flesh and my heart fail, God is the strength of my heart, and my portion for ever.
019	PSA	073	027	For, lo! they who are far from thee perish; Thou destroyest all who estrange themselves from thee.
019	PSA	073	028	But it is good for me to draw near to God; I put my trust in the Lord Jehovah, That I may declare all thy works.
019	PSA	074	001	“A psalm of Asaph.” O God! why hast thou cast us off for ever? Why doth thine anger smoke against the flock of thy pasture?
019	PSA	074	002	Remember the people which thou didst purchase of old; Thine own inheritance, which thou didst redeem; That Mount Zion, where thou once didst dwell!
019	PSA	074	003	Hasten thy steps to those utter desolations! Every thing in the sanctuary hath the enemy abused!
019	PSA	074	004	Thine enemies roar in the place of thine assemblies; Their own symbols have they set up for signs.
019	PSA	074	005	They appear like those who raise the axe against a thicket;
019	PSA	074	006	They have broken down the carved work of thy temple with axes and hammers;
019	PSA	074	007	They have cast fire into thy sanctuary; They have profaned, and cast to the ground, the dwelling-place of thy name.
019	PSA	074	008	They said in their hearts, “Let us destroy them all together!” They have burned all God's places of assembly in the land.
019	PSA	074	009	We no longer see our signs; There is no prophet among us, Nor any one that knoweth how long this desolation shall endure.
019	PSA	074	010	How long, O God! shall the adversary revile? Shall the enemy blaspheme thy name for ever?
019	PSA	074	011	Why withdrawest thou thy hand, even thy right hand? Take it from thy bosom, and destroy!
019	PSA	074	012	Yet God was our king of old, Working salvation in the midst of the earth.
019	PSA	074	013	Thou didst divide the sea by thy power; Thou didst crush the heads of the sea-monsters in the waters.
019	PSA	074	014	Thou didst break in pieces the head of the crocodile; Thou gavest him for food to the inhabitants of the desert.
019	PSA	074	015	Thou didst cleave forth the fountain and the stream; Thou didst dry up perennial rivers.
019	PSA	074	016	Thine is the day, and thine the night; Thou didst prepare the light and the sun.
019	PSA	074	017	Thou didst establish all the boundaries of the earth; Thou didst make summer and winter.
019	PSA	074	018	O remember that the enemy hath reviled Jehovah; That an impious people hath blasphemed thy name!
019	PSA	074	019	Give not up the life of thy turtle-dove to the wild beast; Forget not for ever thine afflicted people!
019	PSA	074	020	Have regard to thy covenant! For all the dark places of the land are full of the abodes of cruelty.
019	PSA	074	021	O let not the afflicted go away ashamed! Let the poor and needy praise thy name!
019	PSA	074	022	Arise, O God! maintain thy cause! Remember how the impious revileth thee daily!
019	PSA	074	023	Forget not the clamor of thine adversaries, —The noise of thine enemies, which continually increaseth!
019	PSA	075	001	“For the leader of the music. To the tune of “Do not destroy.” A psalm of Asaph.” We give thanks to thee, O God! we give thanks to thee, and near is thy name; Men shall declare thy wondrous deeds!
019	PSA	075	002	“When I see my time, Then will I judge with equity.
019	PSA	075	003	The earth trembleth, and all her inhabitants; But I uphold her pillars.”
019	PSA	075	004	I say to the proud, Behave not proudly! To the wicked, Lift not up your horn!
019	PSA	075	005	Lift not up your horn on high, And speak not with a stiff neck!
019	PSA	075	006	For promotion cometh neither from the east, nor from the west, nor from the south;
019	PSA	075	007	But it is God that judgeth; He putteth down one, and setteth up another.
019	PSA	075	008	For in the hand of the LORD there is a cup; The wine is foaming and full of spices, And of it he poureth out; Even to the dregs shall all the wicked of the earth drink it.
019	PSA	075	009	Therefore I will extol him for ever; I will sing praise to the God of Jacob.
019	PSA	075	010	“I will bring down all the power of the wicked; But the righteous shall lift up their heads.”
019	PSA	076	001	“For the leader of the music. Upon stringed instruments. A Psalm of Asaph.” In Judah is God known; Great is his name in Israel.
019	PSA	076	002	In Jerusalem is his tabernacle, And in Zion his dwelling-place.
019	PSA	076	003	There brake he the lightning of the bow, The shield, the sword, and all the weapons of battle.
019	PSA	076	004	More glorious and excellent art thou Than those mountains of robbers!
019	PSA	076	005	Spoiled are the stout-hearted; They sank into their sleep; The hands of the mighty were powerless.
019	PSA	076	006	Before thy rebuke, O God of Jacob! Fell chariot and horseman into a deep sleep!
019	PSA	076	007	Thou, thou, O God! art terrible! Who can stand before thee in thine anger?
019	PSA	076	008	Thou didst cause judgment to be heard from heaven; The earth trembled and was still,
019	PSA	076	009	When God arose to judgment, To save all the oppressed of the earth!
019	PSA	076	010	The wrath of man shall praise thee, When thou girdest on the whole of thy wrath!
019	PSA	076	011	Make and perform vows to Jehovah, your God! Let all that dwell around him bring gifts to the terrible One,
019	PSA	076	012	Who casteth down the pride of princes, Who is terrible to the kings of the earth!
019	PSA	077	001	“For the leader of the music of the Jeduthunites. A psalm of Asaph.” I call upon God; I cry aloud for help; I call upon God, that he would hear me!
019	PSA	077	002	In the day of my trouble I seek the Lord; In the night is my hand stretched forth continually; My soul refuseth to be comforted.
019	PSA	077	003	I remember God, and am disquieted; I think of him, and my spirit is overwhelmed.
019	PSA	077	004	Thou keepest mine eyelids from closing; I am distressed, so that I cannot speak!
019	PSA	077	005	I think of the days of old, —The years of ancient times.
019	PSA	077	006	I call to remembrance my songs in the night; I meditate in my heart, And my spirit inquireth:
019	PSA	077	007	Will the Lord be angry for ever? Will he be favorable no more?
019	PSA	077	008	Is his mercy utterly withdrawn for ever? Doth his promise fail from generation to generation?
019	PSA	077	009	Hath God forgotten to be gracious? Hath he in anger shut up his compassion?
019	PSA	077	010	Then I say, “This is mine affliction, A change in the right hand of the Most High.”
019	PSA	077	011	I remember the deeds of Jehovah; I think of thy wonders of old.
019	PSA	077	012	I meditate on all thy works, And talk of thy doings.
019	PSA	077	013	Thy ways, O God! are holy! Who so great a god as our God?
019	PSA	077	014	Thou art a God who doest wonders; Thou hast manifested thy power among the nations.
019	PSA	077	015	With thy strong arm thou didst redeem thy people, —The sons of Jacob and Joseph.
019	PSA	077	016	The waters saw thee, O God! The waters saw thee, and feared, And the deep trembled.
019	PSA	077	017	The clouds poured out water, The skies sent forth thunder, And thine arrows flew.
019	PSA	077	018	Thy thunder roared in the whirlwind; Thy lightning illumined the world; The earth trembled and shook.
019	PSA	077	019	Thy way was through the sea, And thy path through great waters; And thy footsteps could not be found.
019	PSA	077	020	Thou didst lead thy people like a flock, By the hands of Moses and Aaron.
019	PSA	078	001	“A psalm of Asaph.” Give ear, O my people, to my instruction! Incline your ears to the words of my mouth!
019	PSA	078	002	I will open my mouth in a psalm; I will utter sayings of ancient times.
019	PSA	078	003	What we have heard and learned, And our fathers have told us,
019	PSA	078	004	We will not hide from their children; Showing to the generation to come the praises of Jehovah, His might, and the wonders he hath wrought.
019	PSA	078	005	For he appointed statutes in Jacob, And established a law in Israel, Which he commanded our fathers To make known to their children;
019	PSA	078	006	So that the generation to come might know them; The children, which should be born, and rise up, Who should declare them to their children;
019	PSA	078	007	That they might put their trust in God, And not forget his deeds, But keep his commandments;
019	PSA	078	008	And might not be, like their forefathers, A stubborn and rebellious generation, —A generation whose heart was not fixed upon God, And whose spirit was not steadfast toward the Almighty.
019	PSA	078	009	The children of Ephraim were like armed bowmen, Who turn their backs in the day of battle.
019	PSA	078	010	They kept not the covenant of God, And refused to walk in his law;
019	PSA	078	011	And forgot his mighty deeds, And the wonders he had shown them.
019	PSA	078	012	Marvellous things did he in the sight of their fathers, In the land of Egypt, in the field of Zoan.
019	PSA	078	013	He divided the sea, and caused them to pass through; Yea, he made the waters to stand as a heap.
019	PSA	078	014	By day he led them by a cloud, And all the night by a light of fire.
019	PSA	078	015	He clave the rocks in the wilderness, And gave them drink, as from the great deep.
019	PSA	078	016	From the rock he brought flowing streams, And made water to run down like rivers.
019	PSA	078	017	Yet still they sinned against him, And provoked the Most High in the desert.
019	PSA	078	018	They tempted God in their hearts, By asking food for their delight.
019	PSA	078	019	Yea, they spake against God, and said, “Can God spread a table in the wilderness?
019	PSA	078	020	Behold! he smote the rock, and the water flowed, And streams gushed forth: Is he also able to give bread? Can he provide flesh for his people?”
019	PSA	078	021	When, therefore, the LORD heard this, he was wroth: So a fire was kindled against Jacob, And anger arose against Israel.
019	PSA	078	022	Because they believed not in God, And trusted not in his aid.
019	PSA	078	023	Yet he had commanded the clouds above, And had opened the doors of heaven;
019	PSA	078	024	And had rained down upon them manna for food, And had given them the corn of heaven.
019	PSA	078	025	Every one ate the food of princes; He sent them bread to the full.
019	PSA	078	026	Then he caused a strong wind to blow in the heavens, And by his power he brought a south wind;
019	PSA	078	027	He rained down flesh upon them as dust, And feathered fowls as the sand of the sea.
019	PSA	078	028	He caused them to fall in the midst of their camp, Round about their habitations.
019	PSA	078	029	So they did eat, and were filled; For he gave them their own desire.
019	PSA	078	030	Their desire was not yet satisfied, And their meat was yet in their mouths,
019	PSA	078	031	When the wrath of God came upon them, And slew their strong men, And smote down the chosen men of Israel.
019	PSA	078	032	For all this they sinned still, And put no trust in his wondrous works.
019	PSA	078	033	Therefore he consumed their days in vanity, And their years in sudden destruction.
019	PSA	078	034	When he slew them, they sought him; They returned, and sought earnestly for God;
019	PSA	078	035	And remembered that God was their rock, And the Most High their redeemer.
019	PSA	078	036	But they only flattered him with their mouths, And spake falsely to him with their tongues.
019	PSA	078	037	For their hearts were not true to him, Nor were they steadfast in his covenant.
019	PSA	078	038	Yet, being full of compassion, he forgave their iniquity, And would not utterly destroy them; Often he restrained his indignation, And stirred not up all his anger.
019	PSA	078	039	He remembered that they were but flesh, —A breath, that passeth and cometh not back.
019	PSA	078	040	How often did they provoke him in the wilderness! How often did they anger him in the desert!
019	PSA	078	041	Again and again they tempted God, And offended the Holy One of Israel.
019	PSA	078	042	They remembered not his hand, Nor the day when he delivered them from the enemy;
019	PSA	078	043	What signs he had wrought in Egypt, And what wonders in the fields of Zoan.
019	PSA	078	044	He turned their rivers into blood, So that they could not drink of their streams.
019	PSA	078	045	He sent amongst them flies, which devoured them, And frogs, which destroyed them.
019	PSA	078	046	He gave also their fruits to the caterpillar, And their labor to the locust.
019	PSA	078	047	He destroyed their vines with hail, And their sycamore-trees with frost.
019	PSA	078	048	He also gave up their cattle to hail, And their flocks to hot thunderbolts.
019	PSA	078	049	He sent against them the fierceness of his anger, Wrath, indignation, and woe, —A host of angels of evil.
019	PSA	078	050	He made a way for his anger, He spared them not from death, But gave up their lives to the pestilence.
019	PSA	078	051	He smote all the firstborn in Egypt; The first-fruits of their strength in the tents of Ham.
019	PSA	078	052	But he led forth his own people like sheep, And guided them like a flock in the wilderness.
019	PSA	078	053	He led them on safely, so that they feared not, While the sea overwhelmed their enemies.
019	PSA	078	054	He brought them to his own sacred border, Even to this mountain which his right hand had gained.
019	PSA	078	055	He cast out the nations before them, And divided their land by a measuring-line, as an inheritance, And caused the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.
019	PSA	078	056	Yet they tempted and provoked God, the Most High, And kept not his statutes;
019	PSA	078	057	Like their fathers they were faithless, and turned back; They turned aside, like a deceitful bow.
019	PSA	078	058	They provoked his anger by their high places, And stirred up his jealousy by their graven images.
019	PSA	078	059	God saw this, and was wroth, And greatly abhorred Israel;
019	PSA	078	060	So that he forsook the habitation at Shiloh, The tabernacle where he dwelt among men,
019	PSA	078	061	And delivered his strength into captivity, And his glory into the hand of the enemy.
019	PSA	078	062	His own people he gave up to the sword, And was wroth with his own inheritance.
019	PSA	078	063	Fire consumed their young men, And their maidens did not bewail them.
019	PSA	078	064	Their priests fell by the sword, And their widows made no lamentation.
019	PSA	078	065	But at length the Lord awaked as from sleep, As a hero who had been overpowered by wine;
019	PSA	078	066	He smote his enemies, and drove them back, And covered them with everlasting disgrace.
019	PSA	078	067	Yet he rejected the tents of Joseph, And chose not the tribe of Ephraim;
019	PSA	078	068	But chose the tribe of Judah, The Mount Zion which he loved;
019	PSA	078	069	Where he built, like the heavens, his sanctuary; Like the earth, which he hath established for ever.
019	PSA	078	070	And he chose David, his servant, And took him from the sheepfolds;
019	PSA	078	071	From tending the suckling ewes he brought him To feed Jacob his people, And Israel his inheritance.
019	PSA	078	072	He fed them with an upright heart, And guided them with skilful hands.
019	PSA	079	001	“A psalm of Asaph.” O God! the nations have come into thine inheritance; They have polluted thy holy temple; They have made Jerusalem a heap of ruins!
019	PSA	079	002	They have given the dead bodies of thy servants to be food for the birds of heaven, The flesh of thy holy ones to the wild beasts of the earth!
019	PSA	079	003	Their blood have they shed like water around Jerusalem, And there was none to bury them!
019	PSA	079	004	We have become the reproach of our neighbors, —The scorn and derision of those around us.
019	PSA	079	005	How long, O LORD! wilt thou be angry for ever? How long shall thy jealousy burn like fire?
019	PSA	079	006	Pour out thy wrath on the nations which acknowledge thee not. And on the kingdoms which call not upon thy name!
019	PSA	079	007	For they have devoured Jacob, And laid waste his dwelling-place.
019	PSA	079	008	O remember not against us former iniquities; Let thy tender mercy speedily succor us,
019	PSA	079	009	For we are brought very low! Help us, O God of our salvation! for the honor of thy name; F or thy name's sake save us, and forgive our iniquities!
019	PSA	079	010	Why should the nations say, “Where is their God?” May the revenging of the blood of thy servants, which hath been shed, Be manifested among the nations before our eyes!
019	PSA	079	011	Let the cry of the prisoner come before thee! According to the greatness of thy power preserve those that are appointed to die!
019	PSA	079	012	And return sevenfold into our neighbors' bosoms The reproach with which they have reproached thee, O Lord!
019	PSA	079	013	So shall we, thy people, and the flock of thy pasture, Give thanks to thee for ever. And show forth thy praise to all generations.
019	PSA	080	001	“For the leader of the music. Upon the Shushan-Eduth. A psalm of Asaph.” Give ear, O Shepherd of Israel! Thou who leadest Joseph like a flock, Thou who sittest between the cherubs, shine forth!
019	PSA	080	002	Before Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh, stir up thy strength, And come and save us!
019	PSA	080	003	Bring us back, O God! And cause thy face to shine, that we may be saved!
019	PSA	080	004	O LORD, God of hosts! How long wilt thou be angry against the prayer of thy people?
019	PSA	080	005	For thou causest them to eat the bread of tears, And givest them tears to drink, in full measure.
019	PSA	080	006	Thou hast made us the object of strife to our neighbors, And our enemies hold us in derision.
019	PSA	080	007	Bring us back, O God of hosts! And cause thy face to shine that we may be saved!
019	PSA	080	008	Thou didst bring a vine out of Egypt; Thou didst expel the nations, and plant it.
019	PSA	080	009	Thou didst prepare a place for it; It spread its roots, and filled the land.
019	PSA	080	010	The mountains were covered with its shade, And its branches were like the cedars of God.
019	PSA	080	011	It sent out its boughs to the sea, And its branches to the river.
019	PSA	080	012	Why hast thou now broken down its hedges, So that all who pass by do pluck from it?
019	PSA	080	013	The boar from the wood doth waste it, And the wild beast of the forest doth devour it.
019	PSA	080	014	O God of hosts! return, we beseech thee, Look down from heaven, and behold, And have regard to this vine!
019	PSA	080	015	Protect what thy right hand planted; The branch which thou madest strong for thyself!
019	PSA	080	016	It is burnt with fire; it is cut down; Under thy rebuke they perish.
019	PSA	080	017	May thy hand be over the man of thy right hand, The man whom thou madest strong for thyself!
019	PSA	080	018	So will we no more turn back from thee: Revive us, and upon thy name alone will we call!
019	PSA	080	019	Bring us back, O LORD, God of hosts! And cause thy face to shine, that we may he saved!
019	PSA	081	001	“For the leader of the music. On the Gittith. A psalm of Asaph.” Sing joyfully to God, our strength! Shout with gladness to the God of Jacob!
019	PSA	081	002	Raise a song, and strike the timbrel, The sweet-sounding harp, and the psaltery!
019	PSA	081	003	Blow the trumpet at the new moon; At the full moon, also, on our festal day!
019	PSA	081	004	For this is a statute for Israel, A law of the God of Jacob;
019	PSA	081	005	He appointed it as a memorial in Joseph, When he went out of the land of Egypt, Where he heard a language which he knew not.
019	PSA	081	006	“I relieved [said he] thy shoulders from their burden; Thy hands were removed from the hod.
019	PSA	081	007	Thou didst call in trouble, and I delivered thee; In the secret place of thunder I answered thee; I proved thee at the waters of Meribah. (Pause)
019	PSA	081	008	Hear, O my people! and I will admonish thee! O Israel! that thou wouldst hearken to me!
019	PSA	081	009	Let there be no strange god within thee, Nor worship thou any foreign god!
019	PSA	081	010	I Jehovah am thy God, Who brought thee out of the land of Egypt: Open wide thy mouth, and I will fill it!
019	PSA	081	011	But my people would not listen to my voice, And Israel would not hearken to me.
019	PSA	081	012	So I gave them up to the obstinacy of their hearts, And they walked according to their own devices.
019	PSA	081	013	“O that my people had hearkened to me! That Israel had walked in my ways!
019	PSA	081	014	Soon would I have brought low their enemies, And turned my hand against their adversaries.
019	PSA	081	015	The haters of Jehovah should have become suppliants to them, And their prosperity should have endured for ever.
019	PSA	081	016	With the finest of the wheat I would have fed them, And with honey out of the rock would I have satisfied them.”
019	PSA	082	001	“A psalm of Asaph.” God standeth in God's assembly, He judgeth in the midst of the gods.
019	PSA	082	002	“How long will ye judge unjustly, And favor the cause of the wicked? (Pause)
019	PSA	082	003	Defend the poor and the fatherless; Do justice to the wretched and the needy!
019	PSA	082	004	Deliver the poor and the destitute; Save them from the hand of the wicked!
019	PSA	082	005	They are without knowledge and without understanding; They walk in darkness: Therefore all the foundations of the land are shaken.
019	PSA	082	006	I have said, Ye are gods, And all of you children of the Most High;
019	PSA	082	007	But ye shall die like men, And fall like the rest of the princes.”
019	PSA	082	008	Arise, O God! judge the earth! For all the nations are thy possession.
019	PSA	083	001	“A psalm of Asaph.” O God! keep not silence! Hold not thy peace, and be not still, O God!
019	PSA	083	002	For, lo! thine enemies roar, And they who hate thee lift up their heads.
019	PSA	083	003	For they form secret plots against thy people, And consult together against thy chosen ones.
019	PSA	083	004	“Come,” say they, “let us blot them out from the number of the nations, That the name of Israel may no more be remembered!”
019	PSA	083	005	With one consent they consult together, Against thee do they form a league, —
019	PSA	083	006	The tents of Edom and the Ishmaelites, Of Moab and the Hagarenes,
019	PSA	083	007	Gebal and Ammon and Amalek, The Philistines, with the inhabitants of Tyre.
019	PSA	083	008	The Assyrians also are joined with them; They lend their strength to the children of Lot.
019	PSA	083	009	Do to them as to the Midianites, As to Sisera, as to Jabin at the brook Kison,
019	PSA	083	010	Who perished at Endor, And were trampled like dung to the earth.
019	PSA	083	011	Make their chiefs like Oreb and Zeeb; Yea, all their princes as Zeba and Zalmunna!
019	PSA	083	012	Who say, “Let us seize on God's habitations!”
019	PSA	083	013	Make them, O my God! like whirling chaff; Like stubble before the wind!
019	PSA	083	014	As fire consumeth the forest, And as flame setteth the mountains in a blaze,
019	PSA	083	015	So pursue them with thy tempest, And terrify them with thy storm!
019	PSA	083	016	Cover their faces with shame, That they may seek thy name, O LORD!
019	PSA	083	017	Let them be confounded! Yea, let them be put to shame, and perish!
019	PSA	083	018	That they may know that thy name alone is Jehovah; That thou art the Most High over all the earth.
019	PSA	084	001	“For the leader of the music. On the Gittith. A psalm of the sons of Korah.” How lovely are thy tabernacles, O LORD of hosts!
019	PSA	084	002	My soul longeth, yea, fainteth, for the courts of the LORD; My heart and my flesh cry aloud for the living God.
019	PSA	084	003	The very sparrow findeth an abode, And the swallow a nest, where they may lay their young, By thine altars, O LORD of hosts, My king and my God!
019	PSA	084	004	Happy they who dwell in thy house, Who are continually praising thee! (Pause)
019	PSA	084	005	Happy the man whose glory is in thee, In whose heart are the ways [to Jerusalem]!
019	PSA	084	006	Passing through the valley of Baca, they make it a fountain; and the early rain covereth it with blessings.
019	PSA	084	007	They go on from strength to strength; Every one of them appeareth before God in Zion.
019	PSA	084	008	Hear my prayer, O LORD, God of hosts! Give ear, O God of Jacob! (Pause)
019	PSA	084	009	Look down, O God! our shield, And behold the face of thine anointed!
019	PSA	084	010	For a day spent in thy courts is better than a thousand: I would rather stand on the threshold of the house of my God, Than dwell in the tents of wickedness.
019	PSA	084	011	For the LORD God is a sun and a shield; The LORD giveth grace and glory; No good thing doth he withhold From them that walk uprightly.
019	PSA	084	012	O LORD of hosts! Happy the man who trusteth in thee!
019	PSA	085	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of the sons of Korah.” O LORD! thou hast been favorable to thy land; Thou hast brought back the captives of Jacob;
019	PSA	085	002	Thou didst forgive the iniquity of thy people, And cover all their sins! (Pause)
019	PSA	085	003	Thou didst take away all thy displeasure, And abate the fierceness of thy wrath.
019	PSA	085	004	Restore us, O God of our salvation! And let thine anger towards us cease!
019	PSA	085	005	Wilt thou be angry with us for ever? Wilt thou continue thy wrath from generation to generation?
019	PSA	085	006	Wilt thou not revive us again, That thy people may rejoice in thee?
019	PSA	085	007	Show us thy compassion, O LORD! And grant us thy salvation!
019	PSA	085	008	I will hear what God the LORD will speak: Truly he will speak peace to his people, and to his servants; Only let them not turn again to folly!
019	PSA	085	009	Yea, his salvation is near to those who fear him, That glory may dwell in our land.
019	PSA	085	010	Mercy and truth shall meet together, Righteousness and peace shall kiss each other;
019	PSA	085	011	Truth shall spring out of the earth; Righteousness shall look down from heaven.
019	PSA	085	012	Yea, Jehovah will give prosperity, And our land shall yield her increase.
019	PSA	085	013	Righteousness shall go before him, And set us in the way of his steps.
019	PSA	086	001	“A prayer of David.” Incline thine ear, O LORD! and hear me, For I am poor and distressed!
019	PSA	086	002	Preserve my life, for I am devoted to thee! Save, O thou my God! thy servant who trusteth in thee!
019	PSA	086	003	Have pity upon me, O Lord! For to thee do I cry daily!
019	PSA	086	004	Revive the soul of thy servant, For to thee, O Lord! do I lift up my soul!
019	PSA	086	005	For thou, Lord, art good, and ready to forgive; Yea, rich in mercy to all that call upon thee!
019	PSA	086	006	Give ear, O LORD! to my prayer, And attend to the voice of my supplication!
019	PSA	086	007	In the day of my trouble I call upon thee, For thou dost answer me!
019	PSA	086	008	Among the gods there is none like thee, O Lord! And there are no works like thy works!
019	PSA	086	009	All the nations which thou hast made must come and worship before thee, O Lord! And glorify thy name!
019	PSA	086	010	For great art thou, and wondrous are thy works; Thou alone art God!
019	PSA	086	011	Teach me, O LORD! thy way, That I may walk in thy truth; Unite all my heart to fear thy name!
019	PSA	086	012	I will praise thee, O Lord, my God! with my whole heart; I will give glory to thy name for ever!
019	PSA	086	013	For thy kindness to me hath been great; Thou hast delivered me from the depths of the underworld!
019	PSA	086	014	O God! the proud have risen against me; Bands of cruel men seek my life, And set not thee before their eyes.
019	PSA	086	015	But thou, O Lord! art a God full of compassion and kindness, Long-suffering, rich in mercy and truth!
019	PSA	086	016	Look upon me, and have compassion upon me! Give thy strength to thy servant, And save the son of thy handmaid!
019	PSA	086	017	Show me a token for good, That my enemies may see it and be confounded; Because thou, O LORD! helpest and comfortest me!
019	PSA	087	001	“A psalm of the sons of Korah.” His foundation is in the holy mountains;
019	PSA	087	002	Jehovah loveth the gates of Zion More than all the dwellings of Jacob.
019	PSA	087	003	Glorious things are said of thee, O city of God! (Pause)
019	PSA	087	004	“I name Egypt and Babylon among them that know me; Behold! Philistia, Tyre, and Ethiopia, —They also were born there.”
019	PSA	087	005	And of Zion it shall be said, “Men of every nation were born there, And the Most High hath established her.”
019	PSA	087	006	Jehovah, when he numbereth the nations, shall write, “These were born there!” (Pause)
019	PSA	087	007	Singers as well as dancers, —All my springs are in thee!
019	PSA	088	001	“A psalm of the sons of Korah. For the leader of the music. Upon wind instruments. A psalm of Heman, the Ezrahite.” O LORD, God of my salvation! To thee do I cry by day, And by night is my prayer before thee!
019	PSA	088	002	Let my supplication come before thee; Incline thine ear to my cry!
019	PSA	088	003	For my soul is full of misery, And my life draweth near to the underworld.
019	PSA	088	004	I am counted with those who are going down to the pit; I am like one who hath no strength.
019	PSA	088	005	I am left to myself among the dead, Like the slain who lie in the grave, Whom thou no more rememberest, And who are cut off from thy [protecting] hand.
019	PSA	088	006	Thou hast placed me in a deep pit, In a dark and deep abyss.
019	PSA	088	007	Thy wrath presseth hard upon me, And thou afflictest me with all thy waves! (Pause)
019	PSA	088	008	Thou hast put mine acquaintances far from me, Yea, thou hast made me their abhorrence: I am shut up, and cannot go forth.
019	PSA	088	009	Mine eyes languish by reason of my affliction. I call upon thee daily, O LORD! To thee do I stretch out my hands!
019	PSA	088	010	Canst thou show wonders to the dead? Shall the dead arise, and praise thee? (Pause)
019	PSA	088	011	Shall thy goodness be declared in the grave, Or thy faithfulness in the place of corruption?
019	PSA	088	012	Shall thy wonders be known in the dark, And thy justice in the land of forgetfulness?
019	PSA	088	013	To thee do I cry, O LORD! In the morning doth my cry come before thee.
019	PSA	088	014	Why, O LORD! dost thou cast me off? Why hidest thou thy face from me?
019	PSA	088	015	I have been afflicted and languishing from my youth; I suffer thy terrors, and am distracted.
019	PSA	088	016	Thy fierce wrath overwhelmeth me; Thy terrors utterly destroy me.
019	PSA	088	017	They surround me daily like water; They compass me about together.
019	PSA	088	018	Lover and friend hast thou put far from me; My acquaintances are withdrawn from my sight.
019	PSA	089	001	“A psalm of Ethan, the Ezrahite.” I will sing of the mercies of the LORD for ever; With my mouth will I make known thy faithfulness to all generations!
019	PSA	089	002	For I know that thy mercy endureth for ever; Thou hast established thy truth like the heavens.
019	PSA	089	003	“I have made a covenant with my chosen; I have sworn to David, my servant:
019	PSA	089	004	Thy family I will establish for ever, And build up thy throne to all generations.” (Pause)
019	PSA	089	005	The heavens shall praise thy wonders, O LORD! And the assembly of the holy ones thy truth!
019	PSA	089	006	Who in the heavens can be compared to Jehovah? Who is like Jehovah among the sons of God?
019	PSA	089	007	A God greatly to be feared in the assembly of the holy ones, And to be had in reverence above all who are around him?
019	PSA	089	008	O Jehovah, God of hosts! Who is mighty like thee, O Jehovah? And thy faithfulness is round about thee.
019	PSA	089	009	Thou rulest the raging of the sea; When the waves thereof rise, thou stillest them!
019	PSA	089	010	Thou didst break Rahab in pieces, as one that is slain; Thou didst scatter thine enemies with thy mighty arm.
019	PSA	089	011	The heavens are thine; thine also is the earth; The world and all that is therein, thou didst found them.
019	PSA	089	012	The North and the South were created by thee; Tabor and Hermon rejoice in thy name.
019	PSA	089	013	Thine is a mighty arm; Strong is thy hand, and high thy right hand.
019	PSA	089	014	Justice and equity are the foundation of thy throne; Mercy and truth go before thy face.
019	PSA	089	015	Happy the people that know the trumpet's sound! They walk, O LORD! in the light of thy countenance;
019	PSA	089	016	In thy name they daily rejoice, And in thy righteousness they glory!
019	PSA	089	017	For thou art the glory of their strength; Yea, through thy favor our horn exalteth itself!
019	PSA	089	018	For from Jehovah is our shield, And from the Holy One of Israel is our king.
019	PSA	089	019	Once thou spakest in a vision to thy holy one, And saidst, —”I have laid help on one that is mighty; I have exalted one chosen from the people;
019	PSA	089	020	I have found David, my servant; With my holy oil have I anointed him.
019	PSA	089	021	With him shall my hand be established, And my arm shall strengthen him.
019	PSA	089	022	The enemy shall not have power over him, Nor shall the unrighteous man oppress him.
019	PSA	089	023	For I will beat down his foes before him, And overthrow them that hate him.
019	PSA	089	024	My faithfulness and mercy shall be with him, And through my name shall his horn be exalted.
019	PSA	089	025	I will extend his hand to the sea, And his right hand to the rivers.
019	PSA	089	026	He shall say to me, 'Thou art my father, My God, and the rock of my salvation!'
019	PSA	089	027	I will also make him my first-born, Highest of the kings of the earth.
019	PSA	089	028	My mercy I will continue to him for ever; My covenant with him shall be steadfast.
019	PSA	089	029	I will make his family to endure for ever; And his throne shall be as lasting as the heavens.
019	PSA	089	030	Should his children forsake my law, And walk not in my statutes,
019	PSA	089	031	Should they break my commandments, And observe not my precepts,
019	PSA	089	032	I will punish their transgressions with a rod, And their iniquity with stripes.
019	PSA	089	033	But my kindness will I not withdraw from him, Nor suffer my faithfulness to fail.
019	PSA	089	034	I will not break my covenant, Nor alter what hath gone from my lips.
019	PSA	089	035	Once have I sworn in my holiness, That I will not be false unto David.
019	PSA	089	036	His family shall endure for ever, And his throne as the sun before me.
019	PSA	089	037	It shall be established for ever like the moon; Like the faithful witness in the sky.”
019	PSA	089	038	But now thou forsakest and abhorrest, And art angry with, thine anointed.
019	PSA	089	039	Thou hast made void the covenant with thy servant; Thou hast cast his crown to the ground.
019	PSA	089	040	Thou hast broken down all his hedges; Thou hast brought his strongholds to ruin.
019	PSA	089	041	All who pass by plunder him; He is a reproach to his neighbors.
019	PSA	089	042	Thou hast lifted up the right hand of his enemies; Thou hast made all his adversaries to rejoice.
019	PSA	089	043	Yea, thou hast turned the edge of his sword, And made him unable to stand in battle.
019	PSA	089	044	Thou hast brought his glory to an end, And hast cast down his throne to the ground.
019	PSA	089	045	Thou hast shortened the days of his youth; Thou hast covered him with shame.
019	PSA	089	046	How long, O LORD! wilt thou hide thyself for ever? How long shall thine anger burn like fire?
019	PSA	089	047	Remember how short is my life, To what frailty thou hast created all men!
019	PSA	089	048	What man liveth, and seeth not death? Who can deliver himself from the underworld?
019	PSA	089	049	Where, Lord, is thy former loving-kindness Which thou didst swear to David in thy truth?
019	PSA	089	050	Remember, O Lord! the reproach of thy servants, How I bear in my bosom the taunts of all the many nations,
019	PSA	089	051	With which thine enemies have reproached me, O LORD! With which they have reproached the footsteps of thine anointed!
019	PSA	089	052	[Praised be Jehovah for ever! Amen, yea, amen!]
019	PSA	090	001	“BOOK IV. A prayer of Moses, the man of God.” LORD! thou hast been our dwelling-place In all generations!
019	PSA	090	002	Before the mountains were brought forth, Or ever thou hadst formed the earth and the world, Even from everlasting to everlasting thou art God!
019	PSA	090	003	But man thou turnest again to dust, And sayst, “Return, ye children of men!”
019	PSA	090	004	For a thousand years are, in thy sight, As yesterday when it is past, And as a watch in the night.
019	PSA	090	005	Thou carriest him away as with a flood; He is a dream; In the morning he springeth up like grass,
019	PSA	090	006	Which flourisheth and shooteth up in the morning, And in the evening is cut down, and withered.
019	PSA	090	007	For we are consumed by thine anger, And by thy wrath are we destroyed.
019	PSA	090	008	Thou settest our iniquities before thee, Our secret sins in the light of thy countenance.
019	PSA	090	009	By reason of thine anger all our days vanish away; We spend our years like a thought.
019	PSA	090	010	The days of our life are threescore years and ten, And, by reason of strength, may be fourscore years: Yet is the pride of them weariness and sorrow; For it vanisheth swiftly, and we fly away.
019	PSA	090	011	Yet who attendeth to the power of thine anger? Who with due reverence regardeth thine indignation?
019	PSA	090	012	Teach us so to number our days, That we may apply our hearts to wisdom!
019	PSA	090	013	Desist, O LORD! How long—? Have compassion upon thy servants!
019	PSA	090	014	Satisfy us speedily with thy mercy, That we may rejoice and be glad all our days!
019	PSA	090	015	Make us glad according to the time in which thou hast afflicted us; According to the years in which we have seen adversity!
019	PSA	090	016	Let thy deeds be known to thy servants, And thy glory to their children!
019	PSA	090	017	Let the favor of the LORD our God be upon us, And establish for us the work of our hands; Yea, the work of our hands, establish thou it!
019	PSA	091	001	He who sitteth under the shelter of the Most High Maketh his abode in the shadow of the Almighty.
019	PSA	091	002	I say to the LORD, Thou art my refuge and my fortress; My God, in whom I trust.
019	PSA	091	003	Surely he will deliver thee from the snare of the fowler, And from the wasting pestilence;
019	PSA	091	004	He will cover thee with his feathers, And under his wings shalt thou find refuge; His faithfulness shall be thy shield and buckler.
019	PSA	091	005	Thou shalt not be afraid of the terror of the night, Nor of the arrow that flieth by day;
019	PSA	091	006	Nor of the pestilence that walketh in darkness, Nor of the plague that destroyeth at noonday.
019	PSA	091	007	A thousand shall fall by thy side, And ten thousand at thy right hand; But thee it shall not touch.
019	PSA	091	008	Thou shalt only behold with thine eyes, And see the recompense of the wicked.
019	PSA	091	009	Because thou hast made the LORD thy refuge, And the Most High thy habitation,
019	PSA	091	010	No evil shall befall thee, Nor any plague come near thy dwelling.
019	PSA	091	011	For he will give his angels charge over thee, To guard thee in all thy ways.
019	PSA	091	012	They shall bear thee up in their hands, Lest thou dash thy foot against a stone.
019	PSA	091	013	Thou shalt tread upon the lion and the adder; The young lion and the dragon shalt thou trample under foot.
019	PSA	091	014	“Because he loveth me, I will deliver him; I will set him on high, because he knoweth my name.
019	PSA	091	015	When he calleth upon me, I will answer him; I will be with him in trouble; I will deliver him, and bring him to honor.
019	PSA	091	016	With long life will I satisfy him, And show him my salvation.”
019	PSA	092	001	“A psalm for the Sabbath-day.” It is a good thing to give thanks to the LORD, And to sing praises to thy name, O Most High!
019	PSA	092	002	To show forth thy loving-kindness in the morning, And thy faithfulness every night,
019	PSA	092	003	Upon the ten-stringed instrument and the lute, Upon the harp with a solemn sound.
019	PSA	092	004	For thou, LORD, hast made me glad by thy doings; In the works of thy hands I greatly rejoice!
019	PSA	092	005	How great are thy works, O LORD! How deep thy purposes!
019	PSA	092	006	But the unwise man knoweth not this, And the fool understandeth it not.
019	PSA	092	007	When the wicked spring up like grass, And all who practise iniquity flourish, It is but to be destroyed for ever!
019	PSA	092	008	Thou, O LORD! art for ever exalted!
019	PSA	092	009	For, lo! thine enemies, O LORD! For, lo! thine enemies perish, And dispersed are all who do iniquity!
019	PSA	092	010	But my horn thou exaltest like the buffalo's; I am anointed with fresh oil.
019	PSA	092	011	Mine eye hath gazed with joy upon mine enemies; Mine ears have heard with joy of my wicked adversaries.
019	PSA	092	012	The righteous shall flourish like the palm-tree; They shall grow up like the cedars of Lebanon;
019	PSA	092	013	Planted in the house of the LORD, They shall flourish in the courts of our God.
019	PSA	092	014	Even in old age they bring forth fruit; They are green, and full of sap;
019	PSA	092	015	To show that the LORD, my rock, is upright, That there is no unrighteousness in him.
019	PSA	093	001	Jehovah reigneth; he is clothed with majesty; Jehovah is clothed with majesty, and girded with strength; Therefore the earth standeth firm, and cannot be moved.
019	PSA	093	002	Thy throne was established of old; Thou art from everlasting!
019	PSA	093	003	The floods, O LORD! lift up, The floods lift up their voice; The floods lift up their roaring!
019	PSA	093	004	Mightier than the voice of many waters, Yea, than the mighty waves of the sea, Is the LORD in his lofty habitation.
019	PSA	093	005	Thy promises are most sure; Holiness becometh thy house, O LORD! for ever!
019	PSA	094	001	O LORD! thou God of vengeance! O thou God of vengeance! shine forth!
019	PSA	094	002	Rouse thyself, thou judge of the earth! Render a recompense to the proud!
019	PSA	094	003	How long, O LORD! shall the wicked, How long shall the wicked triumph?
019	PSA	094	004	How long shall their lips pour forth insolence? How long shall all the evil-doers boast?
019	PSA	094	005	O LORD! they trample upon thy people, And oppress thine inheritance!
019	PSA	094	006	They slay the widow, and the stranger, And murder the fatherless;
019	PSA	094	007	And they say, “The LORD doth not see, The God of Jacob doth not regard!”
019	PSA	094	008	Be instructed, ye most stupid of mankind! O when, ye fools, will ye be wise?
019	PSA	094	009	He that planted the ear, shall he not hear? He that formed the eye, shall he not see?
019	PSA	094	010	He that chastiseth nations, shall not he punish? He that teacheth man knowledge, shall not he know?
019	PSA	094	011	The LORD knoweth the thoughts of men, That they are vanity.
019	PSA	094	012	Happy the man, O LORD! whom thou correctest, Whom by thy teaching thou makest wise;
019	PSA	094	013	To give him peace in the days of adversity, Until a pit be digged for the wicked!
019	PSA	094	014	For the LORD will not forsake his people, Nor abandon his own inheritance.
019	PSA	094	015	For judgment shall return to justice, And all the upright in heart shall follow it.
019	PSA	094	016	Who will rise up for me against the wicked? Who will stand up for me against the evil-doers?
019	PSA	094	017	If the LORD had not been my help, I had well nigh dwelt in the land of silence.
019	PSA	094	018	When I think that my foot is slipping, Thy goodness, O LORD! holdeth me up.
019	PSA	094	019	In the multitude of anxieties within me, Thy consolations revive my soul.
019	PSA	094	020	Shall with thee be allied the throne of iniquity, Which deviseth mischief against law?
019	PSA	094	021	They band together against the life of the righteous, And condemn innocent blood.
019	PSA	094	022	But the LORD is my fortress, And my God the rock of my refuge.
019	PSA	094	023	He will bring upon them their own iniquity; Yea, through their own wickedness he will cut them off; Yea, the LORD, our God, will cut them off.
019	PSA	095	001	O come, let us sing to the LORD; Let us raise a voice of joy to the rock of our salvation!
019	PSA	095	002	Let us come into his presence with thanksgiving, And sing joyfully to him with psalms!
019	PSA	095	003	For Jehovah is a great God; Yea, a great king over all gods.
019	PSA	095	004	In his hands are the depths of the earth; His also are the heights of the mountains.
019	PSA	095	005	The sea is his, and he made it; The dry land also his hands formed.
019	PSA	095	006	O come, let us worship and bow down! Let us kneel before the LORD, our maker!
019	PSA	095	007	For he is our God, And we are the people of his pasture and the flock of his hand. O that ye would now hear his voice!
019	PSA	095	008	“Harden not your hearts as at Meribah [the strife], As in the day of temptation [Massah] in the wilderness,
019	PSA	095	009	Where your fathers tempted me And tried me, although they had seen my works.
019	PSA	095	010	Forty years was I offended with that generation: And I said, 'They are a people of a perverse heart, And who have no regard to my ways.'
019	PSA	095	011	Therefore I sware, in my wrath, That they should not enter into my rest.”
019	PSA	096	001	O sing to Jehovah a new song; Sing to Jehovah, all the earth!
019	PSA	096	002	Sing to Jehovah; praise his name, Show forth his salvation from day to day!
019	PSA	096	003	Proclaim his glory among the nations, His wonders among all people!
019	PSA	096	004	For Jehovah is great, and greatly to be praised; He is to be feared above all gods.
019	PSA	096	005	For all the gods of the nations are idols; But Jehovah made the heavens.
019	PSA	096	006	Honor and majesty are before him; Glory and beauty are in his holy abode.
019	PSA	096	007	Give to Jehovah, ye tribes of the people, Give to Jehovah glory and praise!
019	PSA	096	008	Give to Jehovah the glory due to his name; Bring an offering, and come into his courts!
019	PSA	096	009	O worship Jehovah in holy attire! Tremble before him, all the earth!
019	PSA	096	010	Say among the nations, Jehovah is king; The world shall stand firm; it shall not be moved; He will judge the nations in righteousness.
019	PSA	096	011	Let the heavens be glad, and the earth rejoice; Let the sea roar, and the fulness thereof;
019	PSA	096	012	Let the fields be joyful, with all that is therein; Let all the trees of the forest rejoice
019	PSA	096	013	Before Jehovah! for he cometh, He cometh to judge the earth! He will judge the world with justice, And the nations with faithfulness.
019	PSA	097	001	The LORD reigneth, let the earth rejoice! Let the multitude of isles be glad!
019	PSA	097	002	Clouds and darkness are round about him; Justice and equity are the foundation of his throne.
019	PSA	097	003	Before him goeth a fire, Which burneth up his enemies around.
019	PSA	097	004	His lightnings illumine the world; The earth beholdeth and trembleth.
