019	PSA	119	112	I have inclined my heart to perform thy statutes, Always, —even to the end.
019	PSA	119	113	I hate impious men, And thy law I do love.
019	PSA	119	114	Thou art my hiding-place and my shield; In thy word I put my trust!
019	PSA	119	115	Depart from me, ye evil-doers! For I will keep the commandments of my God.
019	PSA	119	116	Uphold me according to thy promise, that I may live; And let me not be ashamed of my hope!
019	PSA	119	117	Do thou hold me up, and I shall be safe, And I will have respect to thy statutes continually!
019	PSA	119	118	Thou castest off all who depart from thy laws; For their deceit is vain.
019	PSA	119	119	Thou throwest away all the wicked of the earth, like dross; Therefore I love thine ordinances.
019	PSA	119	120	My flesh trembleth through fear of thee, And I am afraid of thy judgments.
019	PSA	119	121	I have done justice and equity; O leave me not to mine oppressors.
019	PSA	119	122	Be surety for thy servant for good; Let not the proud oppress me!
019	PSA	119	123	Mine eyes fail with looking for thy help, And for thy righteous promise.
019	PSA	119	124	Deal with thy servant according to thy mercy, And teach me thy statutes!
019	PSA	119	125	I am thy servant; give me understanding, That I may know thine ordinances!
019	PSA	119	126	It is time for thee, O LORD! to act; For men have made void thy law.
019	PSA	119	127	Therefore I love thy commandments above gold; Yea, above fine gold.
019	PSA	119	128	Therefore I esteem all thy precepts concerning all things to be right; I hate every false way.
019	PSA	119	129	Wonderful are thine ordinances; Therefore do I observe them.
019	PSA	119	130	The communication of thy precepts giveth light; It giveth understanding to the simple.
019	PSA	119	131	I open my mouth and pant: For I long for thy commandments.
019	PSA	119	132	Look thou upon me, and be gracious to me, As is just to those who love thy name!
019	PSA	119	133	Establish my footsteps in thy word, And let no iniquity have dominion over me!
019	PSA	119	134	Redeem me from the oppression of men, So will I keep thy precepts!
019	PSA	119	135	Let thy face shine on thy servant, And teach me thy statutes!
019	PSA	119	136	Rivers of water run down mine eyes, Because men keep not thy law.
019	PSA	119	137	Righteous art thou, O LORD! And just are thy judgments!
019	PSA	119	138	Just are the ordinances which thou hast ordained, And altogether righteous.
019	PSA	119	139	My zeal consumeth me, Because my enemies forget thy word.
019	PSA	119	140	Thy word is very pure, Therefore thy servant loveth it.
019	PSA	119	141	Of mean condition am I, and despised; Yet do I not forget thy precepts.
019	PSA	119	142	Thy righteousness is everlasting righteousness, And thy law is truth.
019	PSA	119	143	Trouble and anguish have taken hold of me, But thy laws are my delight.
019	PSA	119	144	The justice of thine ordinances is everlasting; Give me understanding, and I shall live!
019	PSA	119	145	I cry to thee with my whole heart; Hear me, O LORD! that I may keep thy statutes.
019	PSA	119	146	I cry unto thee; save me, And I will observe thine ordinances.
019	PSA	119	147	I come before the dawn with my prayer; I trust in thy promise!
019	PSA	119	148	My eyes anticipate the night-watches, That I may meditate upon thy promise.
019	PSA	119	149	Hear my voice according to thy loving-kindness; O LORD! revive me according to thy mercy!
019	PSA	119	150	Near are they whose aim is mischief; They are far from thy law;
019	PSA	119	151	Yet thou art near, O LORD! And all thy commandments are truth!
019	PSA	119	152	Long have I known concerning thine ordinances, That thou hast founded them for ever.
019	PSA	119	153	Look upon my affliction, and deliver me! For I do not forget thy law.
019	PSA	119	154	Maintain my cause, and redeem me; Revive me according to thy promise!
019	PSA	119	155	Salvation is far from the wicked, Because they seek not thy statutes.
019	PSA	119	156	Great is thy compassion, O LORD! Revive thou me according to thine equity!
019	PSA	119	157	Many are my persecutors and my enemies, Yet do I not depart from thine ordinances.
019	PSA	119	158	I behold the transgressors, and am grieved Because they regard not thy word.
019	PSA	119	159	Behold, how I love thy precepts! O LORD! revive me according to thy loving-kindness!
019	PSA	119	160	The whole of thy word is truth, And all thy righteous judgments endure for ever.
019	PSA	119	161	Princes have persecuted me without cause; But my heart standeth in awe of thy word.
019	PSA	119	162	I rejoice in thy word, As one that hath found great spoil.
019	PSA	119	163	I hate and abhor lying, And thy law do I love.
019	PSA	119	164	Seven times a day do I praise thee On account of thy righteous judgments.
019	PSA	119	165	Great peace have they who love thy law, And no evil shall befall them.
019	PSA	119	166	O LORD! I wait for thy salvation, And keep thy commandments!
019	PSA	119	167	My soul observeth thine ordinances, And loveth them exceedingly.
019	PSA	119	168	I keep thy precepts and thine ordinances; For all my ways are before thee.
019	PSA	119	169	Let my prayer come near before thee, O LORD! According to thy promise, give me understanding!
019	PSA	119	170	Let my supplication come before thee; O deliver me according to thy promise!
019	PSA	119	171	My lips shall pour forth praise; For thou teachest me thy statutes.
019	PSA	119	172	My tongue shall sing of thy word; For all thy commandments are right.
019	PSA	119	173	Let thy hand be my help; For I have chosen thy precepts!
019	PSA	119	174	I long for thy salvation, O LORD! And thy law is my delight!
019	PSA	119	175	Let me live, and I will praise thee; Let thy judgments help me!
019	PSA	119	176	I wander like a lost sheep; seek thy servant, For I do not forget thy commandments!
019	PSA	120	001	“A psalm of steps.” In my distress I called upon the LORD, And he answered me.
019	PSA	120	002	O LORD! deliver me from lying lips, From the deceitful tongue!
019	PSA	120	003	What profit to thee, Or what advantage to thee, is the false tongue?
019	PSA	120	004	It is like the sharp arrows of the mighty man; Like coals of the juniper.
019	PSA	120	005	Alas for me, that I sojourn in Mesech, That I dwell in the tents of Kedar!
019	PSA	120	006	Too long have I dwelt With them that hate peace!
019	PSA	120	007	I am for peace; yet, when I speak for it, They are for war.
019	PSA	121	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up.” I lift up mine eyes to the hills: Whence cometh my help?
019	PSA	121	002	My help cometh from the LORD, Who made heaven and earth.
019	PSA	121	003	He will not suffer thy foot to stumble; Thy guardian doth not slumber.
019	PSA	121	004	Behold, the guardian of Israel Doth neither slumber nor sleep.
019	PSA	121	005	The LORD is thy guardian; The LORD is thy shade at thy right hand.
019	PSA	121	006	The sun shall not smite thee by day, Nor the moon by night.
019	PSA	121	007	The LORD will preserve thee from all evil; He will preserve thy life.
019	PSA	121	008	The LORD will preserve thee, when thou goest out and when thou comest in, From this time forth for ever.
019	PSA	122	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up. By David.” I was glad when they said to me, Let us go up to the house of the LORD!
019	PSA	122	002	Our feet are standing Within thy gates, O Jerusalem!
019	PSA	122	003	Jerusalem, the rebuilt city! The city that is joined together!
019	PSA	122	004	Thither the tribes go up, The tribes of the LORD, according to the law of Israel, To praise the name of the LORD.
019	PSA	122	005	There stand the thrones of judgment, The thrones of the house of David.
019	PSA	122	006	Pray for the peace of Jerusalem! May they prosper who love thee!
019	PSA	122	007	Peace be within thy walls, And prosperity within thy palaces!
019	PSA	122	008	For my brethren and companions' sake will I say, Peace be within thee!
019	PSA	122	009	For the sake of the house of the LORD, our God, Will I seek thy good!
019	PSA	123	001	“A song of the steps, or the goings up.” To thee do I lift up mine eyes, O Thou who dwellest in the heavens!
019	PSA	123	002	Behold, as the eyes of servants look to the hand of their masters, And as the eyes of a maiden to the hand of her mistress, So do our eyes look to the LORD, our God, Until he have pity upon us.
019	PSA	123	003	Have mercy upon us, O LORD! have mercy upon us, For we are overwhelmed with contempt!
019	PSA	123	004	Our soul is filled to the full with the scorn of those who are at ease, And with the contempt of the proud.
019	PSA	124	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up. By David.” If the LORD had not been for us, Now may Israel say,
019	PSA	124	002	If the LORD had not been for us, When men rose up against us,
019	PSA	124	003	Then had they swallowed us up alive, When their wrath burned against us;
019	PSA	124	004	Then the waters had overwhelmed us; The stream had gone over our soul;
019	PSA	124	005	The proud waters had gone over our soul.
019	PSA	124	006	Blessed be the LORD, Who hath not given us a prey to their teeth!
019	PSA	124	007	We have escaped like a bird from the snare of the fowler; The snare is broken, and we have escaped.
019	PSA	124	008	Our help is in the name of the LORD, Who made heaven and earth.
019	PSA	125	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up.” They who trust in the LORD shall be as Mount Zion, Which cannot be moved, which standeth for ever.
019	PSA	125	002	As the mountains are round about Jerusalem, So the LORD is round about his people, Henceforth even for ever!
019	PSA	125	003	For the sceptre of the wicked shall not remain upon the portion of the righteous, Lest the righteous put forth their hands to iniquity.
019	PSA	125	004	Do good, O LORD! to the good, To them that are upright in heart!
019	PSA	125	005	But such as turn aside to their crooked ways, -May the LORD destroy them with the evil-doers! Peace be to Israel!
019	PSA	126	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up.” When the LORD brought back the captivity of Zion, We were like them that dream.
019	PSA	126	002	Then was our mouth filled with laughter, And our tongue with singing. Then said they among the nations, “The LORD hath done great things for them!”
019	PSA	126	003	Yea, the LORD hath done great things for us, For which we are glad.
019	PSA	126	004	Bring back, O LORD! our captivity, Like streams in the South!
019	PSA	126	005	They who sow in tears Shall reap in joy.
019	PSA	126	006	Yea, he goeth forth weeping, bearing his seed; He shall surely come back rejoicing, bearing his sheaves.
019	PSA	127	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up. By Solomon.” Except the LORD build the house, The builders labor in vain; Except the LORD guard the city, The watchman waketh in vain.
019	PSA	127	002	In vain ye rise up early, and go to rest late, And eat the bread of care! The same giveth he his beloved one in sleep.
019	PSA	127	003	Behold! sons are an inheritance from the LORD, And the fruit of the womb is his gift.
019	PSA	127	004	As arrows in the hand of the warrior, So are the sons of young men:
019	PSA	127	005	Happy the man that hath his quiver full of them! They shall not be put to shame, When they speak with adversaries in the gate.
019	PSA	128	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up.” Happy is he who feareth the LORD, Who walketh in his ways!
019	PSA	128	002	Thou shalt eat the labor of thy hands; Happy shalt thou be, and it shall be well with thee!
019	PSA	128	003	Thy wife shall be like a fruitful vine within thy house; Thy children like olive-branches round about thy table.
019	PSA	128	004	Behold! thus happy is the man who feareth the LORD!
019	PSA	128	005	Jehovah shall bless thee out of Zion, And thou shalt see the prosperity of Jerusalem all the days of thy life;
019	PSA	128	006	Yea, thou shalt see thy children's children. Peace be to Israel!
019	PSA	129	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up.” Much have they afflicted me from my youth, May Israel now say;
019	PSA	129	002	Much have they afflicted me from my youth, Yet have they not prevailed against me.
019	PSA	129	003	The ploughers ploughed up my back; They made long their furrows;
019	PSA	129	004	But the LORD was righteous; He cut asunder the cords of the wicked.
019	PSA	129	005	Let all be driven back with shame Who hate Zion!
019	PSA	129	006	Let them be as grass upon the house-tops, Which withereth before one pulleth it up;
019	PSA	129	007	With which the reaper filleth not his hand, Nor he that bindeth sheaves his bosom!
019	PSA	129	008	And they who pass by do not say, “The blessing of the LORD be upon you! We bless you in the name of the LORD!”
019	PSA	130	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up.” Out of the depths do I cry to thee, O LORD!
019	PSA	130	002	O Lord! listen to my voice, Let thine ears be attentive to my supplication!
019	PSA	130	003	If thou, LORD, shouldst treasure up transgressions, Lord, who could stand?
019	PSA	130	004	But with thee is forgiveness, That thou mayst be feared.
019	PSA	130	005	I trust in the LORD; my soul doth trust, And in his promise do I confide.
019	PSA	130	006	My soul waiteth for the LORD More than they who watch for the morning; Yea, more than they who watch for the morning!
019	PSA	130	007	O Israel! trust in the LORD! For with the LORD is mercy, And with him is plenteous redemption.
019	PSA	130	008	He will redeem Israel From all his iniquities.
019	PSA	131	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up. Of David.” O LORD! my heart is not haughty, nor my eyes lofty; I employ not myself on great things, or things too wonderful for me!
019	PSA	131	002	Yea, I have stilled and quieted my soul As a weaned child upon his mother; My soul within me is like a weaned child.
019	PSA	131	003	O Israel! trust in the LORD, Henceforth even for ever!
019	PSA	132	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up.” O LORD! remember David, And all his affliction!
019	PSA	132	002	How he sware to Jehovah, And vowed to the Mighty One of Jacob:
019	PSA	132	003	“I will not go into my house, Nor lie down on my bed,
019	PSA	132	004	I will not give sleep to my eyes, Nor slumber to my eyelids,
019	PSA	132	005	Until I find a place for Jehovah, A habitation for the Mighty One of Jacob.”
019	PSA	132	006	Behold, we heard of it at Ephratah; We found it in the fields of the forest.
019	PSA	132	007	Let us go into his habitation; Let us worship at his footstool!
019	PSA	132	008	Arise, O LORD! into thy rest, Thou, and the ark of thy strength!
019	PSA	132	009	Let thy priests be clothed with righteousness, And thy holy ones shout for joy!
019	PSA	132	010	For the sake of thy servant David, Reject not the prayer of thine anointed!
019	PSA	132	011	Jehovah hath sworn in truth unto David, And he will not depart from it: “Of the fruit of thy body will I place upon the throne for thee.
019	PSA	132	012	If thy children keep my covenant, And my statutes, which I teach them, Their children also throughout all ages Shall sit upon thy throne.”
019	PSA	132	013	For Jehovah hath chosen Zion; He hath desired it as his dwelling-place.
019	PSA	132	014	“This is my resting-place for ever; Here will I dwell, for I have chosen it.
019	PSA	132	015	I will abundantly bless her provision; I will satisfy her poor with bread.
019	PSA	132	016	I will also clothe her priests with salvation, And her holy ones shall shout aloud for joy.
019	PSA	132	017	There will I cause to spring forth a horn for David; I have prepared a light for mine anointed.
019	PSA	132	018	His enemies will I clothe with shame, And the crown shall glitter upon his head.”
019	PSA	133	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up. By David.” Behold, how good and pleasant it is For brethren to dwell together in unity!
019	PSA	133	002	It is like precious perfume upon the head, Which ran down upon the beard, The beard of Aaron; Which went down to the very border of his garments;
019	PSA	133	003	Like the dew of Hermon, Like that which descendeth upon the mountains of Zion. For there the LORD commandeth a blessing, Even life for evermore.
019	PSA	134	001	“A psalm of the steps, or the goings up.” Praise the LORD, all ye servants of the LORD, Who stand in the house of the LORD by night!
019	PSA	134	002	Lift up your hands to the sanctuary, And praise the LORD!
019	PSA	134	003	May the LORD, who made heaven and earth, Bless thee out of Zion!
019	PSA	135	001	Praise ye the LORD! Praise ye the name of the LORD! Praise him, O ye servants of the LORD!
019	PSA	135	002	Ye who stand in the house of the LORD, In the courts of the house of our God!
019	PSA	135	003	Praise ye the LORD, for the LORD is good; Praise his name, for he is kind!
019	PSA	135	004	For the LORD chose Jacob for himself, And Israel for his own possession.
019	PSA	135	005	I know that the LORD is great; That our Lord is above all gods.
019	PSA	135	006	All that the LORD pleaseth, that he doeth, In heaven and upon earth, In the sea, and in all deeps.
019	PSA	135	007	He causeth the clouds to ascend from the ends of the earth; He maketh lightnings for the rain; He bringeth the wind from his store-houses.
019	PSA	135	008	He smote the first-born of Egypt, Both of man and beast.
019	PSA	135	009	He sent signs and wonders into the midst of thee, O Egypt! Against Pharaoh and all his servants!
019	PSA	135	010	He smote many nations, And slew mighty kings;
019	PSA	135	011	Sihon, the king of the Amorites, And Og, the king of Bashan, And all the kings of Canaan;
019	PSA	135	012	And gave their land for an inheritance, For an inheritance to Israel, his people.
019	PSA	135	013	Thy name, O LORD! endureth for ever; Thy memorial, O LORD! to all generations!
019	PSA	135	014	For the LORD judgeth his people, And hath compassion on his servants.
019	PSA	135	015	The idols of the nations are silver and gold, The work of men's hands.
019	PSA	135	016	They have mouths, but they speak not; Eyes have they, but they see not.
019	PSA	135	017	They have ears, but they hear not; And there is no breath in their mouths.
019	PSA	135	018	They that make them are like them; So is every one that trusteth in them.
019	PSA	135	019	Praise the LORD, O house of Israel! Praise the LORD, O house of Aaron!
019	PSA	135	020	Praise the LORD, O house of Levi! Ye that fear the LORD, bless the LORD!
019	PSA	135	021	Praised be the LORD out of Zion, He that dwelleth in Jerusalem! Praise ye the LORD!
019	PSA	136	001	O give thanks to the LORD! for he is kind; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	002	O give thanks to the God of gods; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	003	O give thanks to the Lord of lords; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	004	To him that alone doeth great wonders; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	005	To him that made the heavens with wisdom; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	006	To him that spread out the earth upon the waters; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	007	To him that made the great lights; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	008	The sun to rule the day; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	009	The moon and stars to rule the night; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	010	To him that smote in Egypt their first-born; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	011	And brought Israel from the midst of them; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	012	With a strong hand and an outstretched arm; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	013	To him who divided the Red sea into parts; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	014	And made Israel to pass through the midst of it; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	015	And overthrew Pharaoh and his host in the Red sea; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	016	To him who led his people through the wilderness; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	017	To him who smote great kings; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	018	And slew mighty kings; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	019	Sihon, the king of the Amorites; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	020	And Og, the king of Bashan; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	021	And gave their land for an inheritance; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	022	For an inheritance to Israel his servant; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	023	Who remembered us in our low estate; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	024	And redeemed us from our enemies; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	025	Who giveth food unto all; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	136	026	O give thanks to the God of heaven; For his goodness endureth for ever!
019	PSA	137	001	By the rivers of Babylon, there we sat down, yea, we wept, When we remembered Zion.
019	PSA	137	002	We hung our harps on the willows in the midst thereof.
019	PSA	137	003	For there they who carried us away captive required of us a song; They who wasted us required of us mirth: “Sing us one of the songs of Zion!”
019	PSA	137	004	How shall we sing the LORD'S song In a strange land?
019	PSA	137	005	If I forget thee, O Jerusalem, Let my right hand forget her cunning!
019	PSA	137	006	If I do not remember thee, Let my tongue cleave to the roof of my mouth; If I prefer not Jerusalem above my chief joy!
019	PSA	137	007	Remember, O LORD! against the children of Edom The day of the calamity of Jerusalem! Who said, “Raze it, Raze it to its foundations!”
019	PSA	137	008	O daughter of Babylon, thou destroyer! Happy be he who requiteth thee As thou hast dealt with us!
019	PSA	137	009	Happy be he who seizeth thy little ones And dasheth them against the stones!
019	PSA	138	001	“A psalm of David.” I will praise thee with my whole heart; Before the gods will I sing praise to thee;
019	PSA	138	002	I will worship toward thy holy temple, And praise thy name for thy goodness and thy truth; For thy promise thou hast magnified above all thy name!
019	PSA	138	003	In the day when I called, thou didst hear me; Thou didst strengthen me, and encourage my soul.
019	PSA	138	004	All the kings of the earth shall praise thee, O LORD! When they hear the promises of thy mouth!
019	PSA	138	005	Yea, they shall sing of the ways of the LORD; For great is the glory of the LORD.
019	PSA	138	006	The LORD is high, yet he looketh upon the humble, And the proud doth he know from afar.
019	PSA	138	007	Though I walk through the midst of trouble, thou wilt revive me; Thou wilt stretch forth thy hand against the wrath of my enemies; Thou wilt save me by thy right hand!
019	PSA	138	008	The LORD will perform all things for me; Thy goodness, O LORD! endureth ever: Forsake not the works of thine hands!
019	PSA	139	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” O LORD! thou hast searched me and known me!
019	PSA	139	002	Thou knowest my sitting-down and my rising-up; Thou understandest my thoughts from afar!
019	PSA	139	003	Thou seest my path and my lying-down, And art acquainted with all my ways!
019	PSA	139	004	For before the word is upon my tongue, Behold, O LORD! thou knowest it altogether!
019	PSA	139	005	Thou besettest me behind and before, And layest thine hand upon me!
019	PSA	139	006	Such knowledge is too wonderful for me; It is high, I cannot attain to it!
019	PSA	139	007	Whither shall I go from thy spirit, And whither shall I flee from thy presence?
019	PSA	139	008	If I ascend into heaven, thou art there! If I make my bed in the underworld, behold, thou art there!
019	PSA	139	009	If I take the wings of the morning, And dwell in the remotest parts of the sea,
019	PSA	139	010	Even there shall thy hand lead me, And thy right hand shall hold me!
019	PSA	139	011	If I say, “Surely the darkness shall cover me;” Even the night shall be light about me.
019	PSA	139	012	Yea, the darkness hideth not from thee, But the night shineth as the day; The darkness and the light are both alike to thee!
019	PSA	139	013	For thou didst form my reins; Thou didst weave me in my mother's womb.
019	PSA	139	014	I will praise thee; for I am fearfully and wonderfully made; Marvellous are thy works, And this my soul knoweth full well!
019	PSA	139	015	My frame was not hidden from thee, When I was made in secret. When I was curiously wrought in the lower parts of the earth.
019	PSA	139	016	Thine eyes did see my substance, while yet unformed, And in thy book was every thing written; My days were appointed before one of them existed.
019	PSA	139	017	How precious to me are thy thoughts, O God! How great is the sum of them!
019	PSA	139	018	If I should count them, they would outnumber the sand: When I awake, I am still with thee!
019	PSA	139	019	O that thou wouldst slay the wicked, O God! Ye men of blood, depart from me!
019	PSA	139	020	For they speak against thee wickedly; Thine enemies utter thy name for falsehood.
019	PSA	139	021	Do I not hate them that hate thee, O LORD? Do I not abhor them that rise up against thee?
019	PSA	139	022	Yea, I hate them with perfect hatred; I count them mine enemies.
019	PSA	139	023	Search me, O God! and know my heart; Try me, and know my thoughts;
019	PSA	139	024	And see if the way of trouble be within me, And lead me in the way everlasting!
019	PSA	140	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” Deliver me, O LORD! from the evil man, Save me from the man of violence,
019	PSA	140	002	Who meditate mischief in their heart, And daily stir up war!
019	PSA	140	003	They sharpen their tongues like a serpent; The poison of the adder is under their lips. (Pause)
019	PSA	140	004	Defend me, O LORD! from the hands of the wicked, Preserve me from the man of violence, Who have purposed to cause my fall! (Pause)
019	PSA	140	005	The proud have hidden snares and cords for me; They have spread a net by the way-side; They have set traps for me.
019	PSA	140	006	I say to Jehovah, Thou art my God; Hear, O Jehovah! the voice of my supplication!
019	PSA	140	007	The Lord Jehovah is my saving strength: Thou shelterest my head in the day of battle!
019	PSA	140	008	Grant not, O LORD! the desires of the wicked; Let not their devices prosper; Let them not exalt themselves!
019	PSA	140	009	As for the heads of those who encompass me, Let the mischief of their own lips cover them!
019	PSA	140	010	Let burning coals fall upon them; May they be cast into the fire, And into deep waters from which they shall not arise!
019	PSA	140	011	The slanderer shall not be established upon the earth; Evil shall pursue the violent man to destruction.
019	PSA	140	012	I know that the LORD will maintain the cause of the afflicted, And the right of the poor.
019	PSA	140	013	Yea, the righteous shall praise thy name; The upright shall dwell in thy presence!
019	PSA	141	001	“For the leader of the music. A psalm of David.” I cry to thee, O LORD! make haste unto me! Give ear to my voice, when I cry unto thee!
019	PSA	141	002	Let my prayer come before thee as incense, And the lifting-up of my hands, as the evening sacrifice!
019	PSA	141	003	Set a watch, O LORD! before my mouth; Guard the door of my lips!
019	PSA	141	004	Let not my heart incline to any evil thing; Let me not practise wickedness with the doers of iniquity, And let me not eat of their delicacies!
019	PSA	141	005	Let the righteous smite me, —it shall be a kindness; Let him reprove me, and it shall be oil for my head; Let him do it again, and my head shall not refuse it; But now I pray against their wickedness!
019	PSA	141	006	When their judges are hurled over the side of the rock, They shall hear how pleasant are my words.
019	PSA	141	007	So are our bones scattered at the mouth of the underworld, As when one furroweth and ploweth up the land.
019	PSA	141	008	But to thee do my eyes look, O Lord Jehovah! In thee is my trust; Let not my life be poured out!
019	PSA	141	009	Preserve me from the snares which they have laid for me, And from the nets of evil-doers!
019	PSA	141	010	Let the wicked fall together into their own traps, Whilst I make my escape!
019	PSA	142	001	“A psalm of David; a prayer, when he was in the cave” I cry unto the LORD with my voice; With my voice to the LORD do I make my supplication.
019	PSA	142	002	I pour out my complaint before him; I declare before him my distress.
019	PSA	142	003	When my spirit is overwhelmed within me, Thou knowest my path! In the way which I walk, they have hid a snare for me.
019	PSA	142	004	I look on my right hand, and behold, But no man knoweth me; Refuge faileth me; No one careth for me.
019	PSA	142	005	I cry unto thee, O LORD! I say, Thou art my refuge, My portion in the land of the living.
019	PSA	142	006	Attend to my cry, for I am brought very low; Deliver me from my persecutors, For they prevail against me!
019	PSA	142	007	Bring me out of prison, That I may praise thy name! The righteous shall gather around me, When thou shalt show me thy favor.
019	PSA	143	001	“A psalm of David.” Hear my prayer, O LORD! give ear to my supplications! In thy faithfulness, and in thy righteousness, answer me!
019	PSA	143	002	Enter not into judgment with thy servant; For before thee no man living is righteous.
019	PSA	143	003	For the enemy pursueth my life; He hath smitten me to the ground; He hath made me dwell in darkness, As those that have been dead of old.
019	PSA	143	004	My spirit is overwhelmed within me; My heart within me is desolate.
019	PSA	143	005	I remember the days of old; I meditate on all thy works; I muse on the deeds of thy hands.
019	PSA	143	006	I stretch forth my hands unto thee; My soul thirsteth for thee, like a parched land.
019	PSA	143	007	Hear me speedily, O LORD! My spirit faileth; Hide not thy face from me. Lest I become like those who go down to the pit!
019	PSA	143	008	Cause me so see thy loving-kindness speedily; For in thee do I trust! Make known to me the way which I should take; For to thee do I lift up my soul!
019	PSA	143	009	Deliver me, O LORD! from mine enemies; For in thee do I seek refuge!
019	PSA	143	010	Teach me to do thy will; For thou art my God! Let thy good spirit lead me in a plain path!
019	PSA	143	011	Revive me, O LORD! for thy name's sake! In thy righteousness, bring me out of my distress!
019	PSA	143	012	And, in thy compassion, cut off mine enemies, And destroy all that distress me! For I am thy servant.
019	PSA	144	001	Blessed be the LORD, my rock, Who teacheth my hands to war, And my fingers to fight!
019	PSA	144	002	He who is my loving-kindness and my fortress; My high tower and my deliverer, My shield, and he in whom I trust; Who subdueth peoples under me.
019	PSA	144	003	LORD, what is man, that thou art mindful of him, Or the son of man, that thou makest account of him?
019	PSA	144	004	Man is like a vapor; His day is like a shadow that passeth away.
019	PSA	144	005	Bow thy heavens, O LORD! and come down; Touch the mountains, so that they shall smoke!
019	PSA	144	006	Cast forth lightnings, and scatter them; Shoot forth thine arrows, and destroy them!
019	PSA	144	007	Send forth thine hand from above; Rescue and save me from deep waters; From the hands of aliens,
019	PSA	144	008	Whose mouth uttereth deceit, And whose right hand is a right hand of falsehood!
019	PSA	144	009	I will sing to thee a new song, O God! Upon a ten-stringed psaltery will I sing praise to thee;
019	PSA	144	010	To thee, who givest salvation to kings, Who deliverest David, thy servant, from the destructive sword!
019	PSA	144	011	Rescue and deliver me from the hands of aliens, Whose mouth uttereth deceit, And whose right hand is a right hand of falsehood!
019	PSA	144	012	That our sons may be as plants, Grown up in their youth; Our daughters as corner-pillars, Hewn like those of a palace!
019	PSA	144	013	That our garners may be full, Affording all kinds of store; That our sheep may bring forth thousands And ten thousands in our streets.
019	PSA	144	014	That our cattle may be fruitful; That there be no breaking in, or going out; And no outcry in our streets.
019	PSA	144	015	Happy the people that is in such a state! Yea, happy the people whose God is Jehovah!
019	PSA	145	001	“A song of praise. By David.” I will extol thee, my God, the King! I will praise thy name for ever and ever!
019	PSA	145	002	Every day will I bless thee, And praise thy name for ever and ever!
019	PSA	145	003	Great is the LORD, and greatly to be praised; Yea, his greatness is unsearchable.
019	PSA	145	004	One generation shall praise thy works to another, And shall declare thy mighty deeds.
019	PSA	145	005	I will speak of the glorious honor of thy majesty, And of thy wonderful works.
019	PSA	145	006	Men shall speak of the might of thy terrible deeds, And I will declare thy greatness;
019	PSA	145	007	They shall pour forth the praise of thy great good And sing of thy righteousness.
019	PSA	145	008	The LORD is gracious, and full of compassion, Slow to anger, and rich in mercy.
019	PSA	145	009	The LORD is good to all. And his tender mercies are over all his works.
019	PSA	145	010	All thy works praise thee, O LORD! And thy holy ones bless thee!
019	PSA	145	011	They speak of the glory of thy kingdom, And talk of thy power;
019	PSA	145	012	To make known to the sons of men his mighty deeds, And the glorious majesty of his kingdom.
019	PSA	145	013	Thy kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, And thy dominion endureth throughout all generations.
019	PSA	145	014	The LORD upholdeth all that fall, And raiseth up all that are bowed down.
019	PSA	145	015	The eyes of all wait upon thee, And thou givest them their food in due season;
019	PSA	145	016	Thou openest thine hand, And satisfiest the desire of every living thing.
019	PSA	145	017	The LORD is righteous in all his ways, And merciful in all his works.
019	PSA	145	018	The LORD is nigh to all that call upon him, To all that call upon him in truth.
019	PSA	145	019	He fulfilleth the desire of them that fear him; He heareth their cry, and saveth them.
019	PSA	145	020	The LORD preserveth all that love him; But all the wicked he will destroy.
019	PSA	145	021	My mouth shall speak the praise of the LORD; And let all flesh bless his holy name for ever and ever!
019	PSA	146	001	Praise ye the LORD! Praise the LORD, O my soul!
019	PSA	146	002	I will praise the LORD, as long as I live; I will sing praises to my God, while I have my being.
019	PSA	146	003	Put not your trust in princes, In the son of man, in whom is no help!
019	PSA	146	004	His breath goeth forth; he returneth to the dust; In that very day his plans perish.
019	PSA	146	005	Happy is he that hath the God of Jacob for his help; Whose hope is in the LORD, his God;
019	PSA	146	006	Who made heaven and earth, The sea, and all that is therein; Who keepeth truth for ever;
019	PSA	146	007	Who executeth judgment for the oppressed; Who giveth food to the hungry. The LORD setteth free the prisoners;
019	PSA	146	008	The LORD openeth the eyes of the blind; The LORD raiseth up them that are bowed down; The LORD loveth the righteous.
019	PSA	146	009	The LORD preserveth the strangers; He relieveth the fatherless and the widow; But the way of the wicked he maketh crooked.
019	PSA	146	010	The LORD shall reign for ever; Thy God, O Zion! to all generations! Praise ye the LORD!
019	PSA	147	001	Praise ye the LORD! For it is good to sing praise to our God; For it is pleasant, and praise is becoming.
019	PSA	147	002	The LORD buildeth up Jerusalem; He gathereth together the dispersed of Israel.
019	PSA	147	003	He healeth the broken in heart, And bindeth up their wounds.
019	PSA	147	004	He counteth the number of the stars; He calleth them all by their names.
019	PSA	147	005	Great is our Lord, and mighty in power; His understanding is infinite.
019	PSA	147	006	The LORD lifteth up the lowly; He casteth the wicked down to the ground.
019	PSA	147	007	Sing to the LORD with thanksgiving; Sing praises upon the harp to our God!
019	PSA	147	008	Who covereth the heavens with clouds, Who prepareth rain for the earth, Who causeth grass to grow upon the mountains.
019	PSA	147	009	He giveth to the cattle their food. And to the young ravens, when they cry.
019	PSA	147	010	He delighteth not in the strength of the horse, He taketh not pleasure in the legs of a man.
019	PSA	147	011	The LORD taketh pleasure in those who fear him, In those who trust in his mercy.
019	PSA	147	012	Praise the LORD. O Jerusalem! Praise thy God, O Zion!
019	PSA	147	013	For he hath strengthened the bars of thy gates; He hath blessed thy children within thee.
019	PSA	147	014	He maketh peace in thy borders, And satisfieth thee with the finest of the wheat.
019	PSA	147	015	He sendeth forth his command to the earth; His word runneth very swiftly.
019	PSA	147	016	He giveth snow like wool, And scattereth the hoar-frost like ashes.
019	PSA	147	017	He casteth forth his ice like morsels; Who can stand before his cold?
019	PSA	147	018	He sendeth forth his word, and melteth them; He causeth his wind to blow, and the waters flow.
019	PSA	147	019	He publisheth his word to Jacob, His statutes and laws to Israel.
019	PSA	147	020	He hath dealt in this manner with no other nation; And, as for his ordinances, they have not known them. Praise ye the LORD!
019	PSA	148	001	Praise ye the LORD! Praise the LORD from the heavens! Praise him in the heights!
019	PSA	148	002	Praise him, all ye his angels! Praise him, all ye his hosts!
019	PSA	148	003	Praise ye him, sun and moon! Praise him, all ye stars of light!
019	PSA	148	004	Praise him, ye heavens of heavens! Ye waters, that are above the heavens!
019	PSA	148	005	Let them praise the name of the LORD; For he commanded, and they were created.
019	PSA	148	006	He hath also established them for ever; He hath given them a law, and they transgress it not.
019	PSA	148	007	Praise the LORD from the earth, Ye sea-monsters, and all deeps!
019	PSA	148	008	Fire and hail, snow and vapor; Thou tempest, that fulfillest his word!
019	PSA	148	009	Ye mountains, and all hills! Fruit-trees, and all cedars!
019	PSA	148	010	Ye wild beasts, and all cattle! Ye creeping things, and winged birds!
019	PSA	148	011	Ye kings, and all peoples, Princes, and all judges of the earth!
019	PSA	148	012	Young men and maidens, Old men and children!
019	PSA	148	013	Let them praise the name of the LORD! For his name alone is exalted; His glory is above the earth and the heavens.
019	PSA	148	014	He exalteth the horn of his people, The glory of all his godly ones, Of the children of Israel, a people near to him. Praise ye the LORD!
019	PSA	149	001	Praise ye the LORD! Sing unto the LORD a new song; His praise in the assembly of the godly!
019	PSA	149	002	Let Israel rejoice in him that made him; Let the sons of Zion be joyful in their king!
019	PSA	149	003	Let them praise his name in the dance; Let them praise him with the timbrel and harp!
019	PSA	149	004	For the LORD taketh pleasure in his people; He will beautify the distressed with salvation.
019	PSA	149	005	Let the godly-rejoice in their glory; Let them shout for joy upon their beds!
019	PSA	149	006	Let the praises of God be in their mouth, And a two-edged sword in their hand,
019	PSA	149	007	To execute vengeance upon the nations, And punishment upon the peoples!
019	PSA	149	008	To bind their kings with chains. And their nobles with fetters of iron;
019	PSA	149	009	To execute upon them the sentence which is written: This honor have all his godly ones. Praise ye the LORD!
019	PSA	150	001	Praise ye the LORD! Praise God in his sanctuary! Praise him in his glorious firmament!
019	PSA	150	002	Praise him for his mighty deeds! Praise him according to his excellent greatness!
019	PSA	150	003	Praise him with the sound of trumpets! Praise him with the psaltery and harp!
019	PSA	150	004	Praise him with the timbrel and dance! Praise him with stringed instruments and pipes!
019	PSA	150	005	Praise him with the clear-sounding cymbals! Praise him with the high-sounding cymbals!
019	PSA	150	006	Let every thing that hath breath praise the LORD! Praise ye the LORD!
