# BOOK	020	PRO	Proverbs	Proverbs
020	PRO	001	001	The proverbs of Solomon, the son of David, king of Israel:
020	PRO	001	002	That one may learn wisdom and instruction, And receive words of understanding;
020	PRO	001	003	That one may gain the instruction of prudence, Justice, equity, and uprightness;
020	PRO	001	004	Which will give caution to the simple, To the young man wisdom and discretion;
020	PRO	001	005	Let the wise man hear, and he will increase his knowledge, And the man of understanding will gain wise counsels;
020	PRO	001	006	So as to understand a proverb and a deep maxim, The words of the wise and their dark sayings.
020	PRO	001	007	The fear of the LORD is the beginning of knowledge; Fools despise wisdom and instruction.
020	PRO	001	008	Hear, O my son! the instruction of thy father, And neglect not the teaching of thy mother!
020	PRO	001	009	For they shall be a graceful wreath for thy head, And a chain around thy neck.
020	PRO	001	010	My son, if sinners entice thee, Consent thou not!
020	PRO	001	011	If they say, “Come with us, Let us lie in wait for blood, Let us lurk secretly for him who is innocent in vain;
020	PRO	001	012	Let us swallow them up alive, like the underworld, Yea, in full health, as those that go down into the pit;
020	PRO	001	013	We shall find all kinds of precious substance, We shall fill our houses with spoil;
020	PRO	001	014	Thou shalt cast thy lot among us; We will all have one purse;”—
020	PRO	001	015	My son, walk thou not in their way, Refrain thy foot from their path!
020	PRO	001	016	For their feet run to evil, And make haste to shed blood.
020	PRO	001	017	For as the net is spread in vain Before the eyes of any bird,
020	PRO	001	018	So they lie in wait for their own blood; They lurk secretly for their own lives.
020	PRO	001	019	Such are the ways of every one greedy of unjust gain; It taketh away the life of the possessor thereof.
020	PRO	001	020	Wisdom crieth out in the highway; In the market-place she uttereth her voice;
020	PRO	001	021	At the head of the noisy streets she crieth aloud; At the entrances of the gates, throughout the city, she proclaimeth her words [saying]:
020	PRO	001	022	How long, ye simple ones, will ye love simplicity? How long will scoffers delight themselves in scoffing, And fools hate knowledge?
020	PRO	001	023	Turn ye at my reproof! Behold, I will pour out my spirit to you; I will make known my words to you!
020	PRO	001	024	“Because I have called, and ye have refused, —Because I have stretched out my hand, and no one hath regarded.
020	PRO	001	025	Because ye have rejected all my counsel, And have slighted my rebuke, —
020	PRO	001	026	I also will laugh at your calamity, I will mock when your fear cometh;
020	PRO	001	027	When your fear cometh upon you like a storm. And destruction overtaketh you like a whirlwind, When distress and anguish come upon you.
020	PRO	001	028	Then will they call upon me, but I will not answer! They will seek me early, But they shall not find me!
020	PRO	001	029	Because they have hated knowledge, And have not chosen the fear of the LORD, —
020	PRO	001	030	Because they would not attend to my counsel, And have despised all my reproof, —
020	PRO	001	031	Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, And be filled to the full with their own devices;
020	PRO	001	032	Yea, the turning away of the simple shall slay them, And the carelessness of fools shall destroy them.
020	PRO	001	033	But whoso hearkeneth to me shall dwell securely, And shall not be disquieted with the fear of evil.”
020	PRO	002	001	Oh, my son, that thou wouldst receive my words, And treasure up my precepts within thee;
020	PRO	002	002	That thou wouldst apply thine ear to wisdom, And incline thy heart to understanding!
020	PRO	002	003	For if thou wilt call aloud to knowledge, And lift up thy voice to understanding, —
020	PRO	002	004	If thou wilt seek her as silver, And search for her as for hidden treasures,
020	PRO	002	005	Then shalt thou understand the fear of the LORD, And find the knowledge of God.
020	PRO	002	006	For the LORD giveth wisdom; From his mouth proceed knowledge and understanding:
020	PRO	002	007	He layeth up safety for the righteous; He is a shield to them that walk uprightly:
020	PRO	002	008	He guardeth the paths of equity, And defendeth the way of his servants.
020	PRO	002	009	Then shalt thou understand righteousness and equity And uprightness, yea, every good path.
020	PRO	002	010	When wisdom entereth into thy heart, And knowledge is pleasant to thy soul,
020	PRO	002	011	Discretion will guard thee, Understanding will preserve thee.
020	PRO	002	012	It will deliver thee from the way of the wicked, From the men who speak perverse things;
020	PRO	002	013	Who forsake the paths of uprightness, To walk in the ways of darkness;
020	PRO	002	014	Who rejoice in doing evil, And delight in the perverseness of the wicked;
020	PRO	002	015	Whose paths are crooked, And who are froward in their ways.
020	PRO	002	016	It will deliver thee from the wife of another, From the stranger, who useth smooth words;
020	PRO	002	017	Who forsaketh the friend of her youth, And forgetteth the covenant of her God.
020	PRO	002	018	For her house sinketh down to Death, And her paths to the shades of the dead:
020	PRO	002	019	None that go to her return again; They will not attain the paths of life.
020	PRO	002	020	Therefore walk thou in the way of good men, And keep the paths of the righteous:
020	PRO	002	021	For the upright shall dwell in the land, And the righteous shall remain in it;
020	PRO	002	022	But the wicked shall be cut off from the land, And transgressors shall be rooted out of it.
020	PRO	003	001	My son, forget not my teaching, And let thy heart observe my precepts!
020	PRO	003	002	For length of days, and years of life, And peace shall they multiply to thee.
020	PRO	003	003	Let not kindness and truth forsake thee; Bind them around thy neck, Write them upon the tablet of thy heart:
020	PRO	003	004	Then shalt thou find favor and good success In the sight of God and man.
020	PRO	003	005	Trust in the LORD with all thy heart, And lean not on thine own understanding;
020	PRO	003	006	In all thy ways acknowledge him, And he will make thy paths plain.
020	PRO	003	007	Be not wise in thine own eyes; Fear the LORD, and depart from evil.
020	PRO	003	008	It shall be health to thy muscles, And moisture to thy bones.
020	PRO	003	009	Honor the LORD with thy substance, And with the first-fruits of all thy increase;
020	PRO	003	010	So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, And thy vats overflow with new wine.
020	PRO	003	011	My son, despise not the correction of the LORD, Nor be impatient under his chastisement!
020	PRO	003	012	For whom the LORD loveth he chasteneth, Even as a father the son in whom he delighteth.
020	PRO	003	013	Happy the man who findeth wisdom; Yea, the man who getteth understanding!
020	PRO	003	014	For the profit thereof is greater than that of silver, And the gain thereof than that of fine gold.
020	PRO	003	015	More precious is she than pearls, And none of thy jewels is to be compared with her.
020	PRO	003	016	Length of days is in her right hand; In her left hand are riches and honor.
020	PRO	003	017	Her ways are ways of pleasantness, And all her paths are peace.
020	PRO	003	018	She is a tree of life to them that lay hold of her, And happy is every one who hath her in his grasp.
020	PRO	003	019	The LORD by wisdom founded the earth; By understanding he framed the heavens.
020	PRO	003	020	By his knowledge the deep waters were cleft, And the clouds drop down the dew.
020	PRO	003	021	My son, let them not depart from thine eyes; Keep sound wisdom and discretion!
020	PRO	003	022	For they shall be life to thy soul, And grace to thy neck.
020	PRO	003	023	Then shalt thou go on thy way securely, And thy foot shall not stumble;
020	PRO	003	024	When thou liest down, thou shalt not be afraid, Yea, thou shalt lie down, and thy sleep shall be sweet.
020	PRO	003	025	Be not thou afraid of sudden alarm, Nor of the storm that is for the wicked, when it cometh;
020	PRO	003	026	For the LORD shall be thy confidence; Yea, he will keep thy foot from being taken.
020	PRO	003	027	Withhold not kindness from those who need it, When it is in the power of thy hand to do it.
020	PRO	003	028	Say not to thy neighbor, “Go, and come again, And to-morrow I will give to thee,” when thou hast it by thee.
020	PRO	003	029	Devise not evil against thy neighbor, While he dwelleth securely by thee.
020	PRO	003	030	Contend not with a man without cause, When he hath done thee no harm.
020	PRO	003	031	Envy not the oppressor, And choose none of his ways.
020	PRO	003	032	For the perverse man is the abomination of the LORD, But he is in friendship with the upright.
020	PRO	003	033	The curse of the LORD is upon the house of the wicked, But he blesseth the dwelling of the righteous.
020	PRO	003	034	Surely the scorners he treadeth scornfully, But giveth favor to the lowly.
020	PRO	003	035	The wise shall obtain honor, But fools shall bear off shame.
020	PRO	004	001	Hear, ye children, the instruction of a father, And attend, that ye may learn understanding!
020	PRO	004	002	For I give you good instruction; Forsake ye not my commandments.
020	PRO	004	003	For I was my father's son, A tender and only child in the sight of my mother.
020	PRO	004	004	He taught me, and said to me, Let thy heart hold fast my words; Keep my commandments, and live.
020	PRO	004	005	Get wisdom, get understanding; Forget not, and depart not from, the words of my mouth.
020	PRO	004	006	Forsake her not, and she will guard thee: Love her, and she will preserve thee.
020	PRO	004	007	Wisdom is the principal thing; therefore gain wisdom, And with all thy gain, gain understanding.
020	PRO	004	008	Exalt her, and she will promote thee; She will bring thee to honor, when thou dost embrace her;
020	PRO	004	009	She will give to thy head a graceful wreath, A beautiful crown will she bestow upon thee.
020	PRO	004	010	Hear, O my son! and receive my sayings! So shall the years of thy life be many.
020	PRO	004	011	I have taught thee the way of wisdom, I have guided thee in the right path.
020	PRO	004	012	When thou goest, thy steps shall not be confined; And, when thou runnest, thou shalt not stumble.
020	PRO	004	013	Take fast hold of instruction; let her not go; Keep her, for she is thy life.
020	PRO	004	014	Enter not into the path of the wicked, And go not in the way of evil men;
020	PRO	004	015	Avoid it, pass not upon it, Turn from it, and go away.
020	PRO	004	016	For they sleep not, unless they have done mischief; Yea, their sleep is taken away, unless they have caused some to fall.
020	PRO	004	017	For they eat the bread of wickedness, And drink the wine of violence.
020	PRO	004	018	But the path of the righteous is as the light of dawn, Which groweth brighter and brighter unto the perfect day.
020	PRO	004	019	The way of the wicked is as thick darkness; They know not at what they stumble.
020	PRO	004	020	My son, attend to my words; Incline thine ear to my sayings;
020	PRO	004	021	Let them not depart from thine eyes; Keep them in the midst of thy heart!
020	PRO	004	022	For they are life to those who find them, And health to all their flesh.
020	PRO	004	023	More than any thing which thou watchest, watch thy heart; For from it goeth forth life.
020	PRO	004	024	Put away from thee a deceitful mouth, And remove far from thee perverse lips.
020	PRO	004	025	Let thine eyes look straight forward, And thine eyelids be directed before thee.
020	PRO	004	026	Give heed to the path of thy foot, And let all thy ways be steadfast.
020	PRO	004	027	Turn not to the right hand or to the left; Remove thy foot from evil.
020	PRO	005	001	My son, attend to my wisdom. And bow thine ear to my understanding;
020	PRO	005	002	That thou mayest keep discretion, And that thy lips may preserve knowledge!
020	PRO	005	003	Truly, the lips of a strange woman drop honey, And her mouth is smoother than oil;
020	PRO	005	004	But her end is bitter as wormwood, Sharp as a two-edged sword.
020	PRO	005	005	Her feet go down to death; Her steps lay hold of the under-world.
020	PRO	005	006	That she may not ponder the way of life, Her paths waver when she heedeth it not.
020	PRO	005	007	Hear me now, therefore, O children! And turn not away from the words of my mouth!
020	PRO	005	008	Remove thy way far from her. And come not nigh the door of her house:
020	PRO	005	009	Lest thou give thy bloom to others, And thy years to a cruel one;
020	PRO	005	010	Lest strangers be filled with thy wealth, And thine earnings be in the house of an alien;
020	PRO	005	011	And lest thou mourn in thy latter end. When thy flesh and thy body are consumed,
020	PRO	005	012	And say, “How have I hated instruction! And how hath my heart despised reproof!
020	PRO	005	013	I have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, Nor inclined mine ear to my instructors;
020	PRO	005	014	I have well-nigh fallen into utter misery; In the midst of the congregation and the assembly.”
020	PRO	005	015	Drink water out of thine own cistern. And running water out of thine own well:
020	PRO	005	016	So shall thy fountains overflow in the streets, In the wide streets, as streams of water;
020	PRO	005	017	They shall belong to thee alone, And not to strangers with thee;
020	PRO	005	018	And thy fountain shall be blessed, Yea, thou shalt have joy in the wife of thy youth.
020	PRO	005	019	A lovely hind, a graceful doe, Her breasts shall satisfy thee at all times, And thou shalt be always ravished with her love.
020	PRO	005	020	Why, then, my son, wilt thou be ravished with a wanton, And embrace the bosom of a stranger?
020	PRO	005	021	For the ways of man are before the eyes of the LORD, And he weigheth well all his paths.
020	PRO	005	022	His own iniquities shall ensnare the wicked; Yea, he shall be held fast by the cords of his own sins.
020	PRO	005	023	He shall die for want of instruction; Yea, through the greatness of his folly he shall stagger.
020	PRO	006	001	My son, if thou hast become surety for another, If thou hast stricken hands for another,
020	PRO	006	002	If thou hast become ensnared by the words of thy mouth, If thou hast been caught by the words of thy mouth,
020	PRO	006	003	Do this now, my son, and rescue thyself, —Since thou hast fallen into the hands of thy neighbor, —Go, prostrate thyself, and be urgent with thy neighbor!
020	PRO	006	004	Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber to thine eyelids;
020	PRO	006	005	Rescue thyself, as a roe from the hand, And as a bird from the hand of the fowler.
020	PRO	006	006	Go to the ant, O sluggard! Consider her ways, and be wise!
020	PRO	006	007	She hath no governor, Nor overseer, nor ruler;
020	PRO	006	008	Yet she prepareth in the summer her food, She gathereth in the harvest her meat.
020	PRO	006	009	How long wilt thou lie in bed, O sluggard? When wilt thou arise from thy sleep?
020	PRO	006	010	“A little sleep, —a little slumber, —A little folding of the hands to rest:”
020	PRO	006	011	So shall thy poverty come upon thee like a robber, Yea, thy want, as an armed man!
020	PRO	006	012	A worthless wretch is the unrighteous man, Who walketh with a deceitful mouth;
020	PRO	006	013	Who winketh with his eyes, Speaketh with his feet, And teacheth with his fingers.
020	PRO	006	014	Fraud is in his heart; He deviseth mischief continually; He scattereth contentions.
020	PRO	006	015	Therefore shall calamity come upon him suddenly; In a moment shall he be destroyed, and that without remedy;
020	PRO	006	016	These six things doth the LORD hate; Yea, seven are an abomination to him:
020	PRO	006	017	Lofty eyes, a false tongue, And hands which shed innocent blood;
020	PRO	006	018	A heart that contriveth wicked devices; Feet that are swift in running to mischief,
020	PRO	006	019	A false witness, that uttereth lies, And him that soweth discord among brethren.
020	PRO	006	020	Keep, O my son! the commandment of thy father, And forsake not the precepts of thy mother!
020	PRO	006	021	Bind them continually to thy heart, Tie them around thy neck!
020	PRO	006	022	When thou goest forth, they shall guide thee; When thou sleepest, they shall watch over thee; And, when thou awakest, they shall talk with thee.
020	PRO	006	023	For the commandment is a lamp, and instruction a light; Yea, the rebukes of correction lead to life.
020	PRO	006	024	They shall guard thee from the evil woman, From the smooth tongue of the unchaste woman.
020	PRO	006	025	Desire not her beauty in thy heart, Nor let her catch thee with her eyelids;
020	PRO	006	026	For by a harlot a man is brought to a morsel of bread, And the adulteress layeth snares for the precious life.
020	PRO	006	027	Can a man take fire into his bosom, And his clothes not be burned?
020	PRO	006	028	Can one walk upon burning coals, And his feet not be scorched?
020	PRO	006	029	So is it with him who goeth in to his neighbor's wife; Whoever toucheth her shall not go unpunished.
020	PRO	006	030	Men do not overlook a thief, Though he steal to satisfy his appetite, when he is hungry;
020	PRO	006	031	If found, he must repay sevenfold, And give up all the substance of his house.
020	PRO	006	032	Whoso committeth adultery with a woman lacketh understanding; He that doeth it destroyeth himself;
020	PRO	006	033	Blows and dishonor shall he get, And his reproach shall not be wiped away.
020	PRO	006	034	For jealousy is the fury of a man; He will not spare in the day of vengeance;
020	PRO	006	035	And he will not pay regard to any ransom, Nor be content, though thou offer many gifts.
020	PRO	007	001	My son, keep my words, And treasure up my commandments with thee!
020	PRO	007	002	Keep my commandments and live! Yea, my teaching, as the apple of thine eye!
020	PRO	007	003	Bind them upon thy fingers, Write them upon the tablet of thy heart!
020	PRO	007	004	Say unto wisdom, “Thou art my sister!” And call understanding thy near acquaintance;
020	PRO	007	005	That they may keep thee from the wife of another, From the stranger, that useth smooth words.
020	PRO	007	006	For through the window of my house, Through the lattice I was looking forth,
020	PRO	007	007	And I saw among the simple ones, I discerned among the youths, A young man void of understanding.
020	PRO	007	008	He was passing through the street near her corner, And was going the way to her house,
020	PRO	007	009	At twilight, in the evening, At midnight, yea, in the thick darkness.
020	PRO	007	010	And, behold, a woman met him, In the attire of a harlot, and subtle of heart, —
020	PRO	007	011	One noisy and unruly, Whose feet abide not in her house;
020	PRO	007	012	Who is now in the streets, now in the broad places, And lurketh near every corner.
020	PRO	007	013	She caught hold of him and kissed him, And with a shameless face said to him,
020	PRO	007	014	“Thank-offerings have been upon me, And this day have I performed my vows;
020	PRO	007	015	Therefore came I forth to meet thee, —Diligently to seek thy face, and I have found thee!
020	PRO	007	016	I have spread my bed with coverlets, With tapestry of the thread of Egypt.
020	PRO	007	017	I have sprinkled my bed With myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.
020	PRO	007	018	Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning; Let us solace ourselves with caresses.
020	PRO	007	019	For the good-man is not at home; He is gone a long journey;
020	PRO	007	020	He hath taken a purse of money with him; At the day of the full moon he will return.”
020	PRO	007	021	By her much fair speech she seduced him; By the smoothness of her lips she drew him away.
020	PRO	007	022	He goeth after her straightway, As an ox goeth to the slaughter, Or as one in fetters to the chastisement of the fool,
020	PRO	007	023	Till an arrow strike through his liver; —As a bird hasteneth into the snare, And knoweth not that it is laid for its life.
020	PRO	007	024	Now, therefore, ye children, hearken to me, And attend to the words of my mouth!
020	PRO	007	025	Let not thy heart turn aside to her ways; Go not astray in her paths!
020	PRO	007	026	For many are the wounded which she hath cast down; Yea, countless is the number of those slain by her.
020	PRO	007	027	Her house is the way to the under-world, Leading down to the chambers of death.
020	PRO	008	001	Doth not wisdom cry aloud, And understanding put forth her voice?
020	PRO	008	002	Upon the top of the high places, By the wayside, In the cross-ways, She taketh her station.
020	PRO	008	003	By the side of the gates, In the entrance of the city, In the approaches to the doors, she crieth aloud.
020	PRO	008	004	“To you, O men! do I call, And my voice is to the sons of men!
020	PRO	008	005	O ye simple ones! learn wisdom, And ye fools, be ye of an understanding heart!
020	PRO	008	006	Hear, for I speak excellent things, And my lips utter that which is right.
020	PRO	008	007	For my mouth speaketh truth, And wickedness is an abomination to my lips.
020	PRO	008	008	All the words of my mouth are in uprightness; There is nothing crooked or deceitful in them;
020	PRO	008	009	They are all plain to the man of understanding, And right to those who find knowledge.
020	PRO	008	010	Receive my instruction, and not silver. And knowledge rather than choice gold!
020	PRO	008	011	For wisdom is better than pearls, And no precious things are to be compared with her.
020	PRO	008	012	“I, wisdom, dwell with prudence, And find out the knowledge of sagacious counsels.
020	PRO	008	013	The fear of the LORD is to hate evil; Pride, and arrogance, and the evil way, And the deceitful mouth, do I hate.
020	PRO	008	014	Counsel is mine, and sound reason; I am understanding; I have strength.
020	PRO	008	015	By me kings reign, And princes decree justice.
020	PRO	008	016	By me princes rule, And nobles, even all the judges of the earth.
020	PRO	008	017	I love them that love me, And they who seek me early shall find me.
020	PRO	008	018	Riches and honor are with me; Yea, durable riches and prosperity.
020	PRO	008	019	My fruit is better than gold, yea, than fine gold. And my revenue than choice silver.
020	PRO	008	020	I walk in the way of righteousness, In the midst of the paths of equity.
020	PRO	008	021	I cause those who love me to possess substance; Yea, I fill their treasuries.
020	PRO	008	022	“The LORD created me, the firstling of his course, Before his works, of old;
020	PRO	008	023	I was anointed from everlasting, From the beginning, even before the earth was made.
020	PRO	008	024	When as yet there were no deeps, I was brought forth. When there were no springs, abounding with water.
020	PRO	008	025	Before the mountains were settled, Yea, before the hills, I was brought forth;
020	PRO	008	026	Ere yet he had made the land and the wastes, And the first of the clods of the earth.
020	PRO	008	027	When he framed the heavens, I was there; When he drew a circle upon the face of the deep;
020	PRO	008	028	When he made firm the sky above, And the fountains of the deep rushed forth;
020	PRO	008	029	When he gave to the sea its bounds, that the waters should not pass their border; When he marked out the foundations of the earth, —
020	PRO	008	030	Then was I by him as a master-builder; I was his delight day by day, Exulting before him at all times;
020	PRO	008	031	Exulting in the habitable part of his earth, And my delight was with the sons of men.
020	PRO	008	032	“Now, therefore, ye children, hearken to me! For happy are they who keep my ways!
020	PRO	008	033	Hear instruction, and be wise! Yea, reject it not!
020	PRO	008	034	Happy the man who hearkeneth to me, Who watcheth day by day at my gates, Who waiteth at the posts of my doors;
020	PRO	008	035	For he that findeth me findeth life, And obtaineth favor from the LORD;
020	PRO	008	036	But he who misseth me doeth violence to himself; All they who hate me love death.”
020	PRO	009	001	Wisdom hath builded her house; She hath hewn out her seven pillars.
020	PRO	009	002	She hath killed her fatlings; She hath mingled her wine; Yea, she hath furnished her table.
020	PRO	009	003	She hath sent forth her maidens; She crieth aloud upon the highest places of the city:
020	PRO	009	004	“Whoever is simple, let him turn in hither!” To him that is void of understanding she saith,
020	PRO	009	005	“Come, eat of my bread, And drink of the wine which I have mingled!
020	PRO	009	006	Forsake folly, and live! And go forward in the way of understanding!
020	PRO	009	007	“He who correcteth a scoffer Bringeth shame upon himself; And he who rebuketh the wicked Bringeth upon himself a stain.
020	PRO	009	008	Rebuke not a scoffer, lest he hate thee; Rebuke a wise man, and he will love thee.
020	PRO	009	009	Give instruction to a wise man, and he will be yet wiser; Teach a righteous man, and he will increase his learning.
020	PRO	009	010	The fear of the LORD is the beginning of wisdom, And the knowledge of the Most Holy is understanding.
020	PRO	009	011	Yea, through me thy days shall be multiplied, And the years of thy life shall be increased.
020	PRO	009	012	If thou art wise, thou art wise for thyself; And if thou art a scoffer, thou alone must bear it.”
020	PRO	009	013	The foolish woman is clamorous; She is very simple, and careth for nothing.
020	PRO	009	014	She sitteth at the door of her house, Upon a seat in the high places of the city,
020	PRO	009	015	To call aloud to those that pass by, Who go straight forward in their ways,
020	PRO	009	016	“Whoever is simple, let him turn in hither!” And to him that is void of understanding she saith,
020	PRO	009	017	“Stolen water is sweet, And bread eaten in secret is pleasant.”
020	PRO	009	018	But he considereth not that the dead are there, That in the vales of the under-world are her guests.
020	PRO	010	001	The Proverbs of Solomon. A wise son maketh a glad father, But a foolish son is the grief of his mother.
020	PRO	010	002	Treasures of wickedness do not profit; But righteousness delivereth from death.
020	PRO	010	003	The LORD will not suffer the righteous to famish; But he disappointeth the craving of the wicked.
020	PRO	010	004	He that worketh with a slack hand becometh poor; But the hand of the diligent maketh rich.
020	PRO	010	005	He that gathereth in summer is a wise son; But he that sleepeth in harvest is a son causing shame.
020	PRO	010	006	Blessings are upon the head of the just; But the mouth of the wicked concealeth violence.
020	PRO	010	007	The memory of the righteous man shall be blessed; But the name of the wicked shall rot.
020	PRO	010	008	He who is wise in heart receiveth precepts; But the foolish talker falleth headlong.
020	PRO	010	009	He that walketh uprightly walketh securely; But he that perverteth his ways shall be punished.
020	PRO	010	010	He that winketh with the eye causeth sorrow; And a foolish talker falleth headlong.
020	PRO	010	011	The mouth of the righteous is a fountain of life; But the mouth of the wicked concealeth violence.
020	PRO	010	012	Hatred stirreth up strife; But love covereth all offences.
020	PRO	010	013	Upon the lips of a man of understanding wisdom is found; But a rod is for the back of him that lacketh understanding.
020	PRO	010	014	Wise men treasure up knowledge; But the mouth of the foolish is destruction close at hand.
020	PRO	010	015	The rich man's wealth is his strong city; The destruction of the poor is their poverty.
020	PRO	010	016	The earnings of the righteous minister to life; The revenues of the wicked, to sin.
020	PRO	010	017	He that keepeth instruction is in the path of life; But he that refuseth reproof goeth astray.
020	PRO	010	018	He that hideth hatred hath lying lips; And he that uttereth slander is a fool.
020	PRO	010	019	In the multitude of words there wanteth not offence; But he who restraineth his lips is wise.
020	PRO	010	020	The tongue of the righteous is as choice silver; The understanding of the wicked is of little worth.
020	PRO	010	021	The lips of the righteous feed many; But fools die through want of wisdom.
020	PRO	010	022	It is the blessing of the LORD that maketh rich, And he addeth no sorrow with it.
020	PRO	010	023	It is as sport to a fool to do mischief; But a man of understanding hath wisdom.
020	PRO	010	024	The fear of the wicked shall come upon him; But the desire of the righteous shall be granted.
020	PRO	010	025	When the whirlwind passeth by, the wicked is no more; But the righteous is an everlasting foundation.
020	PRO	010	026	As vinegar to the teeth, and as smoke to the eyes, So is the sluggard to them that send him.
020	PRO	010	027	The fear of the LORD prolongeth life; But the years of the wicked shall be shortened.
020	PRO	010	028	The hope of the righteous shall be gladness: But the expectation of the wicked shall come to nothing.
020	PRO	010	029	The way of the LORD is a stronghold for the upright, But destruction for those who do iniquity.
020	PRO	010	030	The righteous shall never be moved; But the wicked shall not dwell in the land.
020	PRO	010	031	The mouth of the righteous man yieldeth wisdom; But the perverse tongue shall be cut off.
020	PRO	010	032	The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable; But the mouth of the wicked what is perverse.
020	PRO	011	001	False scales are an abomination to the LORD; But a perfect weight is his delight.
020	PRO	011	002	When pride cometh, then cometh disgrace; But with the humble is wisdom.
020	PRO	011	003	The integrity of the upright shall guide them; But the perverseness of transgressors shall destroy them.
020	PRO	011	004	Riches do not profit in the day of wrath; But righteousness delivereth from death.
020	PRO	011	005	The righteousness of the good man maketh his way plain; But the wicked falleth through his wickedness.
020	PRO	011	006	The righteousness of the upright delivereth them; But transgressors are ensnared in their own mischief.
020	PRO	011	007	When the wicked man dieth, his hope cometh to an end; Yea, the expectation of the unjust cometh to an end.
020	PRO	011	008	The righteous man is delivered from trouble, And the wicked cometh into it in his stead.
020	PRO	011	009	By his mouth the vile man destroyeth his neighbor; But by the knowledge of the righteous are men delivered.
020	PRO	011	010	When it goeth well with the righteous, the city rejoiceth; And when the wicked perish, there is shouting.
020	PRO	011	011	By the blessing of the upright the city is exalted; But it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked.
020	PRO	011	012	He who despiseth his neighbor is void of understanding; A man of discernment holdeth his peace.
020	PRO	011	013	He who goeth about as a tale-bearer revealeth secrets; But he who is of a faithful spirit concealeth a matter.
020	PRO	011	014	Where there is no counsel, the people fall; But in a multitude of counsellors there is safety.
020	PRO	011	015	He that is surety for another shall smart for it; But he that hateth suretyship is sure.
020	PRO	011	016	A graceful woman obtaineth honor, Even as strong men obtain riches.
020	PRO	011	017	He that doeth good to himself is a man of kindness; But he that tormenteth his own flesh is cruel.
020	PRO	011	018	The wicked toileth for deceitful wages; But he who soweth righteousness shall have a sure reward.
020	PRO	011	019	As righteousness tendeth to life, So he who pursueth evil pursueth it to his death.
020	PRO	011	020	The perverse in heart are the abomination of the LORD; But the upright in their way are his delight.
020	PRO	011	021	From generation to generation the wicked shall not go unpunished; But the posterity of the righteous shall be delivered.
020	PRO	011	022	As a jewel of gold in a swine's snout, So is a beautiful woman who is without discretion.
020	PRO	011	023	The desire of the righteous is only good; But the expectation of the wicked is wrath.
020	PRO	011	024	There is that scattereth, and yet increaseth; And there is that withholdeth more than is right, yet he cometh to want.
020	PRO	011	025	The bountiful man shall be enriched, And he that watereth shall himself be watered.
020	PRO	011	026	Him that keepeth back corn the people curse; But blessing shall be upon the head of him that selleth it.
020	PRO	011	027	He, who earnestly seeketh good, seeketh favor; But he that seeketh mischief, it shall come upon him.
020	PRO	011	028	He who trusteth in his riches shall fall; But the righteous shall flourish as a leaf.
020	PRO	011	029	He that harasseth his household shall inherit wind; And the fool shall be the servant of the wise.
020	PRO	011	030	The fruit of a righteous man is a tree of life; And the wise man winneth souls.
020	PRO	011	031	Behold, the righteous man is requited on the earth; Much more the wicked man and the sinner!
020	PRO	012	001	He who loveth correction loveth knowledge; But he who hateth rebuke remaineth stupid.
020	PRO	012	002	The good man obtaineth favor from the LORD; But the man of wicked devices he condemneth.
020	PRO	012	003	A man shall not be established by wickedness; But the root of the righteous shall not be moved.
020	PRO	012	004	A virtuous woman is a crown to her husband; But she who causeth shame is as rottenness in his bones.
020	PRO	012	005	The purposes of the righteous are just; The designs of the wicked are deceitful.
020	PRO	012	006	The words of the wicked lie in wait for men's blood; But the mouth of the upright delivereth them.
020	PRO	012	007	The wicked are overthrown, and are no more; But the house of the righteous shall stand.
020	PRO	012	008	A man will be commended according to his wisdom; But he that is of a perverse heart shall be despised.
020	PRO	012	009	Better is he that demeaneth himself, and hath a servant, Than he that exalteth himself, and hath no bread.
020	PRO	012	010	The righteous man careth for the life of his beast; But the tender mercies of the wicked are cruel.
020	PRO	012	011	He who tilleth his own land shall be satisfied with bread; But he who followeth worthless persons is void of understanding.
020	PRO	012	012	The wicked man longeth after the prey of evil-doers; But the root of the righteous yieldeth fruit.
020	PRO	012	013	In the transgression of the lips is a dangerous snare; But the righteous man shall escape from trouble.
020	PRO	012	014	By the fruit of a man's mouth he shall be filled with good, And the recompense of a man's hands shall be rendered unto him.
020	PRO	012	015	The way of a fool is right in his own eyes; But he that hearkeneth to counsel is wise.
020	PRO	012	016	A fool's wrath is instantly known; But he that hideth insult is wise.
020	PRO	012	017	He that speaketh truth testifieth what is right; But a false witness, deceit.
020	PRO	012	018	There is who babbleth like the piercing of a sword; But the tongue of the wise is health.
020	PRO	012	019	The lip of truth shall be established for ever; But the tongue of falsehood, but for a moment.
020	PRO	012	020	Deceit is in the heart of those who contrive evil; But to the counsellors of peace shall be joy.
020	PRO	012	021	No evil shall happen to the righteous; But the wicked shall be filled with calamity.
020	PRO	012	022	False lips are the abomination of the LORD; But they who deal truly are his delight.
020	PRO	012	023	A prudent man concealeth his knowledge; Bur the heart of fools proclaimeth their foolishness.
020	PRO	012	024	The hand of the diligent shall bear rule; But the slothful shall be under tribute.
020	PRO	012	025	Anxiety in the heart of a man boweth it down; But a kind word maketh it glad.
020	PRO	012	026	The righteous showeth the way to his neighbor; But the way of the wicked leadeth them astray.
020	PRO	012	027	The slothful man shall not roast his game; But a precious treasure to any man is he that is diligent.
020	PRO	012	028	In the path of righteousness is life, And in her pathway there is no death.
020	PRO	013	001	A wise son listeneth to the instruction of his father; But a scoffer listeneth not to rebuke.
020	PRO	013	002	By the fruit of a man's mouth he shall eat good; But the appetite of transgressors shall be sated with violence.
020	PRO	013	003	He who keepeth his mouth keepeth his life; But destruction shall be to him who openeth wide his lips.
020	PRO	013	004	The appetite of the sluggard longeth, and hath nothing; But the appetite of the diligent is fully satisfied.
020	PRO	013	005	A righteous man hateth words of falsehood; But a wicked man causeth disgrace and shame.
020	PRO	013	006	Righteousness preserveth him who is upright in his way; But wickedness overthroweth the sinner.
020	PRO	013	007	There is who maketh himself rich, yet hath nothing, Who maketh himself poor, yet hath great riches.
020	PRO	013	008	A man's wealth is the ransom of his life; But the poor man heareth no threatenings.
020	PRO	013	009	The light of the righteous shall rejoice; But the lamp of the wicked shall be put out.
020	PRO	013	010	By pride cometh only contention; But with the well-advised is wisdom.
020	PRO	013	011	Wealth gotten by vanity will become small; But he who gathereth it into the hand increaseth it.
020	PRO	013	012	Hope deferred maketh the heart sick; But the desire accomplished is a tree of life.
020	PRO	013	013	He that despiseth the word shall be destroyed; But he who revereth the commandment shall be rewarded.
020	PRO	013	014	The instruction of the wise is a fountain of life; By it men escape from the snares of death.
020	PRO	013	015	A good understanding winneth favor; But the way of transgressors is hard.
020	PRO	013	016	Every prudent man acteth with knowledge; But a fool spreadeth abroad his folly.
020	PRO	013	017	A wicked messenger falleth into trouble; But a faithful ambassador is health.
020	PRO	013	018	Poverty and shame are for him who rejecteth instruction; But he that regardeth reproof shall come to honor.
020	PRO	013	019	The desire accomplished is sweet to the soul; But it is an abomination to fools to depart from evil.
020	PRO	013	020	He who walketh with wise men shall be wise; But the companion of fools shall be destroyed.
020	PRO	013	021	Calamity pursueth the wicked; But the righteous is rewarded with good.
020	PRO	013	022	The good man leaveth his substance to his children's children; But the wealth of the sinner is laid up for the just.
020	PRO	013	023	There is much food from the fallow-ground of the poor; But there is who is brought low for want of uprightness.
020	PRO	013	024	He that spareth the rod hateth his son; But he who loveth him chasteneth him early.
020	PRO	013	025	The righteous man eateth to the satisfying of his desire; But the stomach of the wicked suffereth want.
020	PRO	014	001	The wise woman buildeth her house; But the foolish teareth it down with her hands.
020	PRO	014	002	He who walketh in uprightness feareth the LORD; But he who is perverse in his ways despiseth him.
020	PRO	014	003	In the mouth of the foolish pride is a scourge; But the lips of the wise preserve them.
020	PRO	014	004	Where there are no oxen, the crib is clean; But there is great increase by the strength of the ox.
020	PRO	014	005	A faithful witness doth not lie; But a false witness poureth forth lies.
020	PRO	014	006	The scoffer seeketh wisdom, and findeth it not; But knowledge is easy to the man of understanding.
020	PRO	014	007	Go from the presence of a foolish man; For thou hast not perceived in him the lips of knowledge.
020	PRO	014	008	The wisdom of the prudent is in giving heed to his way; But the folly of fools is deceit.
020	PRO	014	009	Fools make a mock at sin; But with the upright is favor.
020	PRO	014	010	The heart knoweth its own bitterness. And a stranger cannot intermeddle with its joy.
020	PRO	014	011	The house of the wicked shall be destroyed; But the tent of the upright shall flourish.
020	PRO	014	012	There is a way which seemeth right to a man, But its end is the way to death.
020	PRO	014	013	Even in laughter the heart is sorrowful, And the end of joy is grief.
020	PRO	014	014	The perverse in heart shall be filled with his own ways; And from himself shall the good man be satisfied.
020	PRO	014	015	The simple man believeth every word; But the prudent looketh well to his steps.
020	PRO	014	016	The wise man feareth, and departeth from evil; But the fool is haughty and confident.
020	PRO	014	017	He who is hasty in his anger will commit folly; And the man of wicked devices will be hated.
020	PRO	014	018	The simple inherit folly; But the prudent are crowned with knowledge.
020	PRO	014	019	The evil bow before the good; Yea, the wicked at the gates of the righteous.
020	PRO	014	020	The poor is hated even by his own neighbor; But the rich hath many friends.
020	PRO	014	021	He who despiseth his neighbor sinneth; But happy is he who hath mercy on the poor.
020	PRO	014	022	Do not they who devise evil fail of their end? But they who devise good meet with kindness and truth.
020	PRO	014	023	In all labor there is profit; But the talk of the lips tendeth only to penury.
020	PRO	014	024	Riches are a crown to the wise; But the promotion of fools is folly.
020	PRO	014	025	A true witness saveth lives; But a deceitful witness poureth forth lies.
020	PRO	014	026	In the fear of the LORD is strong confidence; Yea, to his children he will be a refuge.
020	PRO	014	027	The fear of the LORD is a fountain of life; By it men escape from the snares of death.
020	PRO	014	028	In a numerous people is the glory of a king; But the want of people is the destruction of a prince.
020	PRO	014	029	He who is slow to anger is of great understanding. But he who is of a hasty spirit setteth folly on high.
020	PRO	014	030	A quiet heart is the life of the flesh; But the ferment of passion is rottenness to the bones.
020	PRO	014	031	He who oppresseth the poor reproacheth his Maker; But he who hath mercy on the poor honoreth him.
020	PRO	014	032	By his wickedness the wicked is thrust down; But the righteous hath hope even in death.
020	PRO	014	033	Wisdom resteth quietly in the heart of the wise; But in the breast of fools it will be made known.
020	PRO	014	034	Righteousness exalteth a people; But the reproach of nations is sin.
020	PRO	014	035	The king's favor is toward a wise servant; But his wrath is against him that causeth shame.
020	PRO	015	001	A soft answer turneth away wrath; But harsh words stir up anger.
020	PRO	015	002	The tongue of the wise maketh knowledge pleasing; But the mouth of fools poureth forth folly.
020	PRO	015	003	The eyes of the LORD are in every place; They behold the evil and the good.
020	PRO	015	004	A mild tongue is a tree of life; But perverseness therein is a wound in the spirit.
020	PRO	015	005	The fool despiseth the correction of his father; But he that regardeth reproof is prudent.
020	PRO	015	006	In the house of the righteous is much wealth; But in the revenues of the wicked there is trouble.
020	PRO	015	007	The lips of the wise spread abroad knowledge; But the heart of the foolish is not sound.
020	PRO	015	008	The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination to the LORD; But the prayer of the righteous is his delight.
020	PRO	015	009	The way of the wicked is an abomination to the LORD; But him who followeth after righteousness he loveth.
020	PRO	015	010	Sore chastisement shall be to him that forsaketh the way; He that hateth reproof shall die.
020	PRO	015	011	The underworld, yea, the region of death, is before the LORD; How much more the hearts of the sons of men!
020	PRO	015	012	The scoffer loveth not his reprover; He will not resort to the wise.
020	PRO	015	013	A joyous heart maketh a bright countenance; But by sorrow of the heart the spirit is broken.
020	PRO	015	014	The heart of the man of understanding seeketh knowledge; But the mouth of fools feedeth on folly.
020	PRO	015	015	The days of the afflicted are all evil; But he that hath a cheerful heart hath a continual feast.
020	PRO	015	016	Better is a little, with the fear of the LORD, Than much treasure, and trouble therewith.
020	PRO	015	017	Better is a dinner of herbs, where there is love, Than a fatted ox, and hatred therewith.
020	PRO	015	018	The passionate man stirreth up strife; But he who is slow to anger appeaseth strife.
020	PRO	015	019	The way of the slothful is as a hedge of thorns; But the way of the righteous is a highway.
020	PRO	015	020	A wise son maketh a glad father; But a foolish man despiseth his mother.
020	PRO	015	021	Folly is joy to him who lacketh wisdom; But the man of understanding walketh uprightly.
020	PRO	015	022	Without counsel, plans come to nought; But with a multitude of counsellors they are established.
020	PRO	015	023	A man hath joy by the answer of his mouth; And a word in due season, how good it is!
020	PRO	015	024	The path of life is upward for the wise, So that he turneth away from the underworld beneath.
020	PRO	015	025	The LORD destroyeth the house of the proud; But he will establish the border of the widow.
020	PRO	015	026	Evil devices are an abomination to the LORD; But pleasant words are pure.
020	PRO	015	027	He who is greedy of gain troubleth his own house; But he who hateth bribes shall live.
020	PRO	015	028	The heart of the righteous meditateth on his answer; But the mouth of the wicked poureth out evil things.
020	PRO	015	029	The LORD is far from the wicked: But he heareth the prayer of the righteous.
020	PRO	015	030	The light of the eyes rejoiceth the heart, And good tidings make the bones fat.
020	PRO	015	031	The ear that hearkeneth to the reproof of life Shall dwell among the wise.
020	PRO	015	032	He that refuseth instruction despiseth his own life; But he that hearkeneth to rebuke getteth understanding.
020	PRO	015	033	The fear of the LORD guideth to wisdom, And before honor is humility.
020	PRO	016	001	To man belongeth the preparation of the heart; But the answer of the tongue is from the LORD.
020	PRO	016	002	All the ways of a man are pure in his own eyes; But the LORD weigheth the spirit.
020	PRO	016	003	Commit thy doings to the LORD, And thy purposes shall be established.
020	PRO	016	004	The LORD hath ordained every thing for its end; Yea, even the wicked for the day of evil.
020	PRO	016	005	Every one that is proud in heart is an abomination to the LORD; From generation to generation he shall not be unpunished.
020	PRO	016	006	Through kindness and truth, iniquity is expiated; And, through the fear of the LORD, men depart from evil.
020	PRO	016	007	When a man's ways please the LORD, He maketh even his enemies to be at peace with him.
020	PRO	016	008	Better is a little with righteousness, Than great revenues without right.
020	PRO	016	009	The heart of man deviseth his way, But the LORD establisheth his steps.
020	PRO	016	010	A divine sentence is upon the lips of a king; His mouth transgresseth not in judgment.
020	PRO	016	011	A just balance and scales are the appointment of the LORD; All the weights of the bag are his work.
020	PRO	016	012	The doing of wickedness is an abomination to kings; For by righteousness is the throne established.
020	PRO	016	013	Righteous lips are the delight of kings, And they love him who speaketh right things.
020	PRO	016	014	The wrath of a king is messengers of death; But a wise man will pacify it.
020	PRO	016	015	In the light of the king's countenance is life, And his favor is a like a cloud bringing the latter rain.
020	PRO	016	016	How much better is it to get wisdom than gold! Yea, to get understanding is rather to be chosen than silver.
020	PRO	016	017	It is the highway of the upright to depart from evil; He that taketh heed to his way preserveth his life.
020	PRO	016	018	Pride goeth before destruction, And a haughty spirit before a fall.
020	PRO	016	019	Better is it to be of a humble spirit with the lowly, Than to share the spoil with the proud.
020	PRO	016	020	He who giveth heed to the word shall find good; And he who trusteth in the LORD, happy is he!
020	PRO	016	021	The wise in heart shall be called intelligent, And sweetness of the lips increaseth learning.
020	PRO	016	022	Understanding is a wellspring of life to him that hath it. And the chastisement of fools is their folly.
020	PRO	016	023	The heart of the wise man instructeth his mouth, And addeth learning to his lips.
020	PRO	016	024	Pleasant words are like a honeycomb, Sweet to the taste, and health to the bones.
020	PRO	016	025	There is a way that seemeth right to a man, But the end thereof is the way to death.
020	PRO	016	026	The hunger of the laborer laboreth for him; For his mouth urgeth him on.
020	PRO	016	027	A worthless man diggeth mischief, And on his lips there is, as it were, a burning fire.
020	PRO	016	028	A deceitful man stirreth up strife, And a whisperer separateth friends.
020	PRO	016	029	A man of violence enticeth his neighbor, And leadeth him into a way which is not good.
020	PRO	016	030	He who shutteth his eyes to devise fraud, He who compresseth his lips, hath accomplished mischief!
020	PRO	016	031	The hoary head is a crown of glory, If it be found in the way of righteousness.
020	PRO	016	032	He who is slow to anger is better than the mighty; And he who ruleth his spirit, than he that taketh a city.
020	PRO	016	033	The lot is cast into the lap; But the whole decision thereof is from the LORD.
020	PRO	017	001	Better is a dry morsel, and quietness therewith, Than a house full of flesh-banquets with strife.
020	PRO	017	002	A prudent servant shall rule over a son who causeth shame; Yea, with brothers he shall share the inheritance.
020	PRO	017	003	The refining-pot is for silver, and the furnace for gold; But the LORD trieth hearts.
020	PRO	017	004	An evil-doer listeneth to mischievous lips; And a liar giveth ear to a destructive tongue.
020	PRO	017	005	Whoso mocketh the poor reproacheth his Maker; He that is glad at calamities shall not go unpunished.
020	PRO	017	006	Children's children are the crown of the aged, And their fathers the glory of sons.
020	PRO	017	007	Excellent speech becometh not the base; How much less lying lips the noble!
020	PRO	017	008	A gift is a precious stone in the eyes of him who taketh it; Whithersoever it turneth it hath success.
020	PRO	017	009	He who covereth an offence seeketh love; But he who recurreth to a matter removeth a friend.
020	PRO	017	010	A reproof will penetrate deeper into a wise man Than a hundred stripes into a fool.
020	PRO	017	011	An evil man seeketh only rebellion; Therefore shall a cruel messenger be sent against him.
020	PRO	017	012	Let a man meet a bear robbed of her whelps, Rather than a fool in his folly.
020	PRO	017	013	Whoso returneth evil for good, Evil shall not depart from his house.
020	PRO	017	014	The beginning of strife is as when one letteth out water; Therefore leave off contention before it rolleth onward.
020	PRO	017	015	He that justifieth the wicked, And he that condemneth the just, Both alike are an abomination to the LORD.
020	PRO	017	016	Why should a price be in the hand of a fool To get wisdom, seeing he hath no sense?
020	PRO	017	017	A friend loveth at all times; But in adversity he is born a brother.
020	PRO	017	018	A man who lacketh understanding striketh hands, And becometh surety in the presence of his friend.
020	PRO	017	019	He who loveth strife loveth transgression; He who raiseth high his gate seeketh ruin.
020	PRO	017	020	He that is of a deceitful heart shall find no good; And he that turneth about with his tongue shall fall into mischief.
020	PRO	017	021	Whoso begetteth a fool doeth it to his sorrow; Yea, the father of the fool hath no joy.
020	PRO	017	022	A merry heart doeth good to the body; But a broken spirit drieth up the bones.
020	PRO	017	023	The wicked man taketh a gift out of the bosom, To pervert the ways of judgment.
020	PRO	017	024	Wisdom is before the face of him that hath understanding; But the eyes of a fool are in the ends of the earth.
020	PRO	017	025	A foolish son is a grief to his father, And bitterness to her that bore him.
020	PRO	017	026	Moreover, to punish the righteous is not good, Nor to smite the noble for their equity.
020	PRO	017	027	He that spareth his words is imbued with knowledge; And he that is of a cool spirit is a man of understanding.
020	PRO	017	028	Even a fool, when he is silent, is accounted wise; He that shutteth his lips is a man of understanding.
020	PRO	018	001	He who separateth himself seeketh his own desire; Against all sound discretion he rusheth on.
020	PRO	018	002	The fool hath no delight in understanding, But rather in revealing his own mind.
020	PRO	018	003	When the wicked cometh, then cometh also contempt; And with baseness, shame.
020	PRO	018	004	The words of a man's mouth are deep waters, And the wellspring of wisdom is an overflowing brook.
020	PRO	018	005	It is not good to be partial to the wicked, So as to overthrow the righteous in judgment.
020	PRO	018	006	The lips of a fool enter into strife, And his mouth calleth for blows.
020	PRO	018	007	A fool's mouth is his destruction, And his lips are a snare for his life.
020	PRO	018	008	The words of a talebearer are like sweet morsels; For they go down to the innermost parts of the body.
020	PRO	018	009	Moreover, he that is slothful in his work Is brother to him that is a great waster.
020	PRO	018	010	The name of the LORD is a strong tower; The righteous runneth to it, and is safe.
020	PRO	018	011	The rich man's wealth is his strong city, And as a high wall, in his own conceit.
020	PRO	018	012	Before destruction the heart of a man is haughty, And before honor is humility.
020	PRO	018	013	He who answereth a matter before he hath heard it, It is folly and shame to him.
020	PRO	018	014	The spirit of a man will sustain his infirmity; But a wounded spirit who can bear?
020	PRO	018	015	The heart of the intelligent will acquire knowledge, And the ear of the wise will seek knowledge.
020	PRO	018	016	A gift maketh room for a man, And bringeth him into the presence of the great.
020	PRO	018	017	He that first pleadeth his cause appeareth just; But his opponent cometh, and searcheth him through.
020	PRO	018	018	The lot causeth contentions to cease, And parteth asunder the mighty.
020	PRO	018	019	A brother offended is harder to be won than a strong city; Yea, their contentions are like the bars of a castle.
020	PRO	018	020	With the fruit of a man's mouth shall his stomach be filled; He shall be filled with the produce of his lips.
020	PRO	018	021	Death and life are in the power of the tongue; They that love it shall eat its fruit.
020	PRO	018	022	He that findeth a wife findeth a blessing, And obtaineth favor from the LORD.
020	PRO	018	023	The poor useth entreaties; But the rich answereth roughly.
020	PRO	018	024	A man of many friends will show himself false; Yet there is a friend who sticketh closer than a brother.
020	PRO	019	001	Better is the poor man who walketh in his integrity, Than he who is of false lips and a fool.
020	PRO	019	002	Moreover, that the soul be without knowledge is not good, And he that hasteth with is feet stumbleth.
020	PRO	019	003	The folly of man destroyeth his way, And then his heart fretteth against the LORD.
020	PRO	019	004	Wealth maketh many friends; But the poor is separated from his neighbor.
020	PRO	019	005	A false witness shall not be unpunished, And he that speaketh lies shall not escape.
020	PRO	019	006	Many are they who caress the noble, And every one is the friend of him who giveth gifts.
020	PRO	019	007	All the brethren of the poor man hate him; How much more do his friends go far from him! He runneth after their words, —they are gone!
020	PRO	019	008	He that getteth wisdom loveth himself; He that keepeth understanding shall find good.
020	PRO	019	009	A false witness shall not be unpunished, And he that speaketh lies shall perish.
020	PRO	019	010	Luxury is not seemly for a fool; Much less should a servant have rule over princes.
020	PRO	019	011	A man of understanding is slow to anger; Yea, it is his glory to pass over an offence.
020	PRO	019	012	The wrath of a king is like the roaring of a lion; But his favor, like dew upon the grass.
020	PRO	019	013	A foolish son is a calamity to his father, And the contentions of a wife are a continual dropping.
020	PRO	019	014	Houses and riches are an inheritance from fathers; But a prudent wife is from the LORD.
020	PRO	019	015	Slothfulness casteth into a deep sleep, And the idle person shall suffer hunger.
020	PRO	019	016	He that keepeth the commandment keepeth his life; But he that neglecteth his ways shall die.
020	PRO	019	017	He who hath pity on the poor lendeth to the LORD, And that which he giveth will he repay him.
020	PRO	019	018	Chasten thy son because there is hope, But let not thy soul desire to slay him.
020	PRO	019	019	A man of great wrath will suffer punishment; For if thou deliver him, yet must thou do it again.
020	PRO	019	020	Listen to counsel and receive instruction, That thou mayst be wise in thy latter years.
020	PRO	019	021	Many are the devices in the heart of a man; But the purpose of the LORD, that shall stand.
020	PRO	019	022	The charm of a man is his kindness; And better is a poor man than a liar.
020	PRO	019	023	The fear of the LORD tendeth to life, And he that hath it shall abide satisfied; He shall not be visited with evil.
020	PRO	019	024	The slothful man dippeth his hand into the dish: He doth not bring it back even to his mouth.
020	PRO	019	025	Strike the scoffer, and the simple will become prudent; Reprove a man of understanding, and he will discern knowledge.
020	PRO	019	026	The son that causeth shame and disgrace doeth violence to his father, And chaseth away his mother.
020	PRO	019	027	Cease, my son, to listen to the instruction That causeth thee to wander from the words of knowledge!
020	PRO	019	028	A worthless witness scoffeth at justice, And the mouth of the wicked swalloweth down iniquity.
020	PRO	019	029	Punishments are prepared for scoffers, And stripes for the back of fools.
020	PRO	020	001	Wine is a mocker, strong drink a brawler, And he that reeleth with it is not wise.
020	PRO	020	002	The terror of a king is like the roaring of a lion; He who provoketh him sinneth against himself.
020	PRO	020	003	It is an honor to a man to cease from strife; Bur every fool rusheth into it.
020	PRO	020	004	The sluggard will not plough by reason of the cold; Therefore shall he beg in harvest, and have nothing.
020	PRO	020	005	A design in the heart of a man is like deep waters; But a man of understanding draweth it out.
020	PRO	020	006	Many will proclaim their own kindness; But a faithful man who can find?
020	PRO	020	007	He who walketh in his integrity is a righteous man; Happy will be his children after him!
020	PRO	020	008	The king, sitting upon the throne of judgment, Scattereth with his eyes all the wicked like chaff.
020	PRO	020	009	Who can say, “I have kept my heart clean; I am free from my sin?”
020	PRO	020	010	Divers weights and divers measures, —Both of them are an abomination to the LORD.
020	PRO	020	011	Even in childhood one maketh himself known by his doings, Whether his actions will be pure and right.
020	PRO	020	012	The ear that heareth, and the eye that seeth, —The LORD made them both.
020	PRO	020	013	Love not sleep, lest thou come to poverty; Open thine eyes, and thou shalt be satisfied with bread.
020	PRO	020	014	“Bad! bad!” saith the buyer; But when he hath gone his way, then he boasteth.
020	PRO	020	015	There is gold and abundance of pearls; But the lips of knowledge are a precious vase.
020	PRO	020	016	Take his garment who is surety for another; Yea, take a pledge of him who is bound for a stranger.
020	PRO	020	017	The bread of falsehood is sweet to a man; But afterwards his mouth is filled with gravel.
020	PRO	020	018	Purposes are established by counsel; Therefore with good advice make war.
020	PRO	020	019	He who goeth about as a tale-bearer revealeth secrets; Therefore associate not with him who keepeth open his lips.
020	PRO	020	020	Whoso curseth his father or his mother, His lamp shall be put out in midnight darkness.
020	PRO	020	021	A possession may be gotten hastily in the beginning, But in the end it will not be blessed.
020	PRO	020	022	Say not thou, “I will repay evil;” Wait on the LORD, and he will help thee.
020	PRO	020	023	Divers weights are an abomination to the LORD, And a false balance is not good.
020	PRO	020	024	A man's steps are from the LORD; How, then, can a man understand his way?
020	PRO	020	025	It is a snare to a man to utter a vow rashly, And after vows to consider.
020	PRO	020	026	A wise king scattereth the wicked like chaff, And bringeth over them the wheel.
020	PRO	020	027	The spirit of a man is the lamp of the LORD, Which searcheth all the inner chambers of his body.
020	PRO	020	028	Mercy and truth preserve the king; Yea, his throne is upholden by mercy.
020	PRO	020	029	The glory of young men is their strength, And the beauty of old men is the gray head.
020	PRO	020	030	Wounding stripes are the remedy for a bad man; Yea, stripes which reach to the inner chambers of the body.
020	PRO	021	001	As streams of water, So is the heart of the king in the hand of the LORD; He turneth it whithersoever he will.
020	PRO	021	002	All the ways of a man are right in his own eyes; But the LORD weigheth the heart.
020	PRO	021	003	To do justice and equity Is more acceptable to the LORD than sacrifice.
020	PRO	021	004	The lofty look, the proud heart, The lamp of the wicked, is ruin.
020	PRO	021	005	The plans of the diligent tend only to plenty; But the hasty hasteneth only to want.
020	PRO	021	006	The getting of treasures by a false tongue Is the fleeting breath of them that seek death.
020	PRO	021	007	The rapine of the wicked shall snatch them away, Because they refuse to do justice.
020	PRO	021	008	The way of the guilty man is crooked; But he that is pure, his doings are right.
020	PRO	021	009	Better is it to dwell in a corner of the housetop Than with a brawling woman in a large house.
020	PRO	021	010	The soul of the wicked longeth to do evil; His neighbor findeth no compassion in his eyes.
020	PRO	021	011	When the scoffer is punished, the simple is made wise; When the wise man is taught, he receiveth knowledge.
020	PRO	021	012	The righteous man hath regard to the house of the wicked; He casteth the wicked headlong into ruin.
020	PRO	021	013	Whoso stoppeth his ears at the cry of the poor, He also shall cry aloud, but shall not be heard.
020	PRO	021	014	A gift in secret pacifieth anger; And a present in the bosom, strong wrath.
020	PRO	021	015	To do justice shall be joy to the righteous; But destruction is for them that do iniquity.
020	PRO	021	016	A man who wandereth from the way of discretion Shall rest in the assembly of the dead.
020	PRO	021	017	He that loveth pleasure will be a poor man; He that loveth wine and oil will not be rich.
020	PRO	021	018	The wicked shall be a ransom for the righteous! And in the room of the upright shall be the transgressor.
020	PRO	021	019	It is better to dwell in a desert land Than with a contentious and fretful woman.
020	PRO	021	020	Precious treasure and oil are in the dwelling of the wise; But the foolish man swalloweth them up.
020	PRO	021	021	He who followeth after righteousness and mercy Shall find life, prosperity, and honor.
020	PRO	021	022	A wise man scaleth the city of the mighty, And bringeth down the strength in which it trusted.
020	PRO	021	023	Whoso keepeth his mouth and his tongue Keepeth his soul from trouble.
020	PRO	021	024	The proud and haughty, —scoffer is his name; He acteth with haughty arrogance.
020	PRO	021	025	The desire of the sluggard will destroy him; For his hands refuse to labor.
020	PRO	021	026	The covetous man coveteth all the day long; But the righteous man giveth, and doth not withhold.
020	PRO	021	027	The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination; How much more when he bringeth it with an evil design!
020	PRO	021	028	A false witness shall perish; But a man that hearkeneth shall speak forever.
020	PRO	021	029	The wicked man hardeneth his face; But the upright directeth his way.
020	PRO	021	030	Wisdom is nothing, and understanding is nothing, And devices are nothing, against the LORD.
020	PRO	021	031	The horse is prepared for the day of battle; But victory is from the LORD.
020	PRO	022	001	A good name is rather to be chosen than great riches; And better is good-will than silver and gold.
020	PRO	022	002	The rich and the poor meet together; The LORD is the Maker of them all.
020	PRO	022	003	The prudent man seeth the evil, and hideth himself; But the simple rush on, and are punished.
020	PRO	022	004	By humility and the fear of the LORD Are riches and honor and life.
020	PRO	022	005	Thorns and snares are in the way of the deceitful; He that will preserve his life will be far from them.
020	PRO	022	006	Train up a child in accordance with his way, And when he is old he will not depart from it.
020	PRO	022	007	The rich ruleth over the poor, And the borrower is servant to the lender.
020	PRO	022	008	He who soweth iniquity shall reap calamity, And the rod of his punishment is prepared.
020	PRO	022	009	He who hath a bountiful eye shall be blessed, Because he giveth of his bread to the poor.
020	PRO	022	010	Cast out the scoffer, and contention will go out; Yea, strife and reproach will cease.
020	PRO	022	011	He who loveth purity of heart, Grace is upon his lips, and the king will be his friend.
020	PRO	022	012	The eyes of the LORD watch over knowledge; But he overthroweth the words of the treacherous.
020	PRO	022	013	The slothful man saith, “There is a lion without; I shall be slain in the streets.”
020	PRO	022	014	The mouth of strange women is a deep pit; He with whom the LORD is angry shall fall therein.
020	PRO	022	015	Folly is bound to the heart of a child; But the rod of correction will drive it far from him.
020	PRO	022	016	He that oppresseth the poor to increase his wealth, And he that giveth to the rich, shall surely come to want.
020	PRO	022	017	Incline thine ear, and hear the words of the wise, And give heed to my instruction!
020	PRO	022	018	For it will be a pleasant thing, if thou keep them in thy bosom, When they are altogether established upon thy lips.
020	PRO	022	019	That thy trust may be in the LORD, I have this day given to thee instruction, yea, to thee.
020	PRO	022	020	Behold, I have written to thee excellent things Concerning counsel and knowledge;
020	PRO	022	021	That I may make thee know rectitude, and words of truth; That thou mayst bring back words of truth to them that send thee.
020	PRO	022	022	Rob not the poor man, because he is poor, Nor crush thou the destitute at the gate;
020	PRO	022	023	For the LORD will maintain their cause, And despoil their spoilers of life.
020	PRO	022	024	Make no friendship with a passionate man, Nor be the companion of a man prone to wrath;
020	PRO	022	025	Lest thou learn his ways, And take to thyself a snare.
020	PRO	022	026	Be not thou one of those who strike hands, Of those who are sureties for debts.
020	PRO	022	027	When thou hast nothing to pay, Why should thy bed be taken from under thee?
020	PRO	022	028	Remove not the ancient landmark, Which thy fathers have made.
020	PRO	022	029	Seest thou a man diligent in his business? He shall be the minister of kings; He shall not serve obscure men.
020	PRO	023	001	When thou sittest to eat with a ruler, Consider well what is before thee;
020	PRO	023	002	For thou wilt put a knife to thy throat, If thou art a man given to appetite!
020	PRO	023	003	Long not for his dainties. For they are deceitful meat.
020	PRO	023	004	Toil not to become rich; Cease from this, thy wisdom.
020	PRO	023	005	Wilt thou let thine eyes fly toward them? They are gone! For riches truly make to themselves wings; They fly away like the eagle toward heaven.
020	PRO	023	006	Eat not the bread of him that hath an evil eye, And long not for his dainties;
020	PRO	023	007	For as he thinketh in his heart, so is he. “Eat and drink!” saith he to thee; But his heart is not with thee.
020	PRO	023	008	The morsel, which thou hast eaten, thou shalt vomit up; And thou wilt have thrown away thy sweet words.
020	PRO	023	009	Speak not in the ears of a fool; For he will despise the wisdom of thy words.
020	PRO	023	010	Remove not the ancient landmark, And enter not into the fields of the fatherless!
020	PRO	023	011	For their avenger is mighty; He will maintain their cause against thee.
020	PRO	023	012	Apply thy heart to instruction, And thine ears to the words of knowledge.
020	PRO	023	013	Withhold not correction from a child; If thou beat him with the rod, he will not die.
020	PRO	023	014	Beat him thyself with the rod, And thou shalt rescue him from the underworld.
020	PRO	023	015	My son, if thy heart be wise, My heart shall rejoice, even mine;
020	PRO	023	016	Yea, my reins shall exult, When thy lips speak right things.
020	PRO	023	017	Let not thy heart envy sinners, But continue thou in the fear of the LORD all the day long;
020	PRO	023	018	For surely there shall be a reward, And thine expectation shall not be cut off.
020	PRO	023	019	Hear thou, my son, and be wise; And let thy heart go forward in the way!
020	PRO	023	020	Be not thou among winebibbers, And riotous eaters of flesh;
020	PRO	023	021	For the drunkard and the glutton shall come to poverty, And drowsiness will clothe a man with rags.
020	PRO	023	022	Hearken to thy father, who begat thee, And despise not thy mother when she is old.
020	PRO	023	023	Buy the truth, and sell it not; Buy wisdom and instruction and understanding.
020	PRO	023	024	The father of a righteous man shall greatly rejoice; Yea, he who begetteth a wise child shall have joy in him.
020	PRO	023	025	Let thy father and thy mother have joy; Yea, let her that bore thee rejoice!
020	PRO	023	026	My son, give me thy heart, And let thine eyes observe my ways!
020	PRO	023	027	For a harlot is a deep ditch; Yea, a strange woman is a narrow pit.
020	PRO	023	028	Like a robber she lieth in wait, And increaseth the treacherous among men.
020	PRO	023	029	Who hath woe? Who hath sorrow? Who contentions? Who anxiety? Who wounds without cause? Who dimness of eyes?
020	PRO	023	030	They that tarry long at the wine; They that go in to seek mixed wine.
020	PRO	023	031	Look not thou upon the wine when it is red, When it sparkleth in the cup, When it goeth down smoothly.
020	PRO	023	032	At the last it biteth like a serpent, And stingeth like an adder.
020	PRO	023	033	Thine eyes will look upon strange women, And thy heart will utter perverse things.
020	PRO	023	034	Yea, thou shalt be as one that lieth down in the midst of the sea, And as one that lieth down upon the top of a mast.
020	PRO	023	035	They have stricken me [shalt thou say], —I suffered no pain! They have beaten me, —I felt it not! When shall I awake? I will seek it yet again.
020	PRO	024	001	Be not thou envious of wicked men, And desire not to be with them!
020	PRO	024	002	For their heart studieth destruction, And their lips speak mischief.
020	PRO	024	003	Through wisdom is a house builded, And by understanding is it established;
020	PRO	024	004	Yea, by knowledge are the chambers filled With all precious and goodly substance.
020	PRO	024	005	The wise man is strong; Yea, the man of understanding establisheth his strength.
020	PRO	024	006	For by wise counsel shalt thou make war, And by the multitude of counsellors cometh success.
020	PRO	024	007	Wisdom is too high for the fool; He openeth not his mouth at the gate.
020	PRO	024	008	He that deviseth to do evil Shall be called mischief-master.
020	PRO	024	009	The purpose of folly is sin; And a scoffer is an abomination to men.
020	PRO	024	010	If thy spirit faint in the day of adversity, Faint will be thy strength.
020	PRO	024	011	Deliver thou those who are dragged to death, And those who totter to the slaughter, —O keep them back!
020	PRO	024	012	If thou sayst, “Behold, we knew it not!” Doth not he that weigheth the heart observe it? Yea, he that keepeth thy soul knoweth it. And he will render to every man according to his works.
020	PRO	024	013	Eat honey, my son, for it is good, And the honeycomb, which is sweet to thy taste;
020	PRO	024	014	So learn thou wisdom for thy soul! When thou hast found it, there shall be a reward, And thy expectation shall not be cut off.
020	PRO	024	015	Plot not, O wicked man! against the habitation of the righteous; Spoil not his resting-place!
020	PRO	024	016	For though the righteous fall seven times, yet shall he rise up again; But the wicked shall fall into mischief.
020	PRO	024	017	Rejoice not when thine enemy falleth, And let not thy heart be glad when he stumbleth;
020	PRO	024	018	Lest the LORD see, and it displease him, And he turn away his anger from him.
020	PRO	024	019	Fret not thyself on account of evil men, Neither be thou envious of the wicked;
020	PRO	024	020	For there shall be no posterity to the evil man; The lamp of the wicked shall be put out.
020	PRO	024	021	My son, fear thou the LORD and the king; And mingle not with them that are given to change!
020	PRO	024	022	For their calamity shall rise up suddenly, And their ruin, coming from them both, in a moment.
020	PRO	024	023	These also are words of the wise. It is not good to have respect of persons in judgment.
020	PRO	024	024	He that saith to the wicked, “Thou art righteous,” Him shall the people curse; Nations shall abhor him.
020	PRO	024	025	But it shall be well with them that punish him, And the blessing of prosperity shall come upon them.
020	PRO	024	026	He that giveth a right answer Kisseth the lips.
020	PRO	024	027	Arrange thy work without, And prepare it in thy field: Afterwards thou mayst build thy house.
020	PRO	024	028	Be not a witness without cause against thy neighbor, And deceive not with thy lips.
020	PRO	024	029	Say not, “As he hath done to me, So will I do to him; I will render to the man according to his doings.”
020	PRO	024	030	I passed by the field of the slothful, And by the vineyard of the man void of understanding,
020	PRO	024	031	And, lo! it was all overgrown with thorns, And the face thereof was covered with nettles, And the stone wall thereof was broken down.
020	PRO	024	032	Then I saw, and considered it well; I looked upon it. and received instruction.
020	PRO	024	033	“A little sleep, a little slumber! A little folding of the hands to rest!”
020	PRO	024	034	So shall poverty come upon thee like a highwayman; Yea, want like an armed man.
020	PRO	025	001	These also are proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah, king of Judah, collected.
020	PRO	025	002	It is the glory of God to conceal a thing; But it is the glory of kings to search out a matter.
020	PRO	025	003	As the heavens for their height, And as the earth for its depth, So is the heart of kings unsearchable!
020	PRO	025	004	Take away the dross from the silver, And there will come forth a vessel for the founder;
020	PRO	025	005	Take away the wicked man from the presence of the king, And his throne will be established by righteousness.
020	PRO	025	006	Put not thyself forth in the presence of the king, Nor set thyself in the place of the great;
020	PRO	025	007	For better is it that one should say to thee, “Come up hither!” Than that he should put thee in a lower place, In the presence of the prince whom thine eyes behold.
020	PRO	025	008	Go not forth hastily to engage in a suit, Lest thou know not what to do in the end of it, When thine adversary hath put thee to shame.
020	PRO	025	009	Maintain thy cause with thine adversary, But reveal not another's secret;
020	PRO	025	010	Lest he that heareth it put thee to shame, And thy infamy depart not from thee.
020	PRO	025	011	A word spoken in season Is like apples of gold in figured-work of silver.
020	PRO	025	012	As a ring of gold, and an ornament of fine gold, So is a wise reprover to an attentive ear.
020	PRO	025	013	As the cold of snow in the time of harvest, So is a faithful messenger to them that send him; For he refresheth the spirit of his masters.
020	PRO	025	014	As clouds and wind without rain, So is the man that boasteth falsely of giving.
020	PRO	025	015	By long forbearing is a prince appeased; And a soft tongue breaketh bones.
020	PRO	025	016	Hast thou found honey? eat what is sufficient for thee, Lest thou be surfeited with it, and vomit it up.
020	PRO	025	017	Let thy foot be seldom in the house of thy friend, Lest he be surfeited with thee and hate thee.
020	PRO	025	018	A battle-hammer, and a sword, and a sharp arrow, Is the man who beareth false witness against his neighbor.
020	PRO	025	019	As a broken tooth, and a wavering foot, So is trust in an unfaithful man in time of trouble.
020	PRO	025	020	As he that taketh off a garment on a cold day, As vinegar upon nitre, So is he that singeth songs to a heavy heart.
020	PRO	025	021	If thine enemy be hungry, give him bread to eat; And if he be thirsty, give him water to drink;
020	PRO	025	022	For thou wilt heap coals of fire upon his head, And the LORD will reward thee.
020	PRO	025	023	As the north wind bringeth forth rain, So a backbiting tongue maketh an angry countenance.
020	PRO	025	024	Better is it to dwell in a corner of the housetop, Than with a quarrelsome woman in a large house.
020	PRO	025	025	As cold water to the thirsty, So is good news from a far country.
020	PRO	025	026	As a troubled fountain, and as a corrupted spring, So is a righteous man falling before the wicked.
020	PRO	025	027	To eat much honey is not good; So the search of high things is weariness.
020	PRO	025	028	As a city broken through and without a wall, So is he that hath no rule over his spirit.
020	PRO	026	001	As snow in summer, and as rain in harvest, So honor is not becoming to a fool.
020	PRO	026	002	As the sparrow wandereth, and the swallow flieth away, So the curse without cause shall not come.
020	PRO	026	003	A whip for the horse, a bridle for the ass, And a rod for the back of the fool.
020	PRO	026	004	Answer not a fool according to his folly, Lest thou also become like to him.
020	PRO	026	005	Answer a fool according to his folly, Lest he be wise in his own conceit.
020	PRO	026	006	He cutteth off the feet, and drinketh damage, Who sendeth a message by the hand of a fool.
020	PRO	026	007	The legs of a lame man hang loose; So is it with a proverb in the mouth of fools.
020	PRO	026	008	As he who bindeth a stone in a sling, So is he that giveth honor to a fool.
020	PRO	026	009	As a thorn lifted up by the hand of a drunkard, So is a proverb in the mouth of fools.
020	PRO	026	010	As an archer who woundeth every one, So is he who hireth fools and hireth wayfarers.
020	PRO	026	011	As a dog returneth to that which he hath vomited, So a fool repeateth his folly.
020	PRO	026	012	Seest thou a man wise in his own conceit? There is more hope of a fool than of him.
020	PRO	026	013	The slothful man saith, “There is a lion in the way; There is a lion in the streets.”
020	PRO	026	014	As a door turneth upon its hinges, So doth the sluggard upon his bed.
020	PRO	026	015	The sluggard dippeth his hand into the dish; It grieveth him to bring it again to his mouth.
020	PRO	026	016	The sluggard is wiser in his own conceit Than seven men who can render a reason.
020	PRO	026	017	As one that taketh a dog by the ears, So is he who, passing by, is enraged on account of the quarrel of another.
020	PRO	026	018	As a madman That casteth about darts, arrows, and death,
020	PRO	026	019	So is the man who deceiveth his neighbor, And saith, “Was I not in sport?”
020	PRO	026	020	Where there is no wood, the fire goeth out; So, where there is no talebearer, contention ceaseth.
020	PRO	026	021	As coal is for heat, and as wood for fire, So is a contentious man for kindling strife.
020	PRO	026	022	The words of a talebearer are like dainties; For they go down to the innermost parts of the body.
020	PRO	026	023	As drossy silver spread over an earthen vessel, So are warm lips and an evil heart.
020	PRO	026	024	The hater dissembleth with his lips, And layeth up deceit within him.
020	PRO	026	025	When he speaketh fair, believe him not! For there are seven abominations in his heart.
020	PRO	026	026	His hatred is covered by deceit; His wickedness shall be revealed in the great assembly.
020	PRO	026	027	He that diggeth a pit shall fall therein; And he that rolleth a stone, it shall return upon him.
020	PRO	026	028	A lying tongue hateth those whom it woundeth, And a flattering mouth worketh ruin.
020	PRO	027	001	Boast not thyself of to-morrow; For thou knowest not what a day may bring forth!
020	PRO	027	002	Let another man praise thee, and not thine own mouth; A stranger, and not thine own lips.
020	PRO	027	003	A stone is heavy and sand is weighty; But a fool's wrath is heavier than both.
020	PRO	027	004	Wrath is cruel, and anger overwhelming; But who is able to stand before jealousy?
020	PRO	027	005	Better is open rebuke Than love kept concealed.
020	PRO	027	006	Faithful are the wounds of a friend; But the kisses of an enemy are deceitful.
020	PRO	027	007	He who is fed to the full loatheth the honeycomb; But to the hungry any bitter thing is sweet.
020	PRO	027	008	As a bird that wandereth from its nest, So is a man who wandereth from his place.
020	PRO	027	009	Oil and perfume gladden the heart; Sweet also is one's friend by hearty counsel.
020	PRO	027	010	Thine own friend and thy father's friend forsake not; And go not into thy brother's house in the day of thy calamity. Better is a neighbor that is near, than a brother far off.
020	PRO	027	011	Be wise, my son, and make my heart glad, That I may give an answer to him that reproacheth me.
020	PRO	027	012	A prudent man foreseeth the evil, and hideth himself; The simple pass on, and are punished.
020	PRO	027	013	Take his garment who is surety for another; Yea, take a pledge of him who is bound for a stranger.
020	PRO	027	014	He who blesseth his neighbor with a loud voice, rising early for it, It shall be accounted to him as a curse.
020	PRO	027	015	A continual dropping in a very rainy day And a quarrelsome wife are alike.
020	PRO	027	016	He who restraineth her restraineth the wind; And his right hand layeth hold of oil.
020	PRO	027	017	Iron sharpeneth iron; So one man sharpeneth the face of another.
020	PRO	027	018	He that watcheth the fig-tree shall eat its fruit; So he that is careful for his master shall come to honor.
020	PRO	027	019	As in water face answereth to face, So doth the heart of man to man.
020	PRO	027	020	The realms of the dead are never full; So the eyes of man are never satisfied.
020	PRO	027	021	The refining-pot is for silver, and the furnace for gold; So let a man be to the mouth that giveth him praise.
020	PRO	027	022	Though thou shouldst beat a fool in a mortar, Among bruised wheat, with a pestle, Yet will not his folly depart from him.
020	PRO	027	023	Be thou diligent to know the state of thy flocks, And look well to thy herds!
020	PRO	027	024	For riches last not for ever; Not even a crown endureth from generation to generation.
020	PRO	027	025	The hay disappeareth, and the tender grass showeth itself, And the herbage of the mountains is gathered in.
020	PRO	027	026	The lambs are thy clothing, And the goats the price of thy field.
020	PRO	027	027	There is goat's milk enough for thy food, For the food of thy household, And for the sustenance of thy maidens.
020	PRO	028	001	The wicked flee when no one pursueth; But the righteous is as bold as a lion.
020	PRO	028	002	Through the transgression of a land many are its rulers; But through men of prudence and understanding the prince shall live long.
020	PRO	028	003	A poor man who oppresseth the needy Is a sweeping rain which leaveth no food.
020	PRO	028	004	They who forsake the law praise the wicked; But they who keep the law contend with them.
020	PRO	028	005	Wicked men understand not equity; But they who seek the LORD understand all things.
020	PRO	028	006	Better is a poor man who walketh in uprightness, Than he who is perverse in his ways, though he be rich.
020	PRO	028	007	He that keepeth the law is a wise son; But he that is the companion of prodigals bringeth shame on his father.
020	PRO	028	008	He that increaseth his substance by usurious gain Gathereth it for him who will pity the poor.
020	PRO	028	009	He that turneth away his ear from hearing the law, Even his prayer shall be an abomination.
020	PRO	028	010	He that causeth the righteous to go astray in an evil way Shall himself fall into his own pit; But the upright shall have good things in possession.
020	PRO	028	011	The rich man is wise in his own conceit; But the poor man, who hath understanding, will search him through.
020	PRO	028	012	When the righteous rejoice, there is great glorying; But, when the wicked are exalted, men hide themselves.
020	PRO	028	013	He that covereth his sins shall not prosper; But he that confesseth and forsaketh them shall have mercy.
020	PRO	028	014	Happy the man who feareth always! But he who hardeneth his heart shall fall into mischief.
020	PRO	028	015	As a roaring lion and a hungry bear, So is a wicked ruler over a needy people.
020	PRO	028	016	The prince who is weak in understanding is great in oppression; But he who hateth unjust gain shall prolong his days.
020	PRO	028	017	A man who is burdened with life-blood—Let him flee to the pit! let no man stay him!
020	PRO	028	018	He who walketh uprightly shall be safe; But he who is perverse in his ways shall fall at once.
020	PRO	028	019	He who tilleth his land shall have bread enough; And he that followeth after worthless persons shall have poverty enough.
020	PRO	028	020	A faithful man shall abound with blessings; But he that maketh haste to be rich shall not go unpunished.
020	PRO	028	021	To have respect to persons is not good; Since for a piece of bread that man will transgress.
020	PRO	028	022	He who hath an evil eye hasteth after wealth, And considereth not that poverty will come upon him.
020	PRO	028	023	He who rebuketh a man shall afterwards find favor More than he who flattereth with his tongue.
020	PRO	028	024	Whoso stealeth from his father or his mother, And saith, “It is no transgression,” The same is the companion of a robber.
020	PRO	028	025	He who is of a proud heart stirreth up strife; But he that trusteth in the LORD shall be rich.
020	PRO	028	026	He who trusteth in his own understanding is a fool; But he who walketh wisely shall be delivered.
020	PRO	028	027	He who giveth to the poor shall not want; But he that hideth his eyes shall have many a curse.
020	PRO	028	028	When the wicked are exalted, men hide themselves; But, when they perish, the righteous increase.
020	PRO	029	001	He who, being often reproved, hardeneth his neck, Shall suddenly be destroyed, and that without remedy.
020	PRO	029	002	When the righteous are powerful, the people rejoice; But when the wicked beareth rule, the people mourn.
020	PRO	029	003	He who loveth wisdom rejoiceth his father; But he who is a companion of harlots destroyeth his substance.
020	PRO	029	004	A king by equity establisheth a land; But he who receiveth gifts overthroweth it.
020	PRO	029	005	A man who flattereth his neighbor Spreadeth a net for his feet.
020	PRO	029	006	In the transgression of a wicked man there is a snare; But the righteous shall sing and rejoice.
020	PRO	029	007	A righteous man careth for the cause of the poor; A wicked man discerneth not knowledge.
020	PRO	029	008	Scoffers kindle a city into a flame; But wise men pacify wrath.
020	PRO	029	009	If a wise man contend in a cause with a fool, Whether he rage or laugh, there will be no rest.
020	PRO	029	010	The bloodthirsty man hateth the upright; But the righteous seek to preserve his life.
020	PRO	029	011	A fool letteth all his anger come out; But a wise man keepeth it back.
020	PRO	029	012	If a ruler listen to words of falsehood, All his servants become wicked.
020	PRO	029	013	The poor man and the oppressor meet together: The LORD giveth light to the eyes of them both.
020	PRO	029	014	The king that judgeth the poor with uprightness, His throne shall be established for ever.
020	PRO	029	015	The rod and reproof give wisdom; But a child left to himself bringeth shame to his mother.
020	PRO	029	016	When the wicked are powerful, transgression increaseth; But the righteous shall see their fall.
020	PRO	029	017	Chastise thy son, and he will give thee rest; Yea, he will give delight to thy soul.
020	PRO	029	018	Where there is no vision, the people become unruly; But he that keepeth the law, happy is he.
020	PRO	029	019	A servant will not be corrected by words; For, though he understand, he will not obey.
020	PRO	029	020	Seest thou a man hasty in his words? There is more hope of a fool than of him.
020	PRO	029	021	He that bringeth up his servant delicately from childhood Shall have him become a son at the last.
020	PRO	029	022	An angry man stirreth up strife, And a passionate man aboundeth in transgression.
020	PRO	029	023	A man's pride will bring him low; But he that is of a humble spirit shall obtain honor.
020	PRO	029	024	He who shareth with a thief hateth himself: He heareth the curse, but maketh no discovery.
020	PRO	029	025	The fear of man bringeth a snare; But whoso putteth his trust in the LORD shall be safe.
020	PRO	029	026	Many are they who seek the ruler's favor; But every man's judgment cometh from the LORD.
020	PRO	029	027	As the unjust man is an abomination to the righteous, So the upright in his way is an abomination to the wicked.
020	PRO	030	001	The words of Agur, the son of Jakeh, even his prophecy; the inspired utterance of the man to Ithiel, even to Ithiel and Ucal.
020	PRO	030	002	Truly I am more stupid than any man; There is not in me the understanding of a man.
020	PRO	030	003	I have not learned wisdom, Nor have I gained the knowledge of the Most Holy.
020	PRO	030	004	Who hath gone up into heaven and come down? Who hath gathered the wind in his fists? Who hath bound up the waters in a garment? Who hath established all the ends of the earth? What is his name, and what his son's name, if thou knowest?
020	PRO	030	005	Every word of God is pure; A shield is he to them that put their trust in him.
020	PRO	030	006	Add not to his words, Lest he rebuke thee, and thou be found a liar.
020	PRO	030	007	Two things do I ask of thee; Withhold them not from me, before I die!
020	PRO	030	008	Remove far from me falsehood and lies; Give me neither poverty nor riches; Feed me with the food which is needful for me;
020	PRO	030	009	Lest I be full, and deny thee, And say, “Who is the LORD?” Or lest I be poor, and steal, And violate the name of my God.
020	PRO	030	010	Talk not against a servant to his master, Lest he curse thee, and thou suffer for it.
020	PRO	030	011	There is a class of men that curse their fathers, And do not bless their mothers.
020	PRO	030	012	There is a class who are pure in their own eyes, And yet are not washed from their filthiness.
020	PRO	030	013	There is a class, —O how lofty are their eyes, And how are their eyelids lifted up!
020	PRO	030	014	There is a class, whose teeth are swords, And their jaw-teeth knives, To devour the poor from off the earth, And the needy from among men.
020	PRO	030	015	The vampire hath two daughters; “Give! give!” [is their cry.] There are three things which are never satisfied; Yea, four which say not, “Enough!”
020	PRO	030	016	The underworld, and the barren womb; The earth, which is not satiated with water, And fire, which never saith, “It is enough!”
020	PRO	030	017	The eye that mocketh at a father, And scorneth to obey a mother, The ravens of the valley shall pick it out, And the young eagles shall eat it.
020	PRO	030	018	These three things are too wonderful for me; Yea, there are four which I understand not:
020	PRO	030	019	The track of an eagle in the air, The track of a serpent upon a rock, The track of a ship in the midst of the sea, And the track of a man with a maid.
020	PRO	030	020	Such is the way of an adulterous woman; She eateth, and wipeth her mouth, And saith, “I have done nothing wrong.”
020	PRO	030	021	Under three things is the earth disquieted; Yea, under four it cannot bear up:
020	PRO	030	022	Under a servant when he becometh a king, And a fool when he is filled with bread;
020	PRO	030	023	Under an odious woman when she becometh a wife, And a handmaid when she becometh heir to her mistress.
020	PRO	030	024	There are four things which are small upon the earth, Yet are they wise, instructed in wisdom.
020	PRO	030	025	The ants are a people not strong, Yet they prepare in the summer their food.
020	PRO	030	026	The conies are a feeble people, Yet do they make their houses in the rocks.
020	PRO	030	027	The locusts have no king, Yet do they all go forth in bands.
020	PRO	030	028	The lizard seizeth with its hands, And is in king's palaces.
020	PRO	030	029	These three have a graceful step; Yea, four are graceful in their walk:
