023	ISA	064	002	As fire kindleth the dry stubble, As fire causeth water to boil, To make known thy name to thine adversaries, That the nations might tremble at thy presence;
023	ISA	064	003	As thou once didst wonderful things, which we looked not for, And camest down, so that the mountains trembled at thy presence.
023	ISA	064	004	For never have men heard, nor perceived by the ear, Nor hath eye seen, a God beside thee. Who doeth such things for those that trust in him.
023	ISA	064	005	Thou art the friend of those who joyfully do righteousness, Those who remember thee in thy ways. Behold, thou art angry, and we are punished; Long doth the punishment endure, before we are delivered.
